Product Title: Erin Baker's Breakfast Cookies, Chocolate Chunk, Vegan, 3-Ounce Individually Wrapped Cookies, (Pack of 12)
Review: Not too bad before I saw the mold. I was so excited to get these because I thought it would be a great healthy snack to keep at my desk. I ordered these and other flavor (double chocolate chunk) and after eating a couple of each, noticed that one of the cookies had bluish green mold on it. I assumed it was a bad one in the batch. I saw on the manufacturer's website that these should be stored in the freezer since the shelf life is 90 days (due to natural ingredients and no preservatives). I immediately put them in the freezer after getting them 3 weeks earlier. The next 4 cookies I opened had that same mold on it and after I examine the rest, I found that they all were moldy. Apparently Amazon had them stored in their warehouse for a while before I rec'd them. Since there were no dates stamped on the cookies, I have no idea how long they sat in the warehouse before I got them.I will not be ordering these again and will be wary of ordering other food products from Amazon.com. They were great about refunding my money and I will continue to purchase from amazon, just not short shelf life food items.

Product Title: Mission Meats Sugar Free Keto Snacks Grass Fed Beef Bars Whole 30 Gluten Free MSG Free Nitrate Nitrite Free Paleo Healthy Snacks Natural Meat Sticks Beef Jerky Zero Sugar Protein Snacks (12-Count)
Review: Only eat if you like a full salt shaker in every bar. I ordered this and found it WAY TO SALTY!! So much salt that it raised my blood pressure. The beef bar is like a large, moist slim Jim you can by in the gas station store only this has less flavor. And you can't return it!

Product Title: VEGETARIAN PLUS Vegetarian Orange Chicken, 10.5 OZ
Review: You know those soft, artist's pencil erasers you knead in your hand to clean? Like that, with sauce. Completely unpalatable. Would not serve this to a wild coyote (and they'll eat anything). You know those soft, light gray pencil erasers you knead in your hand to clean, and when you stretch them, they get light and airy? This is like that, with sauce. Not even kidding. If you buy this, think of that image while chewing on one of the chicken gumballs (for lack of a better word) for a while--and I assure you it will be a WHILE. The texture of these things falls somewhere between bubble gum, erasers and marshmallows. And they taste like, well, nothing really, with a faint hint of latex, perhaps (might be the bag you microwave it in--which melts!). Yes, this is that bad. Truly an extremely unpleasant thing to put in your mouth. As I chewed the first one up (took a few minutes--they do not break down the way actual FOOD does when you chew it), I could not help but wonder if this would digest properly. I felt like I was eating something from art class, and when I swallowed it, I felt like I had swallowed my chewing gum or something. Absolutely disgusting.This is *not* food.Make sure you read the instructions closely--there is a second bag within the outer bag. Unlike most entrees you heat up in right the packaging, you have to first remove the inner bag from the outer bag. Not sure why they go to the trouble of double-bagging, but this seems misleading (it looks like a larger portion than what is actually in the bag) is not environmentally friendly, and can be confusing--read the instructions closely if you still want to give this a try. Flavor: 0/10, texture: -1/10, packaging 0/10.Oh, and please note the microwave instructions are simply wrong. This was delivered frozen from Whole Foods via Amazon, but I am not sure it is actually meant to be frozen. Following the microwave directions means you are giving this less than half the amount of time actually required to heat up properly. I had to put it in for another two minutes to get it hot enough to serve (it was still partially frozen after following the directions--and I have a 1100w microwave), which made part of the inner bag melt. Really not cool. Pretty sure the end result is a lot of free radicals in your dinner. I threw it out after 2 bites. I absolutely do NOT recommend this product. It was disappointing on every level--just terrible.

Product Title: Revolution Tea - Mesh Infuser Full Leaf Tea - Bombay Chai Black Tea - 20 Bags

One is that it was advertised as BLACK tea and the other that it had peach in it. The picture made it seem there were bits of dried peach in the tea bag. Not only is it CEYLON tea (which I hate) but it tastes nothing like peach and there are no peach bits in the tea bag. Worst of all, after preparing 2 cups (the second with an extra tea bag in the cup to see if I'd get more of a peach taste), I could not get the aftertaste to go away. The aftertaste is a chemical-y cloying nasty experience. I threw the rest of it away and I had bought 2 boxes of it. Don't waste your money.

Product Title: True Lime Black Cherry Limeade, 10 Count, Pack of 2
Review: So gross, I couldn't finish the 1st serving! For a brand with 'True' in the name, they really fall short, and even go so far as to make it difficult to realize all the ingredients are not 'truly' good for you. Such as the fact that it contains, Stevia, which is not mentioned on the front of the box, as it should, to be less deceptive. If it had said it on the front, I would not have bought it! Although Stevia is a 'natural ingredient', that does not automatically make it good for you, or make the product taste good. It does say it in the tiny ingredient list I had to zoom in to see on my phone camera, and on the back. Nowhere is it on the front of the box, where is the place consumers see first. Not to mention that this was truly disgusting! I thought maybe it just needed a second one for the amount of water I had in my jug, but even adding a second serving didn't help. Stevia can cause uncomfortable side effects, like possibly, diarrhea, in those with gastric sensitivities! Stevia is almost as bad as Nutrasweet, which includes phenylalanine, which can cause cancer. So I was looking for something 100% natural, with REAL sugar, and nothing else pretending to be. So if that's what you want too, don't buy this. I had set up an auto subscription, but after tasting this, I immediately cancelled it. Hopefully, my roommate can stand the taste. If not, it was an utter waste of money!

Product Title: Davidson's Tea Bulk, Jasmine Almond with Orange, 16-Ounce Bag
Review: Forget Beer Face, I have a case of Tea Face. Nothing beats a creamy, sugary cup of steaming hot tea on a cold and rainy day (I live in Washington, so I drink a lot of tea).I usually buy loose tea at the grocery store, the price isn't great at $24.99lb but the taste is so far above the drab Lipton tea bags I grew up with that now I can't bear to drink tea from teabags. It's like watching television on a tiny black and white after a few weeks of using a a nice flatscreen, horrible and strange.The price for this Davidson's Irish Breakfast was so much lower than what I get at the grocery store that I thought, 'ha! It must be my lucky day!'Well, when something seems too good to be true, it usually is.From the moment I opened the bag, the tea smelled wrong. I still had a few teaspoons of Irish Breakfast from my last visit to the grocery store and when I compared the teas they looked noticeably different. The grocery tea, hereafter known as 'Good Tea' was darker, the tea leaves more solid with occasional bits of bronzyness scattered willy nilly throughout. The 'Good Tea' was not just slightly darker, it was several shades darker. Also, the Davidson's Irish Breakfast had a grayish-green tinge to it. In fact, it looked a lot like the oolong tea I bought last year and have yet to finish (guess I'm not an oolong girl).I made a cup for my hubby, adding just the right amount of cream and sugar. When he's busy working, sometimes I think he'd drink a cup of soy sauce, as long as it was hot and he didn't have to fetch it himself, he's just so distracted, but he took one sip of the Davidson's and made a sour face. Anyways, he wouldn't drink it and I had to toss my cup down the drain too. There's no amount of sugar, cream or lemon slices that can fix this hellish brew. Sorry, but I'd give this a pass.

Review: GET for the taste, NOT the "health" benefits of dark chocolate. EDIT: OK, I DID call as per the Hershey Company's comments. I am not wrong.This IS processed with alkali (alkali reduces flavonoids which is WHY I eat dark chocolate). A very nice lady DID suggest if I am looking for the health benefits of a dark chocolate NOT DUTCH (or alkali) processed, I look at the ECLIPSE EXTRA DARK CHOCOLATE BAR which is under the HERSHEY banner. I also see a DARK CHOCOLATE called ENDANGERED SPECIES that is NOT DUTCH PROCESSED. It looks like that has a slightly higher Cacao content than Eclipse.I will be checking out NON DUTCH PROCESSED DARK CHOC and will review as I get them. They're available here on Amazon along with other NON ALKALI processed dark chocolate.Sure, tastes fine, but if you're getting for the GREAT HEALTH BENEFITS....you may wish to rethink and get a different brand.I was getting this because of the health benefits of DARK CHOCOLATE. Personally, I prefer milk chocolate. I have gotten these many times as just a treat to keep on hand, thinking of the benefits I am getting.Then I did more research.....THESE are processed with ALKALI....It's also called DUTCH processing. Makes it tastes better, but also...GREATLY reduces the flavonoids which is why I am EATING it in the first place!To get the real health benefits, you need dark chocolate NOT PROCESSED with Alkali....

Product Title: Hoosier Hill Farm Premium Arrowroot Powder, 1 Lb.
Review: Thickens on par with corn starch, NOT xanthan gum - A review for medically-required usage. Have been using Xanthan Gum for a couple of years (after discovering how much cheaper it was, because I had to use so much less, than the Thick-It 2 food thickener. Unfortunately, my kid developed something that is shortened into EoE, and the three triggers are dairy, nuts, xanthan gum. I had really hoped that Arrowroot Powder would have the thickening capabilities of Xanthan Gum, but it sadly does not...not by a mile. I would guess this is more consistent with using plain corn starch. By the time I used enough to barely come close to the thickness we needed (stiff pudding), you could taste the Arrowroot Powder and were also aware of the chalky texture from needing so much Arrowroot Powder. Also, as my kid is a heavy drooler, after a few bites, if any of his (slobber) was on the spoon and re-entered the bowl, the Arrowroot thickness would disappear. I can't recommend this for medically necessary thickening (for poor swallowers), but it might be fine for baking or what have you.

Product Title: HERSHEY'S Organic Milk Chocolate Candy, Individually Wrapped, 1.55 oz Bar (12 Count)
Review: Waxy, hard, plastic like. Doesn't melt in mouth, barely softens in microwave. Use in trail mix. (yuck!!))WHY THE DIFFERENCE? Here are the ingredients for the regular milk chocolate bar versus this organic chocolate bar: I see they omit milk fat and soy lecithin (fat emulsifier), which is basically taking those out is what makes this taste like plastic. They cheaped out taking out these items. If they wanted to make a "soy free" item there are alternatives available. I will not be repurchasing this, I will not recommend it. If the formula ever changes to give it a better mouth feel, then I would consider again. I normally love Hersheys, but this is a huge HECK NO from me.(regular recipe): MILK CHOCOLATE [SUGAR; MILK; CHOCOLATE; COCOA BUTTER; MILK FAT; LECITHIN (SOY); PGPR; NATURAL FLAVOR](organic): ORGANIC MILK CHOCOLATE (ORGANIC SUGAR, ORGANIC COCOA* BUTTER, ORGANIC MILK, ORGANIC CHOCOLATE).---->>>1 star. My rating is based primarily how this tastes in comparison to regular Hershey's chocolate bars. I think it is fair to do this because I am sure there are others that may give this a try thinking that it will at least resemble a Hershey's product. NOPE! It is an entirely different product. The taste, texture, and smell is just different. It isn't "bad" for chocolate flavor, but it is incredibly disappointing if expecting it to resemble the original base formula. There are other healthy recipe chocolates out there that far exceed this.It does NOT have a good mouth feel; it does not have a melt in mouth creaminess to it. It doesn't even melt when placed in microwave. Perhaps with more time it would, but I just put it in there to give it a try---I was just curious to see if it would soften up with any sort of heat. I gave it 10 seconds and expected it to soften. Nope. I gave it another 10, and then another 10. Only at the 30 second mark did it become less "hard", but it didn't soften. There was no glorious chocolate experience. Had that been the regular chocolate bar, it would have been soft at 10 seconds. Or in my mouth, or in my pocket.Waxy, hard, plastic like. Once I get chewing the chocolate flavor is ok, but it doesn't taste like Hershey's, at all. And as mentioned, sure doesnt feel like it.I'll stick to the regular Hershey's for the occasional chocolate treat. I dont eat this stuff enough to try to switch to a "healthy" version. I got this because I was curious. Other reviews said it was bad. I thought how bad can it be? I am an avid reviewer and like trying different stuff and giving it my thoughts in a review. I should have saved my money and heeded the bad reviews because this is not a pleasing product at all. I had also bought it to be used as part of a treat bag for some of my older friends. Just a "thinking of you" gift. I will NOT be adding this in. I would be embarrassed to add this in. I tucked it into my cupboard for possible use in baking, or for use as barter if TEOTWAWKI occurs. :PSo yeh, not one to waste.. I'll use up these bars in baking or break them up for use in a trail mix. But for noshing? nope, no way. SO DISAPPOINTING!

My wife ground some the night prior and stored it in the mason jar which she uses early in the morning if everyone‚Äôs asleep.Okay first: the coffee is about the quality of generic motel coffee. Actually, I‚Äôd rather have motel coffee. This ‚Äúsignature‚Äù label stuff is disgusting.Second: it‚Äôs weak....Third: it grinds chunky and weird. You get big chunky bits. And I know all about coffee grinds, I used to be a barista at an actual cafe (not a chain). I know what I‚Äôm doing.Fourth: I think the ‚Äúsheen‚Äù of the beans is somehow manufactured, not the actual production of healthy oily beans and that‚Äôs why it doesn‚Äôt grind correctly. As if they were old dry stale beans and they lather them in some oil at some point before packaging.I even tried to just make cold brew out of it because you go through a lot of beans to make a good batch......and it‚Äôs disgusting. I tried a percolator too. There‚Äôs just no win for this coffee.I think all the good reviews are a mix of people who maybe got a good batch, false reviews, people who just don‚Äôt care if coffee tastes like crap because it‚Äôs so cheap and maybe at some point they were making good coffee and due to immense pressure to make more......they have failed roasting standards.I‚Äôm tossing the bag.

Product Title: Eggo Thick and Fluffy Frozen Waffles, Frozen Breakfast, Breakfast Food, Original, 11.6oz Box (6 Waffles)
Review: I don't know why I keep hoping Eggo waffles will one day be good. I love waffles. I grew up with my dad making them on Sunday mornings every week like clockwork throughout my childhood. I have his recipe (unbeatable, and I've tried), and I have two fantastic waffle irons, one antique like his, and another modern, high-end one. Both truly make fantastic waffles. Thing is, it's a hassle and a mess to make proper waffles. You have to use multiple mixing bowls and measuring cops, get flour everywhere sifting, and then fold the egg whites in after beating them to soft peaks right before you pour the batter into the waffle iron. This works--well. I am just too lazy for it sometimes. Also, the racket of the mixer beating the egg whites is perhaps better enjoyed post-coffee.Hence the foray into the world of frozen waffles. I've tried a lot of them, and none of them are anything like real waffles--seriously, not even close. Oddly those weird Kodiak Cakes seem to be the best frozen waffles out there to my taste, even though they are high-protein (6g/ea). I gave up on Eggo waffles long ago, as they really have nothing to do with actual waffles. They are almost a different food, definitely very Americanized. The US food industry (P&G, etc) seems to do that--take a good food and "Americanize" it into something ultra-cheap to produce which ends up being almost unrecognizable, far from authentic. Somehow I had a hope that this might be better as they were a specialty product. Nope, same batter, just poured (no doubt by the ton) into a slightly different machine designed to make a slightly taller waffle. Tossed them after the first two.Good thing they are ultra-cheap. Lesson finally learned, perhaps.

Product Title: Nature's Guru Instant Tender Coconut Water Powder Original 10 Count Single Serve On-the-Go Drink Packets (Pack of 4)
Review: Watch your coconut water labels, whether it's liquid or powdered product. (Updated 1/6/16). This is mostly sugar that's why sugar is listed first under "Ingredients:" in the packaging (FDA requires that the packaging lists each ingredient from most in the product to least in that product. Sugar is first). Next is Minerals, well potassium is a mineral that we all need and it's listed as the second ingredient, but I find it odd that it is an ingredient since the potassium should be in the coconut water powder, so they are adding potassium instead of us getting it naturally from the coconut water. Why do I know this? By FDA regulations, ingredients are the things you put into it. If it was all coconut water powder, we wouldn't see Potassium in the Ingredients list, we'd see it under the "Nutrition Label."Coming in dead last in the list? Coconut Water! I have been duped. I have been using coconut water flavored sugar. The least ingredient is what we thought we were buying.I've been using the product for over a year and put 2 of them in my morning protein shake... and now I find out it's sugar with some minerals and a bit of coconut water to top it off. Was it good in my shake, yeah but it is flavored sugar so let's keep that focus. If I stir it into 8oz of water, it's very unpleasant. My mistake was not caring what it tastes like in just water because I was getting my potassium boost from it in my morning shake and the price was right.I have found my replacement. Unfortunately, not at Amazon because all the coconut water powder products are too pricey for how often I use it. The replacement is slightly cheaper than Amazon, but the savings is worth the extra hassle of going to a different site and buying it separately.

Review: Don't buy this in winter it will freeze and break. As you can see from my pictures, the bottle arrived nearly empty, partly filled with ice. The box packaging and the Amazon box were soaked with 'whiskey' too.So the reason I am writing this instead of a review of how nice this is with Coke or mixed with cider and a slice of lemon is that for some reason you cannot return this item or get a refund.So, that's something that I think people should know before they buy this. Also, because of the way items are bundled together in shipping, this could not only end up freezing and spilling, it could end up damaging other shipped items.

Product Title: Lakewood Organic Super Veggie Low Sodium Juice, 32 Ounce (Pack of 6)
Review: TOO SPICY!!!! I'm not a fan of commercially made vegetable juice, but I drink it because I don't have to prepare it and it's supposed to be good for me. When my hands were not crippled with arthritis, I used to make my own delicious vegetable juice each morning with carrots, broccoli, cabbage, and cucumber(s). After the arthritis ruined my hands, I used to water down the low sodium V-8 from Campbell's (half H2O, half juice), warm it up, and drink it as a broth. It's OK plain or with a sandwich, but by comparison to homemade juice, V-8 tastes awful. Then while surfing the net I discovered that the other "natural" ingredients in V-8 are milk, poultry, fish, and beef. If I were vegan or followed a kosher diet, adding ingredients that aren't disclosed up front or on the back label, for that matter, could be disappointing. Anyway, learning about the deception motivated me to find an alternative. I happen to love Lakewood pineapple juice so I decided to give their Super Veggie a try.It tastes pretty bad and has the added negative of being too spicy/hot for me. If Lakewood had omitted or substituted those hot peppers with a more palatable vegetable I probably would have given it three or four stars, but it has to be content with the two b/c I still don't think that processed vegetable juice tastes good. However, Lakewood Organic Super Veggie is truly low in sodium, so I warm it up without diluting it and add whole milk to neutralize the taste of the spicy, stinging hot peppers. Next I'll try low fat or no fat milk and see if it has the same effect. For people who like hot peppers, enjoy!

Product Title: Taylors of Harrogate Green Tea with Jasmine, 20 Count (Pack of 6)
Review: The shy Earl Grey for the timid. This can be either a shy Earl Grey or a shy Darjeeling. Shy in the sense that the distinctive notes that gives the tea their name aren't really there.For those who are not a fan of Bergamot, but want a black tea that hangs around in the background that doesn't come forward by much, this is the tea for you. The complete opposite of the Earl Grey Roi by M.F. The French brand can definitely make this one seem dainty. The British are not known to be dainty. Not in the teas usually nor in their food. But this one, dainty would be the word.It's not a bad tea. The color and flavor of black tea is there. The Bergamot on the other hand is quite absent. More of tease to the palate. It's a gentle tea that is smoother than T of H Afternoon Darjeeling. Makes a good tea to get through the day. Can be refreshing with some ice cubes. Easy on the palate and can go with almost any dish.The nice thing about T of H sachet is that they are all individually wrapped in a sealed bag that is waterproof. Upon opening the bag, the lack of aroma pretty much gave a good idea of how the tea would taste. Either this has been sitting on the shelf too long or this is the usual way it is made. I would not doubt it since it fits the theme of most T of H teas. Their teas tend to be on the weak and lacking side. They make T------- seem more present and prominent in taste.Even Bradleys has more of an aroma and that would be classified as a nickel tea. Although this is better than that brand in terms of not being able to smell the cheap Bergamot aroma. I would not mind drinking this on any given day if I had nothing else better. But I would not exactly think of it as an Earl Grey since it lacks that scent.For those who love their Earl Grey, this is not the one. For those who are new to Earl Grey and want a good introduction, this is not the one. For a smooth black tea that you can add citrus to or drink as is both hot or cold that lacks character, this is the one.Out of the different brands of Earl Grey I have tried, I would recommend the Earl Grey Supreme by H & Sons. The silver tips adds another angle to the tea. It is definitely a Darjeeling base that stands out equally to the Bergamot if not more than the Bergamot. That one makes a sturdy tea that allows citrus to be added and still taste great.Surprisingly, I did not expect the T of H to be this lacking on such a classic tea. I would go through this more often than cheap Earl Grey mainly for it not having that Bergamot aroma. When you double the tea bags into one cup, what you get is the Darjeeling base. The Bergamot is still hiding some where. It's missing a lot of notes quite similar to their Afternoon Darjeeling.Think of it this way. Afternoon Darjeeling without the woodsy bitterness and you have this one that they call Earl Grey. This Earl Grey with the woodsy bitterness added and you have their Afternoon Darjeeling that is rough and unrefined in taste.Most Earl Greys have a Darjeeling base. This one has the color and taste of a Darjeeling. But it lacks so many natural notes that you question what kind of Darjeeling it is other than the bottom of the barrel or something sitting around too long that a lot of flavor has faded away. The flavor is a little more bitter and heavier when you double the amount, but then it seems more Darjeeling than anything else.It is best to consider this as a black tea or plain Darjeeling and nothing more. Perhaps one can make their own Earl Grey by adding some form of grapefruit into the tea. It lacks the distinctive aroma and taste of Bergamot. This one fades into the background without a stand.I give it 2 stars for being a decent black tea. 1 star for being an Earl Grey. 4 stars for T of H keeping their teas consistent even if the theme is weak. Aside from their Afternoon Darjeeling, it is the brand to go to if you want something tamed, mild, not distinctive enough in a good way and don't want any surprises. The aroma is lacking too. It's a Darjeeling that lacks a lot of character. How T of H has managed to find a weak Darjeeling to go with a weak Bergamot and sell so much of it is amazing.I usually give certain brands a try on a variety of different teas so that I would know if they carry a similar theme or if they vary greatly. T of H does not vary much. The box and bag is usually a nicer presentation than the taste of the tea.For a good Earl Grey tea experience, the H & S does a good job with their supreme since there is more than one. You get the combo of the tea and Bergamot in a good way.For those who ever wonder if there is a tea that says, "BERGAMOT" more than tea, the M.F. brand is good with that and they have 3 versions with E.G. Roi being the most prominent one. As in it hangs around your taste buds longer than a breath mint can. The bitterness and aroma stays around for a long time. The leaves smell strong when they are dry and when the tea is made, your palate would definitely be knocked over. The brand has been around since the 1800's. They have their fair share in testing what works and what doesn't after a while. Every other brand on the market is quite subtle on the Bergamot.The M.F. brand is exclusive so it is not that easy to find it in the U.S. and most of the world. Only certain co. carry the brand, but it's very very limited in flavors. It is usually their signature tea that is sold. It is a hit and miss on flavors. High quality, but it is similar to a selection of pastries. Not every kind agrees with every palate. T of H is more predictable which is sort of the theme for many British made teas.If you want Bergamot that zings and has your senses wake up with a soprano note, the F&M Earl Grey would do that. That is from smelling the unopened tin that has not been opened before. I would not ever call Bergamot lemony since usually the taste is heavier and more similar to a grapefruit. The F&M one has high citrus notes.Out of all the different citrus to add to an Earl Grey, the pink grapefruit compliments it best. If you add any sweetness to it, the sweet will be in front and the bitter will come from the back as an after taste. Quite enjoyable. You know you have a good Earl Grey when you can add a citrus note to it and it still taste good. When you add that and you don't taste much of anything else then the tea is lacking in something.A splash of citrus usually compliments an Earl Grey if the Bergamot is present enough. If not, the citrus won't do much. It seems many like the Lady Grey and not realize that is what it is when they add lemon to their Earl Grey.If you add flowers to a Lady Grey, it is called a Baroness Grey. Different citrus and ingredients equal a different name since it changes the drink.

Review: I had high hopes for this brand. I have had so many brands of stevia, some that have even come and gone, that I've lost count. I was hoping it would not have the bitterness issue so that I could use this as a cheaper alternative to what I currently love (i.e., Select Stevia).The old adage, you get what you pay for applies here. This is about 1/3 of the cost of Select Stevia, I made my usual protein shake but this time used Stevita Stevia Clear. When I started drinking it, there was no bitterness detectable. One huge hurdle is now behind me and I didn't think there would be another. Unfortunately, about a 1/4th of the way through the drink I started noticing this strange aftertaste. It wasn't a bitterness, but it was unpleasant. I couldn't finish my protein drink because of it.I don't want to waste it, so for every 5 drops of Select Stevia, I put 2 of this brand. When it's finished, I won't buy another. Yes, I know it makes Select Stevia seem cheaper if I always combine the two stevia brands, but I'm only doing this because I don't want to waste the Stevita purchase. Select Stevia alone is still better than the combination of the two brands. I am just doing this to use up the Stevita.No matter what, I keep coming back to Select Stevia. I know everyone likes different stevia brands. It really comes down to your preference. I suspect my tastes are too sensitive (not a good thing because there are a lot of foods I can't eat because of this).I think for $7.50 and current prices of liquid stevia, you may want to give this a try. It wasn't the most awful stevia I ever had. Actually, far from it. If it was, I would have thrown it in the garbage. It's just not as pleasant tasting as Select Stevia for me. I'm sticking with Select Stevia.

Product Title: Kraft Deluxe White Cheddar Easy Microwavable Macaroni and Cheese Cups (4 ct Pack, 2.39 oz Cups)
Review: Not as good as the boxes. When I was younger, I loved making the boxed Kraft Mac and Cheese (orange), usually adding frozen peas to the mac when it was nearly cooked. My sisters and I could finish off a box as a snack in the afternoon, we never had it as a serious meal. I don't know that Mom and Dad ever tasted it, but we sure enjoyed the fast, easy hot snack that was fun to pick at with a fork, often directly from the pot. My family still enjoys the boxed Kraft mac and cheese, adding peas, broccoli, or kale, always finishing with garlic and pepper. We've tried other boxed mac and cheese packages and none compares, even after decades of attempts. Finding a pack of these Kraft Deluxe Easy Mac White Cheddar Macaroni and Cheese at an insanely good price, I purchased them for the kids because they like to receive individual sized servings of foods from me. The last mac and cheese cups were not good at all, made by another manufacturer. These are okay, not terrible, and they can be improved with condiments if you want to spend the time trying to improve bland and pasty mac and cheese that fills about 1/3 of the cup. For an emergency, they are acceptable if you have a microwave, as a meal of mac and cheese, we all prefer the original blue boxes over these cups and would not purchase them again even at an insanely good price.

Product Title: Annie's Homegrown Real Aged Cheddar Microwave Mac & Cheese with Gluten Free Pasta, 2 Ct, 2.01 OZ Cups (Pack of 6)
Review: Macaroni texture is good, that's about it. First of all, some of the 12 cups I received had plastic seals which were separated from the plastic cups, so the white powder coating the macaroni spilled all over and around the 6 packages of 2 cups each, coating interior of the Annie's box. Maybe it occurred during transit, maybe it occurred while in the Amazon facility, but wherever it occurred, we didn't get to consume those cups. I did salvage the cheese packets which are separate but included in each cup. These are simpler than pie to prepare and they take only about 2 minutes in the microwave, a few seconds to stir in the cheese powder, and an additional minute or two to meld together into a single serving of gluten-free mac and cheese made by a company of which I am a fan. Unfortunately, the solid texture of the pasta doesn't make up for the rather bland taste of the finished product. It's not salty, so that's a good thing in my opinion, but it really does need additions to turn this into an enjoyable and nutritious meal. Adding precooked vegetables like broccoli, peas or carrots will be an improvement that most kids can get into, especially if they are cut into small pieces or interesting shapes. Shredded carrots can be snuck in and will contribute a sweetness for those who shy away from vegetables. There is plenty of space in the cup since the water fill line is about halfway down from the top and the pasta doesn't swell much when cooked. I'm glad we tried these but I will not be repurchasing. All parts of the packaging are recyclable, just separate the paper from the plastic cups and rinse the cups.

Review: Overall disappointing. I tend to avoid writing reviews -- particularly when I have nothing of substance to add to what are already a significant number of positive reviews, which seems generally the case with my purchases.I usually purchase either Twinings (easier to open packaging) or Bigelow (slightly stronger flavor) lemon/ginger tea in 100/120 unit orders - neither was available at a reasonable price when I last re-ordered mid-December 2020. So I was very curious to try Taylors. Sadly the experience was disappointing. Flavor was significantly weaker than either of the two competitors, but what was most vexing was the individual packaging - the scoring of the packet was faulty, frustrating attempts to open, leading to crude tears which often rips the tag; on at least one third of the tea bags I've attempted to use to date, the portions of the strings have been sewn into the bag so that they are too short to be useful. While I don't know whether this is one unfortunate defective box of tea bags, I'm not prepared spend any more money to find out otherwise.(Also curious that Amazon [not a third party seller] is now selling this item for $8.00 more than I paid for it here six weeks ago).

Product Title: Fritos Hot Bean Dip , 9 Ounce
Review: Not hot and just not tasty - DIY instead. Good bean dip is savory and delicious, typically made with pork and spices. This was just ...paste. Refried beans with some faint flavors added in, but just not something I wanted to eat. I had a small amount of it and threw it out. Do yourself a favor - make your own bean dip. It's a snap: fry up some pork chorizo (recommended), and/or finely diced bacon. When fully cooked, add a can of refried beans in with some tapatio or cholula to taste, stirring the whole works together thoroughly. Let it cool and refrigerate what you don't eat. Delicious. VASTLY superior to this product.

Hormel chili is pretty revolting--the absolute bottom rung of the ladder of chilis--so just imagine that squeezed into skinny little mini tamales with a watery pseudo-ranchero sauce. These have little in common with actual tamales, which are delicious. These are a last-resort meal only. Kept in the cupboard for when you run out of literally everything else.

Review: I drank this as my only brand of Matcha for years....HOWEVER. Used to love it, now I feel overpriced and over-rated.EDIT: I have purchased this MANY times. Last time I purchased, didn't feel so well after drinking. Tried it several times. Was not old, wasn't expired. Wondering if things have changed at DoMatcha. I used this for YEARS previously. Now...not so much.OK, I've bought the much more expensive "ceremonial" grade, but unless you're using it straight (and even then, I like the taste), I think it's got GREAT color and taste. MUCH better deal because it's second harvest (and you should check out nutritionally, not such a bad thing) and love the sustained, slower energy boost than I get from coffee (that takes you high than leaves you flat). There is no way to tell the age of the coffee pods and the pod label is different from what is shown on the advertising picture. It also says Noir Soyeux on the label with other French wording around the base of the pod.I am hesitant to use it and seriously consider returning them. The seller needs to be up front about what the buyer is getting and include the best by date!!Update: I just saw that this item is NOT returnable! This makes me very suspicious and concerned about using the coffee. Buyer beware!!

Product Title: SACO Mix 'n Drink Instant Skim Milk, Fat-Free, GMO-Free, Gluten-Free, Nut-Free, rBST Free, High Calcium and Protein, Makes 10 Gallons
Review: UPDATE - pretty decent way to have milk without any going bad. UPDATE @ 2014-03-06fyi, the per-serving cost works out thus ...local grocery store generic dry milk = 0.17 us$this product = 0.38 us$ [61.49 us$ / 160 servings]more than double is far too high a price for convenience. [*sigh ...*]*****UPDATE @ 2013-09-22the price on 2013-05-03 was us$42 and is now us$63. that 50% increase is beyond comprehension. i cannot recommend this item when the price is so unreasonable.rated a TWO since the cost is now insane.*****howdy y'all,this is pretty decent stuff. i used to really dislike dry milk cuz of the odd odor and rather unpleasant flavor. the odor - something similar to milk on the verge of going bad - doesn't seem to be there any more, thank goodness. i've become accustomed to the flavor. [*grin*] i don't drink it straight, tho. it's used for cereal, anti-weight-loss drinks and cooking.the price works out well. i use a tad more than the recommended amount to mix a pitcher of milk since i like the flavor a tad more that way. plus, of course, it never goes bad on me since i make only just enuf in each batch to last a few days.rated a THREE cuz it does what i expect and nothing more.take care,lee

Review: Excellent mayonnaise. I received it today and the expiration date is almost there. This is the second mayonnaise I buy with expiration date within 1 month. Flavor is very good.3 stars because of the expiration date.Expiration date is very importante when you buy a product.

Product Title: Harney & Sons Flavored Black Tea, Paris, 4 Ounce
Review: Not great, not terrible. 5/5 Aroma, 2/5 Body. Let me start by saying that the cheap price of ~$3 USD for the tin is a large portion of the rating. I opened it and it smells like cheap liquid smoke and nothing else, which I wasn't used to for Lapsangs. Combine this smell with a spelling error on the tin and I was convinced i got a fake, but opted to brew it anyway. It brewed to the color featured in the photos, and tasted like a very mild version of the smell. If you don't like the scent of opening a bag of cheap extra-smoky flavored jerky in your nose, you probably wont like this. The flavor, when i can taste anything at all aside from the mild smoky flavor, is even more mild. I was kind of hoping for this tea to figuratively punch me in the mouth with smoke since it was so bold and smoky in the tin, but it didn't come close. Maybe mix this with another more full-bodied tea.I've had better smoked teas for sure, but for the price, it's reminiscent enough for me. I loved smoked teas and this one isn't too terrible, but maybe not a good first choice for someone who is new to Lapsang Souchong.

Product Title: Boost Nutritional Drinks Glucose Control with Extra Nutrient Support Drink, Very Vanilla, Carton, 8 Fl Oz, Pack of 24
Review: A nutritional drink that helps keep blood sugar in control. My dad's doctor recommended these Boost Glocuse Control drinks to help keep his blood sugar levels within an acceptable range for his condition. When he was taking a different supplement drink his blood sugar level would spike, but after a month of using these Boost drinks we have seen his blood sugar readings become normal again. 4g of sugar per Boost drink still seems high, but is still lower or the same compared to the other options on the market. My dad said he likes the chocolate and vanilla flavor a lot. The cartons are easy to hold for him, but he said the twist cap is difficult for him to open. One issue he does experience after drinking these Boost Glucose Control drinks is that he will need to use the bathroom afterwards. Wish the price of these drinks are more affordable. Ordering these drinks through Amazon was easy and straightforward. All the orders were delivered undamaged and had long expiration dates.

Product Title: Gardein Plant-based Chili No Beans, Vegan, 15 oz
Review: Tastes better than it smells, not unlike any other canned chili. Tastes good, well spiced, but it still has like a canned food flavor.

Product Title: Costa Farms Live Indoor Plant, Little Fiddle Leaf Fig Tree, Indoor House Plant, in Premium Rose Gold Decor Planter, 1-2 Feet Tall
Review: Traumatic arrival, but bouncing back slowly with some TLC. I love this plant and when I moved into my new place a few weeks ago I decided it was time to gift myself with this new baby. I was so excited to open it and add it to the new home only to find the poor plant practically suffocating in the box. There was dirt everywhere and barely enough dirt to cover the roots that were completely removed from the nursery. A lot of leaves had shed and many began to brown. It seems that this plant has been through quite a ride with little protection. I just hope it‚Äôs as resilient to bounce back from it.Update: after a day I noticed the leaves were beginning to yellow on the top and a few more from the bottom have fallen. The plant was unable to stand without the bamboo stick so I gave it a pick-me-up by wiping its leaves with warm water and paper towel, topped off the roots with some dirt (although it appears it needs to be replanted very soon), and gave it a good drink under a grow light. It appears it‚Äôs doing a lot better.

Product Title: Ghirardelli Mug Brownie Mix, Chocolate Peanut Butter, 9.2 Ounce, 6 Count
Review: I ‚Äòtweaked‚Äô it and imo it's both good and bad - I would recommend it anyway! PROS: Easy and fast to make Good taste Thick, gooey consistency Single-serve packs convenient (1 at a time great for a single person), no leftovers Fast, no prep, no extra ingredients needed Price very reasonable Not readily available in ‚Äòregular‚Äô stores (at least in northern NJ where I live) Arrived UNdamamaged - every single box! Arrived not expired!CONS: ‚ÄòMug‚Äô size is not correct - 8oz., it's much too large! Mine (the ones I have made already) had small hard pieces like nuts in it, vs. choc. chips (I spit them out, they didn't even melt) Cleaning the mug/cup is not easy or fast, takes more time to clean than to make and eatSUGGESTIONS: Use a micro safe 5-6 ounce cup max per each packet Replace water with syrup or liquor (I've used Torani's Toasted Marshmallow Syrup and Chocolate Biscotti liquor so far) - do NOT use a thick syrup like the ones for *ice cream as they will be too thick Top with ice cream, whipped cream, *sauce for ice cream, nuts, M&M‚Äôs, etc. ***check expiration date when received - it's clearly shown (amazingly the one I got is good for about 1 1/2 years, as compared with many other food and beverage items I've bought online!) Make in a micro-safe disposable cup to avoid the awful, time consuming cleanup (esp. If you're going to eat it before going to bed and don't want an impossible to clean dish when you get up in the morning!)OVERALL SUMMARY: I would recommend this product. 1) during this time (‚Äô20/‚Äô21) with the widespread Covid and the quarantines, closed stores, fears of being near other people 2) during the winter if snowed in and can't go out grocery shopping 3) for a quick sugar fix, snack, dessert, single-use packsHope this short and ‚Äòsweet‚Äô review is helpful to someone looking for this particular dessert mix!

Product Title: Intenso Aroma DI Caffe Forte Espresso E.S.E. Pads/Cialde/Servings, 150 Pods
Review: Good for the price, but a bit too nutty flavor - strong Robusta presence. If you want smoother flavor go with their Classic pod. Not bad for the price - definitely not the highest quality espresso - but it does make a good latte. Much better for milk-based drinks than as straight espresso or americanos. Good packing - pulls a nice slow shot with good crema. Good to have around to test with new espresso machines. Also good for a quick, cheap drink.I'm sure these have a larger blend of Robusta beans - there is a strong nutty flavor, which I don't prefer with my espresso. I like a smaller blend of Robusta mixed in with mostly Arabica beans. If you want what I'm talking about, go with their Classic pods, which I much prefer over these.

Review: Good product. Just damaged this time around. I buy this product often at amazon, as well as at Costco. While I am not a sardines' "aficionada," my little Pom just loves it! These sardines have good flavor (according to my mother for whom I buy them too).The product was leakint as it arrived home. I opened the amazon box in which the sardines came in.Today, I got ready to mix my "dog's delicatessens" into her food. As I get the package, still air-tide wrapped, it was all soaked, and foamy inside. Obviously, the product had decomposed and fermented inside the damaged cans.Beside dissapointed, I repulsed by this overwhelming odor.After floshing the waste throuth the toilet, washing the disgusting cans to spare my neighbors having to deal with such smell, I tossed the empty cans in the outside trash can.I am calling and requesting a either a replacement, or a full refund of my money.

Product Title: Marquis | Zero Sugar Yerba Mate | Caffeine With Benefits | Healthy Natural Energy Drink Alternative | Vegan & Non-GMO | Organic Plant Based Caffeine | 12 Pack, 12 fl oz cans (Variety)
Review: no flavor in the lychee-peach, cant taste either flavor, results in terrible bitter experience. I have the variety pack. I bought it on sale. Glad I did, as I am not liking this all that much and I would have been more disappointed in a full price item. I have a high tolerance for unpleasant, but this actually turned me off, especially the Lychee Peach. Which is truly disappointing because that is the flavor that caught my interest. I love love love Lychee, and I figured peach would be a nice pairing. It tastes NOTHING like lychee or peach. I could not tell you what I was tasting other than spine shivering bitterness. It is almost like they didnt add any actual flavor to the bottle.I dont need sweet, I dont need a lot of flavor, but I need to be able to tell what the flavor is and I need not to drink it and cringe. I shuddered with every sip until I finally just gave up. Energy drinks can be a bit unpleasant, and some taste best super cold, and some kind of grow on me. I tend to overlook some unpleasant for the benefit of lifting the mind fog and giving me a little pep.This (the lychee peach) is so off putting that I ended up not finishing the can. I HATE WASTING food or drink. But this was so.. blegh. Maybe I can salvage it by mixing it with something. I gave the "Super Berry" a try, and that was much better--not great, but it is palatable. I can drink that. It has a berry flavor. I am very familiar with all ingredients and flavors here, so I know what to expect. I am hoping the yuzu (a citrus flavor) is good, and I have high hoped for the mango ginger. But I wont know for a couple more days. I haven't worked through the other 2 flavors yet. So far it is 50-50. Perhaps I will update.I like that it has 100 mg of caffeine. Not too much. I have had some caffeinated drinks that are 200+ mg, and that is too much for me since I already drink coffee. I like an energy drink to top me off, for when I want something cold and bubbly, and for times I am about to start a chore or do a work out that will benefit from the added "motivation". I dont need a lot of caffeine, just usually a little bump. So this having 100 mg and being listed on the front of the bottle is a positive about this product.Also has some vitamin C and some B vitamins.RATING: I am going with middle of road rating of 3. I think it is "OK", and that is only because at least one flavor of the 4 has been good. The lychee peach is terribad (1 star). Super berry is decent (4 stars).I like what they are trying to do here. I have had similar products (where the ingredients are much healthier than other energy drinks), but truly this has been the most disappointing. I doubt it would ever be a repurchase unless one of the flavors truly make me feel good and tastes good.

Product Title: Louisville Vegan Jerky - Smoked Chipotle, Vegetarian and Vegan Friendly Jerky, 21 Grams of Non-GMO Soy Protein, Gluten-Free Ingredients (Pack of 5, 3 Ounces)

I plan to use it as a replacement for seasoned tomato sauce in my own custom pizza sauce recipe (it is very hard to find seasoned tomato sauce without citric acid nowadays).

Product Title: 365 by Whole Foods Market, Ripe Green Pitted Olives, 6 Ounce
Review: Not as good as the major brand. Firstly, from some of the reviews it seems like people don't know their olive varieties. Green ripe olives are normally a bit buttery, a bit oily (very much like good EVOO) and firm. These are not the briney vinegary type (which I also love) I am an olive fan, all types of olives.This particular type was banned in US for quite awhile because of its freckles (google) when they came back I no longer saw the "california" brand on the shelves but "pearls". Pearls were just fine. I actually picked up a case online once and finished them off pretty quickly (I love olives).With my WF order I thought I would see what they had and picked up a few cans of 365. A bit disappointed when I tried for the first time last night. They seemed about a size smaller than the pearls and unfortunately many of them were mushy. Most of them actually. Taste is still good but the mushiness left me wanting and considering price, I would rather order the pearls instead if only I could get them without ordering by the case. My local market stopped carrying this variety and online is my only option.

Product Title: Svelte Organic Protein Shake, Variety Pack, 11 Fl Oz (Pack of 12)
Review: Hurts stomach, maybe from stevia? Taste is good but it hurts my stomach and makes me feel bloated! I‚Äôm not sure what it is but I don‚Äôt usually use stevia so I am wondering if that is it. I wanted to like these but now I am so bummed. Still trying to find a dairy free breakfast shake that doesn‚Äôt hurt.

Product Title: ORIGIN, 100% Natural Spring Water, 900 mL, Recycled Plastic Bottle, 12 Pack
Review: Missing the spring. Missing the spring. Feel silly missing an aunt and uncle now the spring. Since I moved to Florida had to import this most everything doesn‚Äôt do well in transport with the high heat been leaning toward carbonation

Product Title: Lundberg Family Farms Sprouted Brown Basmati Rice, 16 Ounce
Review: THE WORDING ON THIS PACKAGE IS MISLEADING. IT IS ... THE WORDING ON THIS PACKAGE IS MISLEADING. IT IS NOT JUST WILD RICE IT IS A BLEND OF RICE AND WILD RICE.

Product Title: Hostess Variety Pack | Cupcakes, Cinnamon Rolls, Danish, Ding Dongs, Twinkies, Zingers | 30 Count

Product Title: Rovira Export Soda Crackers 21 oz. bucket (Pack of 1)
Review: Taste great but came crumbled in foil... Was not able to make peanut butter or cheese sandwiches because product was crushed/ crumbled...

Product Title: Splash Blast, Flavored Water Beverage, Lemon Flavor, 16.9 Fl Oz Plastic Bottles, 6 Pack
Review: I love lemon water, but this has sucralose & other ingredients. Do you find yourself putting lemons into your drinks? Well this water already has it for you. Its a bit too lemony for me, but it tastes very good over ice or chilled out of the refrigerator. Like water down lemonade. Drinking at room temperature doesn't taste as good. I thought I was buying water with lemon, but they added sucrolose to help reduce the bitterness of lemon. So you actually end up with sweetener, citric acid, and other preservatives.

Product Title: Shortbread House of Edinburgh's Shortbread Fingers Selection Box, 8.8 Ounce (Pack of 2)
Review: Ok, not great. Very crumbly, texture seemed a bit grainy. Taste was just fine, not to die for good.

Product Title: Cantuccini (5.29 oz), Traditional Italian almond biscotti [3 pack] Imported from Italy
Review: Different from another brand. I thought I was buying something like a mini biscotti. They are smaller, which I like, but they are softer as if they are stale. There is a slight lemon taste which I am not a fan of. The overall taste is good. I will see how the other boxes taste before final judgment.

Product Title: Pure Pink Himalayan Ancient Sea Salt 2.5 lb - Gourmet Grade - Fine Grain
Review: Otherwise the salt is good. I wish it had been in. The salt took on the plastic lf the container. Otherwise the salt is good. I wish it had been in glass

Product Title: Vermont Smoke and Cure Uncured Summer Sausage - Antibiotic Free and Gluten Free - Great on Charcuterie Boards With Cheese - 6oz
Review: Not A Bad Product. This summer sausage is NOT a bad product, it doesn't suit my taste. For others they may really like it. I will describe it to youand you can decide for yourself. Here goes, this sausage is very, very, greasy, it has a VERY mild flavor and not much taste.You can tell that it is not chemically made. It is very clean tasting to almost no taste. I do believe that care was taken makingthis summer sausage and it is chemical free, that's the most that I like about.Again, I am not trying to turn you against this sausage just telling you the truth, it may be just what you are looking for. Thecompany did a fantastic job on delivery, matter of fact it arrived before the due date and had a very good freshness date.It was packaged well and arrived in perfect condition. Let me say again, it is fresh and very clean...

Product Title: Organic Orange Bell Pepper, 1 Each
Review: ARRIVED WITH SPOILED AREA AROUND THE STEM. Could not use it.

Product Title: Grown True‚Ñ¢ Organic Tomato-on-the-Vine, 1 lb
Review: One of them arrived with mold on it. Bought these on fresh I actually went for the organic ones because hey I supposed they would be better quality. I tend to have problems when I buy on fresh specially with produce because they always bring the produce that is almost past due or in bad condition. As for the food sometimes they bring in opened things or sometimes cans that are in bad condition too but honestly I did not think I would have a problem with these as well. In fact in the picture there are 5 tomatoes and the ones that arrived were only 3, to this point I was a lil upset but whatever, I opened them as soon as they arrived and realized that one of them had mold on it! I really don't tend to care too much but given I got less than what I expected and that at least one of them was in bad condition I would not buy these again maybe, or just a warning they do this a lot where they put one bad fruit or veggies in between the others so they go bad faster and honestly they should check this more! It has happened way too often specially when I buy on fresh and they always have mold on them specially vegetables or fruits and it's always one of them or when they come in bags I don't know why they do this but I assume it's so we are forced to buy more just not happy overall with this happening.

Product Title: Organic Valley Low Moisture Part Skim Organic Mozzarella Cheese Block
Review: Disappointed. I usually like OV products and although this was OK I was shocked to see it looked/felt exactly like the less pricier 365 and Target brands mozz. It is good for shredding as it is firmer than the mushier mozzarellas (even ones claiming to be low moisture). Since it is so firm (think brick) it also will slice well. Just don't expect the kind of creaminess you get from even a low moisture part skim commercial mozz. This is a brick.

Product Title: Donsuemor Traditional Madeleines - 28 Individually Wrapped - 28 Oz Total
Review: Good but not great. I've bought these before but the last order was a bit stale.

Product Title: Folgers Classic Roast Coffee, Medium Roast Ground Coffee, 11.3 Ounces
Review: Not good, not bad. This is coffee. It is not good, it is not bad. It is just coffee.If I find gophers in the yard, I will pour some of this, down the hole. Yes, it can drive the gophers away! If you don't believe me, check it out.The packaging is not good. It should have a screw-on type lid.Would I buy this again, probably not!

Product Title: Root Beer Barrels Hard Candy Dad's Root Beer Candy Barrels Hard Candy - Old Fashioned Hard Candy By Washburn - Rootbeer Barrels Individually Wrapped Bulk Candy (2 Pound)
Review: Old fashioned candy. This old fashioned candy is great for the root beer barrel lover in you. Still flavorful as you remembered, plenty here for share for the young and old. Packaged nicely. Great buy.

Product Title: Dove Promises Sea Salt Caramel & Dark Chocolate Candy 7.94-Ounce Bag
Review: There are equisite Sea Salt Caramels available, these are ... There are equisite Sea Salt Caramels available, these are not them. Passable, but the chocolate distracts from a lightly salted liquid caramel.

Product Title: Stagg Silverado Beef Chili with Beans, 15 Ounce
Review: Cans dented. FOUR of the six cans I ordered were badly dented, making them useless for long term pantry stocking. I was robbed.

Product Title: Brownie Brittle Chocolate Chip, Brown, 1 Oz, Pack of 24
Review: Too little of a good thing. Delicious but very little in each bag... seems a bit pricey.

Product Title: The Tao of Tea, Hibiscus Ginger Tea, Loose Leaf, 3.0 Ounce Tin to make 50 cups
Review: Very strong. Whew! Very strong flavor and I only steeped it for about 3 mins. Added a sugar cube but still strong. I think diluted it will make great iced tea but not my style for hot tea.

Product Title: Sun-Maid Organic Mediterranean Apricot Snack Pouches | 6 Ounces | Whole Natural Dried Fruit | No Sugar Added | Naturally Gluten Free | Non-GMO
Review: Not as flavorful as other apricots I've eaten. Maybe it was the batch I got, or maybe I'm just used to another brand I had been buying in my supermarket, but these apricots tasted hard, dry and not very flavorful to me. I don't plan to purchase this brand again.

Product Title: Tipo 00 Flour, All Purpose, Product of Italy, 2.2 lbs, All Natural, (Farina), for baking, pizza, bread, Non GMO, 1 PACK x 1 kg (2.2 lbs) by POLSELLI
Review: Kind of expensive. The flour is good but no it great. It makes ok bread but not so good for pizza.

Product Title: Mestemacher Protein Bread, Walnut, 8.8 Ounce (Pack of 9)
Review: Good, but not worth it. The bread was good, but 1 loaf spoiled (weird mold) well before expiration date. Amazon wouldn't replace/refund it and I never got a response from the bread company. The other two loves tasted good, but not as good as I remembered it. I don't think I would ever buy it again. Not worth the money.

Product Title: Green Giant Cut Green Beans, 4 Pack of 14.5 Ounce Cans
Review: Was it a good deal. I was thinking buying bulk that you'd save money instead I spent more money.

Product Title: Organic Turmeric Root Powder w/Curcumin | Lab Tested for Purity | 100% Raw from India | 8oz/226g Resealable Kraft Bag | by FGO
Review: Seems to give minor pain relief. Dislike the flavor. Mix with peanut butter to chow it down. Wish it tasted better.

Product Title: Sclafani Crushed Tomatoes, 28 Ounce (Pack of 12)
Review: It‚Äôs ok but in my opinion there‚Äôs better tasting sauces out there than this. It‚Äôs good not great. Will most likely stick with my usual brands. For the price I thought I‚Äôd give it a try.

Product Title: Baby Ruth Chocolatey, Peanut, Caramel, Nougat, Share Size Individually Wrapped Candy Bars, 3.3 oz each
Review: Tastes great, just don't break a tooth. This was a great deal on this king sized box of Baby Ruth bars. The only problem is that they are harder than a rock when you bite into them. Made my jaw ache just eating one. I normally like Baby Ruth bars, but I think these were on a bit of the old side.

Product Title: Mrs. Cavanaugh's Orange Creme Dark Chocolate 1-lb
Review: what happened. I've ordered these many times and have always been beyond pleased. Until today. I ordered orange creme and these sure don't look nor taste like the orange creme I've ordered in the past. they have zero orange flavor. they were packed just as well as before and the chocolate is excellent. but I won't be ordering orange creme again and I don't recommend it.

Product Title: 365 by Whole Foods Market, Fruit Strips Peach Organic, 0.63 Ounce
Review: Overpriced. Tastes terrible. Even dog wouldn‚Äôt eat it. Bad when my dog won‚Äôt eat it. He eats socks. Baby wouldn‚Äôt touch it so wife and I tried it. Gross.

Product Title: Tiny But Mighty Heirloom Popcorn, Healthy and Delicious, Unpopped Kernels, 1.25lb Bag
Review: good but not special. Wasn't overly impressed with this popcorn, perhaps i got too excited by it from the reviews. The kernels are quite a bit smaller than the stuff you usually buy in the grocery store - I thought this would be better as it would be more tender (hate the hard core some leave) but it wasn't really any more tender you just had to grab more of them to make a handful. I did not find them to be hull-less, and had a similar amount of bits I couldn't eat left over at the end of a bowl‚Ä¶. Overall I'd say it's a fine popcorn but nothing particularly special, I would buy it if the same price as others but not pay extra or go out of my way for it.

Product Title: Hostess Donettes Mini Donuts, Powdered Sugar, 3 Ounce, 10 Count
Review: Waxy coating on your tongue and funky aftertaste. Meh. Something is missing here compared to the powdered sugar donuts from Mrs Bairds. These are heavier and leave a sort of waxy film on the back of your tongue. The donut texture is dense and more cake like than the Mrs Bairds also. The one good thing about these is the dogs love them and I can easily hide pills in a donut, hand it to a dog and no drama.

Product Title: Urban Cowboy Foods Vegan Jerky & Vegetarian Snacks -Vegan Beef Jerky Variety |Plant Based Protein Mushroom Jerky |Vegetarian Jerky Vegan Snacks(Sriracha, Black Pepper, & Sweet Onion Teriyaki, 3-Pack)
Review: Flavor is not that good. I like the idea of vegan snacks but the flavor of it is really not that good. I will not repurchase it

Product Title: Mars, Inc 21265 Cobalt Gum, Individually wrapped, 10/BX, Peppermint
Review: Too much packaging. Each piece is wrapped in its own wrapper, then bundled into 5, with paper around each bundle in a pack of 3 bundles. Then they're put into a typical gum wrapper, then sealed in clear wrap.Do not attempt to eat this gum while driving - it takes two hands and a lot of time.

Product Title: Nutiva Organic Steam-Refined Coconut Oil, 54 Fl Oz, USDA Organic, Non-GMO, Vegan, Keto, Paleo, Neutral Flavor and Aroma for Cooking & Natural Moisturizer for Skin and Hair
Review: Do your home work and watch quality over time. It's ok, but this is not the same quality of coconut oil I brought from this brand/manufacturer/vendor just a few years ago.. Frankly, for the purposes I uses it. Skin, oil pulling and cooking...it feels, and handles like rancid coconut oil that has been perfumed and constituted. Unfortunately, there are TONS of central and south american cottage industries (especially in Panama) that buy this rancid oil from south east Asia, perfume and repackage it and sell it to vendors as "Organic" fresh, cold-pressed coconut oil. Unfortunately, I'm back in the US, and no longer have the rancid sample to which I can compare this particular batch. But I can say for certain, that this is not the same product I've been using over the past 2-3 years. It's changed A LOT.

Product Title: Krusteaz Light and Fluffy Apple Cinnamon Complete Pancake Mix, 28 Ounce
Review: Not up to the usual Krusteaz high standard ... I've used Krusteaz products for years (since the 1980s), and this is my first disappointment.I've made these twice now. The first time, precisely according to the recipe: 1 C mix and 2/3 C water. Mixed with a wire whisk until just barely blended (still lumpy), but I noticed that the mix was very thin and "watery." I let it sit for about 6 minutes while griddle heated to 375, lightly greased the griddle, and I ended up with .... crepes. Flat, apple crepes. That's what happens when the batter is too thin -- it spreads. OK flavor, but I wanted pancakes, not crepes.The second time, I tried it with 1/2 C water instead of 2/3 C. Got a thicker batter, and the end result was a little better, but still not "light and fluffy." More dense and soggy. Nice cinnamon flavor, but not what I was hoping for.I think I'll go back to the Krusteaz Pumpkin Spice mix -- it's really good, and I get perfect fluffy pancakes with a distinct pumpkin flavor and just enough spice. I may keep experimenting with this Apple Cinnamon mix to see if I can come up with a "formula" that works to produce actual apple PANCAKES comparable to other Krusteaz mixes. I'll update this if I find something that works.

Product Title: Highkey Vegan Snacks Keto Cereal - Fruity Plant Based Protein Cereal - 8 Servings - High Protein Breakfast Cereals Diabetic Low Carb Gluten Free Healthy Snack Foods Ketogenic Paleo Diet Sugar Free
Review: Does have a fruit loop flavor. This is a low carb food, and the sweetener is a good one. It has no after taste. It tastes as though it is mixed with the fruit flavor and sprinkled or sprayed onto the cereal after baking.In chewing the cereal, it gets very bitter and grainy. The more you chew the more the flavor is lost, but it does taste a little like fruit loops with the first bite.It worked for me in that it is filling and sticks with you longer than regular boxed cereal, and a great idea for an occasional or quick breakfast.

Product Title: Little Debbie Oatmeal Cr√®me Pie Big Pack, 12 Count per box 31. 78 Ounce
Review: the same taste ,as when you were a child. it's a little bit too sweet and I love sweet things. I don't love the inside. I think I will take them apart , take the white center out and put coffee ice cream inside and make ice cream sandwiches. the oatmeal cookies are very soft and I like hard, crisp, oatmeal cookies.

Review: Just didn‚Äôt work for me. I was not happy at all w/ the taste of this product. I had to return it.

Product Title: Amazon Brand - Happy Belly Original Snack Crackers, 13.7 oz

Product Title: Taylors of Harrogate Green Tea with Jasmine, 20 Count (Pack of 6)
Review: Not Much Flavor for What is Supposed to be a Chai Tea. In my experience Taylor teas are usually very flavorful, but even using two tea bags per cup this tea has very little flavor, especially for a chai tea. I am very disappointed in this product.

Product Title: True Lime 10.6oz Shakers (1 shaker) (Original Version)
Review: Clumps in humid weather. The taste and versatility of this product is phenomenal ... however, it clumps/sticks together if you live in a humid climate and don't use it very very quickly. I even tried adding multiple 'dry packs' (used in medication and food to prevent clumping) but without success. I have resorted in using the individual packets where crystals stay loose/free flowing. However, this adds an additional expense and as a result, I don't use this product as much as I did or would. Too bad because this is a great product for cooking, addition to water or drinks.

Product Title: Candy Cane Spoons Peppermint Flavored - 12 Count
Review: This was and ok purchase. I‚Äôm not happy about the way it was packed, because some of them were broken.

Product Title: Julian Bakery Pure Monk Ultra | Organic | v50% Monk Fruit Extract | Sweetener | 2.65oz | 75 Servings
Review: The Ultra Pure Monk Fruit is no different than the regular one, which is half the price. Pure Monk Fruit Ultra was not as sweet as claimed by Julian Bakery compared to their cheaper product Pure Monk Fruit which is not organic.I corresponded with them via email regarding the color of the powder since their website showed it as orange.I emailed them‚Äú I have used Pure Monk Fruit and Organic Ultra Pure Monk Fruit. Both were absolutely white powder.The lady I spoke to at customer service said all of the monk fruit that Julian Bakery makes now is orange in color, as their website shows.So if I order from now on it should be orange powder and not white?Thank you ‚ÄùTheir reply‚Äú Thank you for reaching out to us. Any Monk Fruit purchased from our website will have an orangeish color to it.Best Regards,ElizabethJulian Bakery‚ÄùAfter their assurance I ordered the Ultra one again, which is pretty expensive, but it‚Äôs as white as the previous ones.Julian Bakery claims that all their monk fruit powders are orange, but they‚Äôre not. All are white. Very disappointing. Makes one wonder which other claims they‚Äôre not truthful about...

Product Title: Unique Snacks Unsalted Splits, Delicious, Vegan, Homestyle Baked, Certified OU Kosher and Non-GMO, 11 Ounce Bag (Pack of 12)
Review: ‚ÄúUnique‚Äù all right! They‚Äôre HUGE! Have never see hard snacking pretzels this large so wasn‚Äôt expecting these to be. Definitely not bite size. As well, they are quite hard and I‚Äôm sorry to say, not very tasty.

Product Title: McCormick Boullion Cubes, Chicken, 32-Ounce
Review: TONS OF SODIUM THO - DON'T USE IF U HAVE HIGH BLOOD PRESSURE PROBLEMS ! LIKE THIS - IT IS WHAT IT IS - GREAT TASTE ! TONS OF SODIUM THO - DON'T USE IF U HAVE HIGH BLOOD PRESSURE PROBLEMS !

Product Title: Shirakiku Pure Japanese Sesame Seed Oil - Premium, Low Carb, Cold Pressed and Rich Flavor Natural Sesame Seed Oil - Perfect for Authentic Oriental Asian Cuisine - 56 Fl Oz
Review: Smells Great, But More For Cooking, No Flavor. The quality of the oil is fine, I cook with it regularly. The smell is fine, and this size is great for refilling bottles.
