Again it's fine for cooking but when you really want that sesame flavor in your soup or dishes, this just does not have it.

Product Title: Funyuns Onion Flavored Rings, .75 Ounce (Pack of 40)
Review: Good but the expiration was within a month. We purchased these for a gift because the recipient loves Funyuns. We were disappointed that the expiration was within a month of when we received them.

Product Title: Healthworks Chia Seeds Raw (96 Ounce / 6 Pounds) | Premium & All-Natural | Contains Omega 3, Fiber & Protein | Great with Shakes, Smoothies & Oatmeal | Packaging May Vary
Review: Very disappointed expiration is only 5 months away! I bought this product on prime day and was excited i was able to get a 6lb bag of raw, pesticide free chia seeds for only $18, which is a great deal! i thought I'd be stocked up for quite a while, but when i received the product on July 19th 2018 and was very disappointed that the expiration on this bag was December 2018, which only gives me about 5 months to consume 6lbs of chia seeds üòëüòñ !! Not happy and would not buy this size product again!

Product Title: Whisps Cheese Crisps Cheddar | Healthy Snacks | Cheddar Cheese Keto Snack, Gluten Free, High Protein, Low Carb (2.12 Oz, 3 Packs)
Review: WANTED to LOVE them, why, for me, they're just OK. Crispy parmesan. What's not to love, right?I love salty, crunchy snacks, but these are too salty for me. Really high in SAT fat too.So well total calories per bag, and it's easy to eat a bag, isn't hight, just 320, the fat is 22 grams and of that 14 is SAT.I get it's CHEESE, but I get grated parmesan a lot and use a lot, but not as much per dish as a bag of these.BOTTOMLINE: GREAT in theory, not quite as much in execution or taste.

Product Title: Trader Joe's California Sun-Dried Tomatoes, 3 oz - 2 Pack
Review: What have I paid for? The tomatoes taste great... But the quantity is so small for the price :/

Product Title: GLUCODOWN, Maintain Healthy Blood Sugar, Delicious Lemon Tea Mix, Diabetic Friendly, 45 Servings, Resealable Package.
Review: Not all that great. First, the scoop you need is in the bottom of the container, so you have to pour out all the powder to recover the scoop before you can try the product... Messy. The flavor is very strong and "artificial" tasting. It's OK, but not all that great. It did lower my blood sugar, from 189 to 70 over a two hour period. Be careful!!

Product Title: Van Houtte Cafe Swiss Water Decaf, Fair Trade & Organic Light Roast Coffee for Keurig Brewers, 24-Count K-Cups (Pack of 2)
Review: no great shakes, as they say. this coffee is okay, but nothing great. I had to brew a smaller cup to get the flavor I enjoy, which means the cost per cup goes up, in my opinion. I also found the plastic cup to be quite brittle after being used once. To save the landfills somewhat, I re-use my K-cups by emptying them, filling them with my own coffee, and re-brewing. These never made it through the process as they usually cracked after the one use and had to be discarded - and they are not recyclable (like all K-cups at this point)

Product Title: VitaCup Power Espresso Capsules 10ct w/ Infused B-Vitamins For Energy & Wellness in Recyclable Single Serve Pod Compatible with Nespresso Original Machines
Review: Did not have the right coffee machine. Did not use. Did not have the right coffee machine

Product Title: RICO RICO Mexican Candy 50 pcs - Dulces Mexicanos Surtidos, Mexican Snacks, Mexican Candies, Sweet and Spicy Candy Assortment Mix by RICO RICO
Review: Pitched most of it. The candy was about 90% highly spiced. That in itself wouldn't be too bad, but to an American palette the taste wasn't good. 7 kids and 3 adults tried everything. The best item was pineapple lollipops... we gave that a 10/10. One or two other items were deemed ok, but at least 75% of the candy was pitched. These are kids who love spicy food and snacks. The problem was the taste not the heat. I'm sure that if you grew up with this candy, it would taste good. Just not to our families taste.

Product Title: Numi Organic Black Tea, Breakfast Blend, 18 Count (Pack of 3) - Packaging May Vary
Review: For the most adventurous tea drinkers, I think. Part of the reason I tried this tea is because one reviewer said he's very much a fan of this kind of tea and that Numi does a good job with the flavor. Since I'm a fan of Numi and chocolate, I bought & tried it. Sadly, I think it's an acquired taste, and I don't care for it. To me, the taste is like tree bark mixed with bitter dark chocolate, and I don't care for it. I also read that this type of tea contains caffeine, so I think I'll pass on ordering more. Back to rooibos, and I will try the mint next time.Additional note: I've now tried this over ice with 1 packet of sweetener, and I like it very much this way. I also drink it with lunch, so the caffine isn't a problem. This way, I'll use up the box, & none will go to waste. I'm enjoying the tea this way very much, and I think it will also be good in hot weather, so I'll continue to purchase it. Good!

Product Title: PLANTERS Salted Mixed Nuts, Party Snacks, Plant-Based Protein, 27 Oz Canister
Review: Not bad mix but taste wise just okay. I had bought a jar of mixed nuts from Costco and the quality was so good I guess it spoiled me. These just didn't taste as savoury and fresh, though after about 1/3 of the jar through my taste re-set and I enjoyed them more. So I am writing this review based on my first impression, which was disappointment. Other than that, I liked the ratios of the various nuts.

Product Title: Amazon Brand - Happy Belly Basil Leaves, 0.95 Oz
Review: Probably good in dressing. Smells okay. I think it would be good in a dressing for tomato salad or in sauce.

Product Title: Gary Poppins Popcorn Creamy Dill Popcorn, Bag, 2oz
Review: Disappointing Dill. I've been experimenting with quite a few of the Gary Poppins flavors. This is a company that's evolved quite a bit since my first taste from a waxy bag in a local shop.This bag keeps the goodness inside nice and fresh.Creamy Dill is slightly disappointing. With more saltiness than dillyness, and not much to give a smooth that would translate as creaminess, this is good, but not great, popcorn.If you love popcorn, give this brand a try. In purchasing through Amazon, the bags have been consistently better than the tins, for whatever reason. The cheese corn is decent, and they have a terrific kettle corn as well as caramel.

Product Title: Tofutti Vanilla Cuties Ice Cream Bars, 8 Count (frozen)
Review: Very melted when received. Received item with other food ordered. These were very soft & melted by the time they were delivered. Disappointed.

Product Title: Sweet'N Low Sweetener, 100 Count Packets (1 Pack)
Review: Convenient but some sweetener was clumpy. I love Sweet N Low. This particular box however must have been exposed to moisture because many of the packets had clumpy, hard sweetener in them.Otherwise it's a great value and I will definitely buy again!!

Product Title: 365 by Whole Foods Market, Paste Tomato Double Concentrated, 5.3 Ounce
Review: Good tasting paste - not nearly as thick as canned. Convenient because it's in a tube, but don't expect the thickness of typical canned tomato pastes. A good value if you buy it at a discount only.

Product Title: Coffig Original Organic Coffee Substitute, Roasted Fig Beverage, Caffeine-Free Herbal Energy Drinks, 3.52oz (100g)
Review: Not a great substitute for coffee. If you like strong coffee, this does not fit the need. Not close to the taste or mouth feel of coffee. Taste is Ok and definitely fig tasting. Best to use French Press. Expensive for quantity with ok taste overall. Would no buy again.

Product Title: NUCO DUO Certified Organic, SHELF STABLE, All Natural, Paleo, Gluten Free, Vegan Non-GMO, Kosher Raw Veggie NUCO Coconut Wraps. NO Salt Added Low Carb and Yeast Free 10 Count Various Quantities
Review: They're Alright. I'm vegan so I have to eat a lot of weird stuff that's trying to be yummy food- in that sense, I felt like I could eat these. They are edible, but I feel like you could do better with a gluten free tortilla. They kind of melt in your hand if you put any wet ingredients: a salsa filled taco is somewhat out of the question. I bought these because I can't eat corn, wheat, or yeast that usually makes an appearance in any other tortilla. I just didn't feel like these are going to be my go-to I'll try some almond flour, cassava, or potato flour options. For someone who is KETO or can't have any carbs I think this would be a great option. They do taste like coconut but it's a pleasant taste to the keto alternative to a tortilla which is generally some boring ass lettuce.

Product Title: The Spice Way - Pure Nigella Seeds no preservatives, non GMO, no salt, just the black seed of the nigella (nigala) 2 oz
Review: I'm Not an expert in this product. Not sure what nigella should taste like, just experimenting so I am not qualified to judge

Product Title: Tara's All Natural Handcrafted Gourmet Sea Salt Caramel: Small Batch, Kettle Cooked, Creamy & Individually Wrapped - 11.5 Ounce
Review: Nothing special. OK caramels with large salt particles on the inside, not the outside like in the picture, that surprise you and aren't always pleasant to bite into. Definitely not worth ten bucks, especially if you live near a Trader Joe's and can get their better salted caramels for half the price.

Product Title: Amazon Brand - Happy Belly Fruit & Grain Cereal Bars, Apple Cinnamon, 8 Count (Pack of 6)
Review: Ok but not the best. These have decent flavor but the filling is much more jelly-like than other fruit bar brands. I don‚Äôt hate them but the texture isn‚Äôt my favorite.

Product Title: Crown Couque D'asse Cream Filled Wafer Cookies 144g, Bundle Pack

Dollar value coming down to .72c per tiny wafer makes it not a good deal. There are only 9 small individually wrapped wafers per box x 2 boxes for a total of $13.00 before shipping charges. Bit of an identity confusion issue though in terms of the recipe: Vietnamese style noodle salad with thin vermicelli-style noodles (may be either egg or rice noodles, seems to randomly vary--depends on the day, apparently), shredded lettuce, carrots and daikon, a Thai satay dressing, and Chinese-style sesame snaps for crunch. Product Title: Vero Gusto Calabrian Marinara Pasta Sauce by Barilla, 20 oz - Made in Parma, Italy - Premium Gluten Free, Non GMO, Kosher & Vegan Pasta Sauce with No Added Sugar (Packaging May Vary)
Review: Great color and aroma. I loved the orange color of this VERO GUSTO BY BARILLA Tomato & Basil Pasta Sauce as it simmered with the cooked Italian pasta in a saucepan. The texture was creamy, aroma was delicious, and when I added freshly grated Italian Parmigiano-Reggiano Cheese to my plated portion, salivation was immediate. As I ate it by the forkful, I thought of how I could taste the tomato, the olive oil and the basil, each individually. There was not a hint of sweetness. Unfortunately, within minutes of finishing the meal, my digestive system revolted, an experience that is unnatural for me. This is quite a disappointment because I'd placed an order for the alternate assortment of three varieties which I intended to include in holiday gifts I'm assembling. Fortunately, I was able to cancel the order before it shipped. The packaging was impressive, the reviews were stellar, and I'd had higher hopes for these more expensive jarred sauces.

Review: Small container. I sent this as a gift and unfortunately, the recipients received a single small bin of the YumEarth tasty lollipops instead of the five containers of 6 ounces each which were purchased. It was packaged in a huge box which I was told was quite funny. I've been purchasing the YumEarth lollipops for more than a decade because they are so tasty and easy to slip into a pocket or bag and always have them on hand to enjoy and share but this is not the way I'd recommend purchasing them. Alternatively, I'd recommend purchasing the 5-pound assortment bag to get all of the flavors, keep them in an airtight container, and use a smaller container for a couple dozen at a time. You could even have the kids decorate one that's easy to open. If you don't need that many lollipops, they are also available in smaller sized bags of around 3 ounces, I believe, so you can get a half dozen of those and keep them fresh until you replenish your candy jar or jug. I'm attaching a photo of what was received so you can see what flavors are included as of today. By the way, YumEarth hard candies are also excellent, especially the peppermint variety.

Product Title: Amazon Brand - Happy Belly Cream of Chicken Soup 10.5 Ounce
Review: Food for the End of Days. There is a lot of salt in this.A lot.However, I didn't buy it to eat it as a regular meal. I bought it to have on hand in case of emergency. A bit of this can add welcome flavor and texture to rice or potato flakes or any of the seed grain foods I keep on hand. And the salt isn't a burden: it's a bonus. It's a preservative.As for my other requirement of emergency provisions - the one where my family has to be willing to eat it often enough to keep supplies reasonably fresh? This isn't something you want to eat by following the directions on the can. It makes a good ingredient (you will waste some, probably, unless you are making enough of something to support an entire can of this) in wild rice hot dishes, some noodle hot dishes, chicken enchilada pie. So not all of it will go to waste. There's nothing in here that will kill you. And it's not overpriced or supporting some tv person with suspect motivation.It's just canned soup. Decent for what it is. But definitely what it is.

Product Title: SkinnyPop Popcorn, Gluten Free, Dairy Free, Non-GMO, Healthy Snacks, Skinny Pop Original Popcorn Snack Packs, 0.65oz Individual Size Snack Bags (6 Count)
Review: tastes great but not nearly as healthy as they make you think it is. I will preface this review by saying that I had heard about this "skinny pop" popcorn and how healthy it was and how great it tasted so I decided to give it a try. I didn't look at the nutrition label beforehand surprisingly and I was under the impression it was really healthy. The front of the bag boasts it's only 39 calories per cup, no trans fat, etc. It does taste great. Maybe not as good as some of the super butter movie style popcorns out there but much better than the low-fat, 94% fat free, type of popcorns out there. So I'm thinking this is a great popcorn! I read the ingredients and it's just popcorn, oil and salt and I thought that was nice it didn't have a bunch of chemicals and preservatives or dairy. But then I finally read the nutrition label. The "serving size" is 4 c (pretty generous but i think standard popcorn serving size) and it has 10 grams of fat! That's quite a lot for something that bills itself as being so good for you and skinny. I still eat it, because it is really good but I think they are a bit misleading with the packaging and would encourage those to read the nutritional information and keep that in mind when trying it. That said, this is a great way to order it on amazon as it's a good price and I can just add a bad onto a regular order.

Product Title: Lotte xylitol gum seven assorted bottle 143g [Parallel import]
Review: Not crazy about the flavor variety. Good for your teeth - flavor last a decent amount of time but I‚Äôm not crazy about the flavors. I will stick with peppermint

Review: Not 'instant' to make and does require more additional ingredients. I love trying new food and being a recent gluten sensitive, I now had to find a substitute for my love of 'instant' noodles. So upon the reviews I was sold. However, this is not 'easy to make' as it does require you to have additional ingredients in the house: shitake mushrooms, meat (optional), for example. Also, what I was not expecting was the 'strong' cinnamon component in the soup base: I know cinnamon is good for you, but fragrant wise, it was strong to both my nose and taste buds. I am not sure where the mushroom flavor was going to come from other than when I add additional ingredients like the mushrooms?The rice noodle cooks really quickly and does become 'gooey', so do watch out for that if you do add other ingredients to the pot.

Review: Dr John's healthy sweets. I have been purchasing these candies for some time so I ordered these and was very, very surprised to receive a tiny package for the price I have been paying for double or triple the amount in the past. My husband is diabetic and so is my sister and these creme cicle like discs are favorites. The list different flavors.. but I have to say to me, they mostly all taste the same or very similar. Product Title: Tasty Brand Organic Cereal Bars, Pumpkin Pie Flavor, 6.2 Ounces 5-Count Bars (Pack of 6)
Review: Pretty good, but I would change a few things.. I ordered a case of Tasty Brand Organic Cereal Bars in the Pumpkin Pie flavor. The following week I accidentally ordered a second case when I placed another amazon.com order, and so I ended up with quite a few bars! This would have been no problem at all had I loved them as much as I had hoped I might. But they are actually kind of dry- like, without a glass of milk, I don't give them to my daughter in case she might choke! And though there is a clear little picture of bananas alongside a pumpkin on the front of the box, I only went with the assumption that they would taste like pumpkin pie. The banana accent is not bad at all, just not what I expected or would call by the same name. The main reason I bought these bars was to have a quick, easy, ORGANIC treat for my family to grab on their way in or out, and that is what we got. Product Title: Heinz No Salt Tomato Ketchup, 14 Ounce -- 6 per case.
Review: Bitter ketchup likely due to storage. Since I was a young person, Heinz Tomato Ketchup was the ketchup of choice in our family. Now I must confess that I am more a mustard fan and user than a ketchup or mayonnaise loving person, so a single bottle usually lasts a long time unless I'm making barbeque sauce out of it. I made this purchase because it's Heinz, it had no added sugar, it was offered at a very good price and I intended to share with my family members and friends who are also avoiding high fructose corn syrup and had already tried this product. The case of 6 looked perfect upon arrival but the first bottle ketchup did not taste good. The consistency was runny and the flavor was bitter. I removed the seal on a second bottle and the ketchup tasted the same. I then made contact with Kraft Foods, the manufacturer of Heinz products, and they responded very quickly. Because of the communicative customer service representative, I'm rating this as an average product and once I purchase it in a brick and mortar store, should I find it to be a better product, I'll up the rating. I'll still keep purchasing the Hot and Spicy Heinz Ketchup because it's so tasty that I often use in place of hot sauce and that says a lot.

Product Title: Taylors of Harrogate Green Tea with Jasmine, 20 Count (Pack of 6)
Review: Good tea, shipping problems though. Taylors makes great tea. I'm not a fan of this flavor though. It's harsh. Also, the box came completely destroyed. The shipping box was fine, but the tea box itself (as well as the other box of tea I ordered with it) was torn and crumpled and the tea inside was in disarray. One packet was even missing. Amazon refunded it completely and I got to keep the tea. Since the individual packets were fine, I didn't see a problem with still drinking them. I'm not sure if that happens frequently, but it happened with this one.

Product Title: Knorr Ultimate Clam Base, 16-Ounce Tubs (Pack of 2)
Review: Short of the Mark! The main reason I buy this type of product is because I know how hard it is to make your own. Requires a nice investment of time and money to locate, in this case the clams mostly, and sacrifice all that goodness into turning a bunch of clams into a flavorful, authentic clam base. I truly love a clam broth, a clam chowder, a pasta with clams sauce, etc. I found out that clam is as good as, let's say, fish stock. Or seafood stock, for when is all said and done a great clam base can turn a seafood chowder into a crowd pleaser. Basically one will get what they put in it, simple as that. I wanted to like Knorr Ultimate Clam Base, 16-Ounce Tubs (Pack of 2) for it offered a nice quantity for the money so I took the plunge. The one I have been using these past years is Minor's Clam Base, which I confess right here and now is the one I like the best.I bought a fish bullion in powder form, a huge can that in the first try it reminded me very fast that somethings can not be duplicated without the really good ingredients. The same thing happened with this product. Much better than the powder fish base, also from Knorr's?, for it does have more natural flavors than the more chemically oriented powder (I did not like it very much and now, I am wondering, how it it going to be consumed excepting in tiny amounts) and if used in moderation it does impart the culinary creations with that precise clam flavor that can make most seafood dishes very appealing. Note I said in moderate amounts because if I add too much its sodium content will overpower any culinary endeavor to the point that it might get rejected, and that is always an embaressment to the wannabee cook. I learned to measure this product carefully. In one case I added a little too much and was able to increase all the other ingredients until they somehow meshed together, resulting in a very edible white sauce with shrimp, scallops and fish over linguini with a touch of parmesan cheese. Knorr Ultimate Clam Base is decent but not as great as Minor's, but of course Minor's must also be used carefully so as not too overpower or under power the creation. Got 2 for under $20 and that is a good thing. Will use it until is gone but I will go back to Minor's Clam Base, because even though is more expensive it appears more naturally tasting, like if it had a higher concentration of clams than the competition so far. Every chef knows that a good base is almost a must, be that chicken, beef, even turkey, clam, fish and seafood form. They add a distinctive quality that is going to be hard to beat if all the other ingredients and the cooking is done right. 3.5 Stars for sure but short of the mark to be considered the best!PS: Today is 2-2-2012. After having used this product repeatedly because I received two tubs, I have to say that it is much better than what I initially had thought. It works very well and the flavor adds body and taste to most seafood creations. Live and Learn, I guess, I should have waited longer because definitely my appreciation for this item has increased. Thank you.

The chicken is therefore not infused with spice, and is also dry and tasteless. I suspect the chicken is pre-cooked for inclusion into a wide variety of packaged foods, probably across several companies. Which is all a bit sad. The curry sauce is pretty good as is the rice. And no, you don't get much for the money: the portions are small and expensive. But, hey, it's better than most microwavable meals available in the USA. Which, also sadly, is not saying much.However, if I was Indian and the original owner of this brand I think I'd be ashamed.

Product Title: PLANTERS Salted Mixed Nuts, Party Snacks, Plant-Based Protein 56oz (1 Canister)

Product Title: Darjeeling Tea - Organic - Loose Leaf - Bulk - Non GMO - 96 Servings, 8 oz
Review: Easing into Darjeeling on a sweeter note - Not bad at all. For the taste, I do find the price a bit high. Consider the 87 single estates of Darjeeling and then how many vendors blend their own at lower grades along with the different flush (season), there can be a lot of general Darjeeling. That makes it confusing. Anyone who wants to get into the better ones, you look for the single estates. When it's labeled Darjeeling, it's anyone's guess. Too often, they don't ever mention the tasting notes. It's good when they do.This is what I like about this brand. It does have that classic muscatel note that's dominant in most Darjeeling teas. Not all of them have that note. Depends on the flush. What makes this one nice is it does have a light, sweet taste at the end. For anyone new to Darjeeling and they want an easier transition to the more prominent muscatel note, this would be the one.Much of the time, Darjeeling has the Earthy, grassy, plant notes. Some are more floral and some are fruity. Often times, when they state almond, peach, muscatel and such, they refer to the skin, not the actual fruit or nut. The taste is more bitter.Those into the Darjeeling have a darker, more Earthy palate. Unless it's a single estate that you're familiar with, majority are going to have heavier tasting notes.If you like the aroma of Lavender, the Namring single est. offers that. For more almond note, Selim Hill single est.This does have more taste than a certain brand sold on here in a blue bag. It doesn't taste as basic. There's a little more to this one that makes it enjoyable to drink all day. For many, this is a good tea. It's not bad at all.So far between the Ceylon and this, it has been pleasant tea. For the quality of it and taste, the price is higher than it should be. That's having a lot of experience with tea.It's much better than Lipton of course. But not the same as a single estate and the quality isn't as high as it could be for the price.For some who tried a thousand teas, not sure that's valid. There are hundreds for sure. Anyone who as tried a lot of teas knows that a lot of teas overlap and it's a mix of grades and other teas to be a diff tea product, but not a whole entire type of tea bush.87 Darjeeling estates. Break that into 3 seasons. Then break it into grades from how finely cut to whole leaves to how fresh it is to barely having any taste. 87 diff tea bushes is that. It breaks into the 3 seasons then you have 261 to choose from, but still it's 87 estates that have their own unique taste. Take the 1st or 2nd flush to blend, that's what you get. Blends.Over a thousand blends from hundreds of different teas, yes. Thousands of tea as if there are that many different bushes, no. 87 diff tea bushes in the Darjeeling region alone can produce hundreds of blends. Anyone who has tried thousands of teas chances are only had hundreds.Even then, no reason to review it as if this is to be the site for the top 100 teas of the world. You want the best teas, it's not sold in this site. Anyone who is really into teas would know that. If they're going to grade it in such a way as if every tea connoisseur thinks that way, then 99% of the teas sold on this site would be a 1 star to folks like that.For all those who want a good tea to enjoy without it being on the same level as the ones sold in most chain stores, this is good. Just the price isn't so good. If the price was much lower, I think this would be a daily staple to have for many.The Idulgashinna single estate Ceylon sold on here under Irish, English breakfast are good, sturdy teas for a good price. You have to find that marked on the bag. Technically it's not Irish or English blend. Single estates are not blends. That's why it's called single estate. If you blend them, you can't call them single estate.The brand is good on its own. It would taste better blended with other teas for those who know how to blend. It's a good all day, any day tea. Not at the level to be addictive.

Product Title: Medley Hills Farm Cereal Marshmallows 1 lb
Review: Cool, but stale. Awesome idea. Kids love them. I found them to be a bit stale. Would try again, but a different brand.

Product Title: Sabatino Tartufi Truffle Salt Seasoning, All Natural Gourmet Truffle Salt, Sicilian Sea Salt,Kosher, Non-Gmo Project Certified, 4 oz
Review: I Don't Care For The Smell. I haven't tried this yet but I don't like the smell too much. It may be really good and I will update after I have tried it.

Product Title: Maggi Season-up! All Purpose Powdered Seasoning Pack of 3
Review: The seal was broken at time of arival. I threw it away. I don't have photo of it

Product Title: Nonni's THINaddictives Almond Thin Cookies - Mango & Coconut Biscotti Italian Cookies - Almond Cookies - Cookie Thins - Sweet Crunchy & Chewy - Perfect w/Coffee - Kosher - 4.4 oz
Review: Love this product, but‚Ä¶. When I previously bought these Nonni‚Äôs Thin Addictives, there were 4 in a package, now there are 3. This was not disclosed before I ordered. Will not purchase again; too expensive.

Product Title: Pillsbury BEST Organic Coconut Flour, 16 Ounce, Gluten Free
Review: Received an old package. I guess the pack I received was old because it had a lot of clumps and made baking little hard for me. The pack is also small.

Product Title: Tara's All Natural Handcrafted Gourmet Sea Salt Caramel: Small Batch, Kettle Cooked, Creamy & Individually Wrapped - 11.5 Ounce
Review: The Caramels are tasty, but not really a salted caramel. The caramels were soft and tasty; however, they were not very much like a salted caramel flavor....mostly caramel. I was hoping for more of a salted caramel flavor.

Product Title: Green & Black's Organic Dark Chocolate Bar, 70% Cacao, 20 - 1.2 oz Bars
Review: Expensive for such a tiny amount. Taste great.....but these are tiny bars. Don't be fooled. Very expensive for the amount that you get. Extremely expensive in fact. Luckily, I got my order for free because the package was practically on fire when it arrived. The ice packs were actually hot water. Everything was melted.But.... the flavor is really good. Not too bitter.Just not worth nearly $30. $15 would be a better price.

Product Title: PUR Gum | Sugar Free Chewing Gum | 100% Xylitol | Vegan, Aspartame Free, Gluten Free & Keto Friendly | Natural Peppermint Flavored Gum, 55 Pieces (Pack of 6)
Review: Couple of minutes. I like the look of the little chewing gum pieces and the ingredients are all fine but the flavor of the cinnamon gum is not impressive. Rather than revealing the bag each time it is opened, I transferred the contents into another airtight container with a flip top for quicker access and storage. This pack doesn't take up much space because the pieces are so small. The reason I don't grab one of these first is because the flavor simply doesn't last. I now only chew one when I take the dog out in the evening. By the time I take the filled bag to the trash, the gum gets deposited as well. That total time is always under 5 minutes.

Product Title: MANISCHEWITZ Matzos, 16 OZ
Review: the box came in an envelope , mashed . there were matzoh crumbs coming out. it should not be sent in a soft envelope, but a box. this is not the manufacture's fault, but whoever mailed this. i cannot use it.

Product Title: Teas' Tea Unsweetened Lemongrass Green Tea 16.9 Ounce (Pack of 12) Organic, Sugar Free, Zero calorie
Review: No trace of ROSE flavor tasted. Definitely NOT my cup of tea. I found very little evidence of any ROSE flavor. That being said, the actual tea flavor itself is very nice and not bitter at all. I do not like sweet tea so I found this ok in that regard, but was disappointed that the ROSE flavor was just not there. Also, it would be better to have in thinner glass bottle because it is quite thick and heavy. When cold it becomes slippery on top of being heavy.

Product Title: Black Forest Juicy Burst Variety, Mixed Fruit & Berry Medley, 10 Count, Pack of 6, 38.4 Ounce
Review: Buy them at your local store. They were hard! Half the fruit snacks juices were out of the fruit snacks.

Product Title: Namyang French Cafe Instant Coffee Mix 1 Gift Pack (100 Sticks) 1,160g
Review: Meh -- better products on the market. I was really looking forward to this because while I love another brand, I think it's too expensive. The coffee is good -- just the right amount of sweetness and creamer -- it's a little weak and to enjoy good flavor I had to use 2 to 3 servings, which sort of defeats the purpose. I'm glad I tried this product and think it's much better than hotel room coffee; just not as good as sbux.

Product Title: Les Trois Petits Cochons Pate - Pat√© de Campagne (8 ounce)
Review: i was pretty good not the best I have ever had. i was pretty good not the best I have ever had. I was disappointed because the way its presented on Amazon makes it look like you will get two kinds to try, you don't you only get one, and it arrived in an absurdly large styrofoam container for one tiny little loaf of pate

Product Title: Boston Harbor Tea 4oz Loose Leaf Resealable Bag
Review: Overpriced and underwhelming. Tea has a decent flavor, nothing spectacular, far better teas for less than half the price, the tin is by far the best part and what you are paying for.

Product Title: Ginger People Crystallized Ginger Candy, 3.5 Ounce
Review: Possibly lead in it? My husband told me this product (and other crystalized ginger snacks, NOT the real ginger) contain some lead. It's too bad if it is. I will come back to get this for sure as my children love this and I believe ginger helps us stay healthy and keep cold away to some extent.

Product Title: Stove Top Cornbread Stuffing Mix (6 oz Boxes, Pack of 12)
Review: Disappointing. I had been purchasing another generic brand but decided to try the name brand that was offered on Amazon. I was disappointed that it was not better. I don't think I will purchase again.

Product Title: Justin's Maple Almond Butter Squeeze Packs, Gluten-Free, Non-GMO, Responsibly Sourced, 1.15 Ounce (10 Pack)
Review: Justins has great products but my batch arrived nearly 3 months PAST best by date. wTH? Come on. My package was loose in the packing envelope. The box was so smashed that it looked like it was just tossed in there in an already damaged state. I can almost overlook that, but then I took a look at the expiration date. I normally dont care, but since I bought this on the warehouse, I wanted to check to see how far out the best by or expiration is. It is normal for the warehouse items to be anywhere from a couple of weeks to a few months out. That is a trade off for the reduced cost. BUT, it is not supposed to be EXPIRED product. On the magnitude of nearly 3 months. Mine has best by date of late May 2022. GOOD GRIEF.Now, I am going to eat this anyway, because I know most products dont go bad the day of the date. I happen to have eaten some Justins products a couple years old without degradation in smell or taste. But I dont want to knowingly buy old product. I do know that the Inspected food is supposed to at least have some time left on it before selling. What happened?Between the smashed up box (again, didnt look like a box that got smashed in shipping, it was so torn apart that it didnt even look like it came in a product box. It was put in there all banged up), and the terribly over past expiry/best by date.. Im disappointed.Product itself? I love Justin's products. Been buying the packets on and off for years. I prefer peanut butter but I gave the maple almond butter a try based on sale price. I like using the packets for on the go use. Can add to food, or eat direct from packet. I always have some tucked away in my car (in a critter proof container) as emergency food. Great for camping, hiking, bug out bags, etc.

Product Title: 365 by Whole Foods Market, Organic Cocoa And Peanut Butter Balls, 10 Ounce
Review: Organic peanut butter and cocoa balls cereal. I was really hoping this would be a good mix... but the flavors were sooooo bland!!! I was hoping for some nice, deep, rich flavors. Perhaps I was expecting too much? If you're OK with faint, whispers of flavor, this is the cereal for you! The "balls" are small... easy to eat. The mushed up pretty quickly in milk, but I am ok with that... For me they were "OK" at best - just my opinion! Hope that helps some

Product Title: Katz Gluten Free Glazed Chocolate Donut Holes | Dairy Free, Nut Free, Soy Free, Gluten Free | Kosher (6 Packs, 6 Ounce Each)
Review: Ok but not delicious. Donuts were ok but, not something I'll be ordering again. Just not tasty.

Product Title: Wiley Wallaby 8 Ounce Allsorts Gourmet Australian Style Soft & Chewy Assorted Licorice Candy (1 Pack)
Review: Licorice, but doesn't taste like licorice. Product is very sweet and has a different taste, but definitely doesn't taste like licorice.

Product Title: SweetLeaf Sweet Drops Flavored Stevia Sweetener Variety Pack (Peppermint, Dark Chocolate) - Liquid Stevia Drops, Zero Calories, Sugar Free, Gluten-Free, Non-GMO, Keto Friendly - 2 Fl Oz, Pack of 2
Review: Yes and no. You get to at a good price. However if your trying to make a peppermint mocha using both it will be too sweet and mocha overtakes the flavor. Used separately for different things great. But together no.

Product Title: Subtle Earth Organic Coffee - Medium-Dark Roast - Whole Bean Coffee - 100% Arabica Beans - Low Acidity and Non-GMO - 2lb bag
Review: It was okay, smooth, but no detectable flavor came through for me. Saw a recommendation for this coffee and decided to try it. While the coffee, is smooth tasting, and no acidic or burnt taste, I did not find any detectable flavor. I used the amount directed. So the next day, I increased the amount by another tablespoon plus, but still no flavor taste change.So while not bad, it was just "okay", I see no reason to buy it again though, sorry. Btw, I prefer medium roast coffee, not bold and not weak coffees, and this is a medium ranked coffee, so thought it would be right, but at this point I almost feel I should see if they have a stronger coffee option to try.

Product Title: 99% Pure Ginger Juice by The Ginger People ‚Äì Drug Free Digestive Health, Original Flavor and Premium Quality, 32 Fl Oz
Review: Where‚Äôs the ginger? Looked like a great buy and love the idea,It wasn‚Äôt as fresh tasting as hoped tho‚ÄîI really like the sharp taste of fresh grated ginger, fresh boiled ginger made into a tea, In a pinch, Trader Joe‚Äôs ginger powder is great; ginger people‚Äôs ginger chews are also awesome‚Ä¶but this juice was pretty bland, even after shaking it up. It had a not so fresh taste. Maybe I got a bad batch, but no matter how much I added to the cup, I could not get the ginger taste I was looking for. I may try it again, since other reviews were positive.

Product Title: Tara's All Natural Handcrafted Gourmet Sea Salt Caramel: Small Batch, Kettle Cooked, Creamy & Individually Wrapped - 11.5 Ounce
Review: Good, but not gluten free as advertised. I purchased these for my gluten free nephew‚Äôs Easter basket. Product Title: Siljans Crispbread, 14-Ounce Package (Pack of 2)

Review: Bottle and lid need improvements. Good honey but the plastic bottle needs to be thicker, it is too thin and the lid better engineered for better pouring control. Product Title: Taylors of Harrogate Green Tea with Jasmine, 20 Count (Pack of 6)

Product Title: USDA Choice Beef Top Sirloin Steak, 2 pcs, 1 lb
Review: Not quite what I thought a pound would get me. I ordered because it said 1 lb, package is less than one pound but close it says. I guess I was anticipating that a pound looked like more. Maybe it's almost a pound including packaging and juices? Looks like a good cut though.

Product Title: Stash Tea Premium Caffeine Free Herbal Tea, Cinnamon Vanilla, 18 Count
Review: Not bad, but not great. Tried it thought it was okay but will not repurchase. It's not a bad cup of tea, but I'm off to try new flavors!! :)

Review: Why would they put green peppercorns in a can whose top has to be opened by a cane opener? Have not used it yet, so can't speak for the quality, but have another container ready to put it in.

Product Title: Angie's BOOMCHICKAPOP Sweet & Salty Kettle Corn Popcorn, 2.25 Ounce (Pack of 12)
Review: Fresh and tasty but not great. Yes, its fresh and tastes good, however, I think that the Trader Joe's kettle corn is WAY better than this, especially because this product is a bit spendy. I did taste a hint of sweet in this, but I didn't taste salt at all. Perhaps my expectations were too high, since I've been waiting to fit this into my snack budget for months.I will absolutely enjoy the whole box of this, but I doubt I'll reorder, and I can't say I recommend this item. Cheers.

Product Title: BranchOut Avocado Powder ‚Äì Hass Avocado Smoothie Powder Mix ‚Äì 100% Pure Dried Avocado KETO Rich in Good Fats ‚Äì Vegan Pure Gluten Free KETO Powder - Also Ideal for Baking, 7 oz
Review: not powder but granules. Gritty. Hint of lemon. Best in smoothies. Mediocre for toast. NO guac. People are scoffing at "freeze dried", This isn't freeze dried. It is low temp dried.OK, so this isn't quite for me, but it isnt "bad". It's just avocado and lemon. Depending on what you are hoping to use it for, your expectation may be met or may fall short. Direct from bag, it is gritty with a mix of yellow and dark green. Do a 1:1 ratio of water and avocado powder. Well, actually it is granular, not at all powder like. Stir for a couple of minutes. I even let it sit. Remained gritty. Maybe a small mixer would help. The grit is going to be the turn off factor for a lot of people who want to use this beyond smoothies.Taste is OK. Very mild avocado taste with hint of lemon. Kinda would prefer no lemon. I think that makes this taste off, especially depending on what it is being use in. Fine if using it in smoothies. Texture is probably best for smoothies, but I was hoping to use it as a topper for toast or coconut basmati rice.I am finding that avocados in store have been sub par. I dont know.. was just hoping for something better here. No bad, but not what I want. Again, I think it is fine for the nutrition and use it in smoothies. Can try it in other applications, just know that it wont quite make the same results. Because of the GRIT.I dont think it is gross; I am not that dramatic. I'll use it up, but it likely wont be a repurchase. I will look for dehydrated or freeze dried avocado powder that can be reconstituted into a non gritty paste.If this was smooth, and had less of a lemon taste (I love lemon by the way), I would like it more. Quality overall seems fine.3.5 stars (4.5/5 stars overall quality, 1 stars for grit, 3.5 stars for taste). Since we can't do half stars, then I am going with middle of road rating of 3.

Product Title: Red Milk Chocolate Cherries (1 Pound)
Review: They are ok if you want to take the gamble... I have been super sad since our Trader Joe stores stopped selling tubs of chocolate covered cherries like this. I saw these as an affordable substitute and thought I'd give it a try. While I do like them, they are a lot sweeter than the other brand I loved from TJ‚Äôs and every once in a while, one of the candy cherry pieces will have a flavor reminiscent to the smell of dryer sheets. I know how that sounds, and when my youngest daughter first told me that after eating one I told her she was obviously ingesting it incorrectly and should leave the rest for me! However, after experiencing it twice now myself, I had to apologize to her and am somewhat reluctant to try any more. The non-detergent flavored cherries, while a tad too sweet, are tasty, but it‚Äôs a gamble I‚Äôm not sure I want to take.

Product Title: KIT KAT Milk Chocolate Snack Size, Wafer Candy Bars Bag, 32.34 oz (66 Pieces)

Product Title: Planters Salted Caramel Peanuts, Salted Caramel Flavored Peanuts, 16 Ounce
Review: Add to ice cream or cookie dough for a treat. I first purchased a smaller canister of the Planters Salted Caramel Peanuts and decided that it was time to order a larger bag which would last longer. The coating is not overly salty or hard, actually more of a granular coating. If I only eat a few, they are quite tasty but if I have one too many, I can't stand them. A very strong artificial flavor overwhelms the peanuts. Instead of eating these on their own, they are much better when used in cookie dough or mixed into a very rich vanilla ice cream. I won't be buying them again.

Product Title: Frontier Grains Of Paradise Grinder 2.26 Ounce
Review: Not worth the bother. Nothing special and the mechanism that grinds it is very hard to turn.

Product Title: Hershey's Caramel Syrup, 22 oz
Review: Good taste. Too thin for us. A lil runny for our liking. Good flavor

Product Title: Jack Link's Beef Jerky, Sweet & Hot, ¬Ω Pounder Bag - Flavorful Meat Snack, 9g of Protein and 80 Calories, Made with Premium Beef - 96 Percent Fat Free, No Added MSG or Nitrates/Nitrites
Review: Thought this was the best, but its only the most common brand. Yes, Jack Link's... every time you hear about beef jerky, this name automatically comes to mind if you're in the United States. But in reality, it's only average in taste for the price. It's not super expensive and it's not super cheap, but for this price, there are some better ones that have better flavor and less moisture content. Yes, the more dry beef jerky is, the more beef they need to use to get the same weight, and this is relatively high on the moisture content. I also like my beef jerky more chewy and though, so another point off. Flavor wise, it's pretty mild, but I'm not going to judge if you've grown up on the taste and want something consistent.

Product Title: Planters Dry Roasted Salted Macadamias (6.25 oz Jar)
Review: Risky purchase, the nuts vary from great to barely edible. I purchased a jar of the Planters Macadamia nuts and thought they were quite the tasty nuts in a small, easy to open and close plastic container which would prevent the risk of overindulgence. Because they were not very salty and each nut in the jar was crisp and enjoyable, I purchased another four jars over a period of a couple of several days as the price was reduced. Unfortunately, after the first jar, the others have been disappointing. The nut sizes range from tiny to robust, the textures vary from nut to nut, some are so dark that I wonder about whether they should even be consumed. The jar I opened yesterday ended up as part of a cookie batch which turned out pretty good but they were not as great as usual. It seems that unlike the first jar we received, the remaining jars will not be the tasty nuts we enjoyed with a cocktail.

Product Title: Amazon Brand - Happy Belly Rainbow Sherbet, 48 Fl Oz (Frozen)
Review: A tasty sherbet but arrived partially melted and refrozen. Ice crystals in the product indicate it had refrozen ‚Ä¶ after melting on one side.

Product Title: Terra Vegetable Chips, Blues with Sea Salt, 5 oz
Review: Interesting in flavor and not really like a potato. Interesting in flavor and not really like a potato, so not sure if I would buy them again. The color is super fun though on a plate for parties.

Review: Not impressed, other brands better. Lots of other brands like Godiva, are much better. Some of them I didn't like at all, some were very hard

Product Title: Haw Green Cardamom Pods 100 Grams| Natural Whole Cardamom Pods 3.5 Ounces| Natural Spice Cardamom for Biryani, Tea, Coffee with Natural Aroma

Product Title: DEL MONTE FRESH CUT Diced Canned Potatoes, Canned Vegetables, 12 Pack, 14.5 oz Can
Review: HARD REVIEW as there is ONE BIG CON with the PROS. First, I'll do the pros:CONVENIENCE - I have to eat high potassium foods as I am low in potassium. Potatoes are high in that, but not convenient to run out to store to get them and then it's hit or miss how long they last. Canned potatoes are convenient.INGREDIENTS/CALORIES - VERY few ingredients, which is a plus, plus low in calories. You can eat a can of these for less than 200 calories.PRICE : Hard to beat as I got for about a buck a can.TASTE - Taste is fine. Easy to nuke to hit up and add whatever ingredients. Already diced and cooked, so that was nice.NOW FOR THE ONE BIG CON: MANY of the cans were dented, I mean dented as in you don't want to chance eating them. A tiny ding on a can I can overlook, a dented can, not so much.SO....except for all the dented cans, there were a few that were in good shape and I did try these, all pluses.

Product Title: BFree Gluten-Free Wrap Tortillas Multigran Dairy-Free Wheat-Free 8 Inch [2 Packs]

Review: Good but pricey. This is mostly my fault... I did not do a price comparison first. I paid 400% of what I would have if I would‚Äôve checked. It is a good product, I just paid $8 for what I went to Walgreens and got 2 for $4. Like I said, good product.... but wow.

Review: Bean chips - can't really taste cheese. Its a bean chip. I like the texture... but cheese flavor wasn't strong or really even very identifiable. Maybe I'll try a different brand or flavor... but i wouldn't buy these again.

Product Title: Tara's All Natural Handcrafted Gourmet Caramel Apple Flavored Caramels: Small Batch, Kettle Cooked, Creamy & Individually Wrapped - 20 Ounce, brown

Product Title: Tazo Organic Iced Tea, Black Tea, 13.8 Ounce Glass Bottles, 8 Pack
Review: up to you... Someone recommended to buy this bottled tea but I am a bit disappointed after trying it. I didn't feel taste of tea ( well, maybe a little bit ) and a little sour just likes something left over night. If anyone wanna try it I suggest to buy one bottle to taste it first.

Review: Not That Strong, Don't Like. I used to like Twining's tea. I switched to Bewley's and also liked it. When I ran out of Bewley's, I went back to the Twining's I have. Review: not for coffee. My opinion is that it's not a replacement for cow milk or soy milk. The taste is very much like cheese.It's not their fault, but if you are looking to replace cow milk or soy milk for your coffee, I don't recommend this.

Review: Not really what I thought. So, very 'natural' & unprocessed, but wasn't really appealing to me.

Apparently during it's long delayed journey this bag of flour became Asexual and reproduced on it's own; Two bags arrived instead of one.Now I want to order other hard to find items and see if they arrive by 2021, and continue the "Where's Waldo" commerce game I have goinh=g

Product Title: Hostess Zingers Devil's Food (Pack of 3) 108g
Review: Received 2 days AFTER expiration date ... I've always liked Hostess products -- I'm old enough to remember when Twinkies were filled with banana cream -- and they're not often easy to find in my local supermarket.Amazon to the rescue! One of my all-time favorites, Zingers and at a decent price, too.Unfortunately, the expiration date was 2 days before my delivery date. Received 1/24; expiration date 1/22. Yes, I know they will keep beyond that date, but they were already stale, somewhat dry, and the icing was hard as a rock. Really, someone needs to be keeping track of expiration dates before shipping product that will expire before it reaches the customer. I still like Zingers, and I stashed them in the freezer to try to prevent further product deterioration, but I shouldn't have to do that.That said, they're as I remember (except for the stale part): nice chocolatey cake, creamy filling, thick layer of chocolate icing. What's not to love?This is the 4th Hostess product I've ordered from Amazon (sold by was Amazon, not a 3rd party seller) that had this problem of the expiration date within days of receipt. I don't think I want to try again. I'll keep an eye out at my local supermarket and try to stock up next time they get them.

Product Title: Gorton‚Äôs Crab Cakes Maryland Style, Real Crab Meat with Onions, Butter, and Seasoning, Frozen, 2 Count, 6 Ounce Package

Review: Delivery was prompt. These were fresh, wrapped very well, arrived quickly BUT we likeMott's much better for flavor and texture.

Product Title: Ac'cent All Natural Flavor Enhancer, 4.5 Ounce
Review: Worked for the purpose... I don't consume this stuff myself -- it's full of sodium and really not very good for your health. However, it does have a peculiar and very useful purpose: training a puppy to desist from the common doggy habit of coprophagy. (Look it up...but be forewarned that if you don't have a dog, you don't want to know!)Sprinkle a small amount of MSG over your dog's food. If you have more than one dog, use it on all servings for all the dogs in the house. Take it easy: large quantities of sodium are no better for your dog than they are for you. As it passes through a dog's digestive tract, MSG turns into a bitter-tasting chemical that dogs find repellent. It only takes a couple of days to convince a puppy (or a grown dog, if you brought one home from the pound) that those lovely little packets in the backyard are NOT good to eat.You don't have to use this product indefinitely to break your dog of this obnoxious habit -- it works in less than a week, and you never have to replay the lesson.

Product Title: BEN'S ORIGINAL Ready Rice Cheese Risotto Flavored Rice, Easy Dinner Side, 8.5 oz Pouch (Pack of 12)
Review: Was given jasmine rice, not whole brown. Was given jasmine rice, not brown

Review: Not for serious low carb dusters. Way too sugary. I buy another name brand and my local store and it‚Äôs way better tasting. Product Title: TAETEA Gold Tuo PU'ER TEA, Aged Fermented Puerh Tea Black Tea 12 Cups for Daily Drink and Gift (chrysanthemum,Ripe)
Review: They‚Äôre just Ok. I‚Äôve been drinking Pu‚Äôer for many years. This tea is very basic and not much flavor. I will try something else next time.

Review: Too sweet and a little chewy. Not as good as a Ding Dong or the powdered sugar version. Meh. Review: Why are they so hard now? These were a lot harder to chew through than I remember when target used to sell them. I remember them being really soft, now they‚Äôre like the toughness of a beef jerky. Like my teeth kind of hurt eating these. Review: Only yellow. I got a whole bag of only yellow.The yellows are my least favorite. I am not happy.

Product Title: ZenSweet Monk Fruit Sweetener - 1:1 Sugar Substitute - 1lb - Zero Calorie, Zero Glycemic Index - Gluten-Free, Grain-Free, Non-GMO, Vegan, and Keto Sweetener - For Cooking and Baking

I am going to see if I can get my money back on this product......After checking out returns, it looks like I am going to be out my money, because it mentioned something like "unopened". Product Title: Coco Re√†l, Cream of Coconut, 16.9 FL OZ Squeezable Bottle, Individually Boxed
Review: Coco Lopez is better, has more taste than this. I liked the idea that this came in a squeeze plastic bottle rather than the Coco Lopez that‚Äôs in a can. I thought it would taste the same and easier to use. Unfortunately this one didn‚Äôt have much taste and seemed like it was watered down. Product Title: Knorr Fish Bouillion Mix, 32-Ounce Canister
Review: Not Really... Every wannabee cook knows that to make an above average culinary creation 3 things are necessary: Talent and creativity, a good recipe, and most important, great ingredients. If those 3 are in place then the results will be nothing short of outstanding every single time.I have been in love with seafood since a toddler when a mini wave took me up to sea and I was rescued by an aging mermaid. I love all things that come from the sea excepting in sushi form, perhaps some of the sea life in raw form does not agree with my palate. I love making seafood dishes, from soups to main entrees. Soups are my biggest weakness for I use to go to a pier where the seafood would arrive early in the morning hours and right then and there a hot pot with water will be waiting to be filled up with all manners of the daily catch. Mussels, fish heads, shell fish, pieces of fish, oysters, octopus, shrimp, etc etc. These selections would be the leftovers, the ones that did not command a sizable market price, they would end in their own version of the french bouillabaisse, with herbs and spices and the phosphorus of the fish heads, in no time the broth would be bursting with natural flavor right from the ocean. Add some lemon (lime here for the lemon in US is not as pungent), a little home made salsa with onions, chilies and tomatoes, and if you were courageous enough extra heat. By the time you would finish this powerful concoction all the phosphorus of the seafood would command to find the nearest hammock and snore for a couple of hours only to wake up feeling like a million dollars.Enter Knorr Fish Boullion Mix, 32 Ounce Canister: yes, somewhere in its contents there is some vague taste of fish, but it certainly does not taste natural. It seems to be a little on the smoky side, it definitely has its own particular taste but it is way off from an above average fish stock. I have been using Minor's Clam Base (because is the cheapest in price and imparts a delicious total flavor to dishes) and this time I was caught on the curiosity of purchasing this powder form bouillon. I loved the quantity and the powder form mystified me, what if it works as good as what I had been using? Of course is much more affordable than the clam base I am talking about (that one must be refrigerated and it is semi solid but it does have a truly clam smell) so I bought it and immediately tried it on a seafood chowder cilantro based. A very simple soup that includes hulled barley, onions finely chopped, fresh corn, small diced potatoes and fresh chilies properly sauteed with fresh garlic and olive oil and then blended with the cilantro and a couple of cans of quality diced tomatoes, preferably the ones with a little herbs thrown in. Who am I kidding? The ones they sell at Costco! This soup replaces the hard task of making your own fish stock which requires good fish heads with very clear eyes and all the other ingredients. Too much work for a wannabee cook these days but if done right it is every bit as good as anything you can eat these days. Throw some scallops, different fish, clams (if you can find plump ones), two or three fillets of mahi mahi, large shrimp, etc. But in the end, really, if the broth is good that is all a person would need to enjoy a hot cup or two of fish broth.This one does not quite reach the levels of goodness I am referring to. It does the job but the final product lacks that essence of the sea, it is a little too processed?Please do not get me wrong. I use the Knorr Chicken Powder and it works for me, a great value, so perhaps some people are more than satisfied with this product as well. I give it 3 Stars but that is it and I realize I am deviating from all the other 5 Star ratings, but the thing is, when you had the chance to try a superior product this one just can not compete. My chowder ended tasting okey but not spectacularly good and that hurts for I threw in a whole lot of seafood. Happy to have Albertsons sell this little packages of $1 each that allows for variety even though it is not the best of the catch they do offer bay scallops, different fishes, even shrimp and calamari, so it is not a bad deal. 3 Stars.

Product Title: CHIQUIL√çN hot paprika, 2.64 oz - 75 grams - Gourmet Products since 1909
Review: Not your best bet if you want smoky paprika - try another brand. Well, I ordered three tins of smoked paprika, one each of sweet, bittersweet and hot.I love the smokiness and flavor it imparts to dishes, and wanted to try some otherstrengths.We received the cans today. It was well-packaged and everything arrived in great shape.The seller was also quick to ship the order out. I have no problems at all with the seller.One tin expires in 2012, and the other two are 2013, so guess I got an older tin of one strength.This review is for the MILD (or sweet) paprika from Chiquilin.What a disappointment!This has NO smoky aroma at all, despite it supposedly being a smoked product.I have not cooked with it yet, but I surely hope that it adds more flavor than it does aroma.Otherwise, I could have just bought plain paprika in the grocery store for a lot less.(The actual smoky paprika ([[ASIN:B000NO943C Smoked Paprika Tin]]) DOES have a wonderful smoky aroma and was what I expected from all the versions.)I read a lot of different information about the brands, and while this was not my #1 choice on brands,it was affordable and the seller did combined shipping, which was why I chose it. I guess you get whatyou pay for? I was under the assumption that all of the Spanish paprikas were smoked paprikas, and you just gotdifferent strengths of the roast. This does not seem to be the case with this brand.We are going to keep the mild/sweet and the smoked, but returning the hot without opening it.I hope it tastes better than it smells. I am admittedly disappointed in the aromatic qualities(or lack of them) of this particular mild paprika. You can probably do better with another brand.

Well, I've bought these a couple of times before.The little bags make it nice and easy for my husband to have a snackand help control his blood sugar while at work.The price needs to be watched though.They opened a Sam's Club near us recently, and this same box is $7.99 there.Of course, no one has to pay shipping that way, but they are basicallydoubling the cost here to cover the "free" shipping.Other than that, they are tasty little peanuts in a very convenient package.

Product Title: Pop Secret 100 Calorie Butter Popcorn, 11.2 Ounce
Review: Great Popcorn But Much Too Expensive. I love this popcorn, it is very tart and has just the right amount of salt. The reason I only gave it 4.stars is because I found I could buy the same size box of Pop Secret 100 Calorie Popcorn in the grocery store for $4.69, it is too expensive on Amazon.

Product Title: DOTS Individually Wrapped Candy - Original Gummy Candy Flavors - Cherry, Lime, Orange, Lemon & Strawberry - Gluten Free, Kosher & Peanut Free Gumdrops - Bulk 12ct, 6.5oz Dots Candy Boxes
Review: Not good if one want to loose weight :). I keep them in the refrigerator once opened (they attracts bugs). But they're addictive. Not terribly sweat.

Product Title: Wilton Red Cookie Icing, 9 Oz.
Review: While not as good as making homemade royal icing. While not as good as making homemade royal icing, it is far more convenient. The application works well for decorating, making it a nice time-saver around holiday baking season.

Product Title: Tillamook Country Smoker - Beef Stick 36 ct Bulk Retail Refill 0.9-1 lbs Beef Jerky Sausage Stick Meat Snack Camping Hiking
Review: After one try, you'll never go back. I actually live a few miles from the Smoker, but their website was down and my out-of-town husband was jonesing for some sticks. So, I paid extra and ordered from Amazon as an stop gap measure. He was ordering for a bunch of boys down in Texas that had actually heard about our little smoker.... needless to say, not it's a non-stop job to keep them supplied with pounds and pounds of these things.... I purchased the beef sticks and the pepperoni. The pepperonis are the clear favs down there, but they'll eat anything that shows up from the Smoker. If you've tried other brands, I challenge you to try just one order of these and compare. You'll never look at others again in the same way. (SORRY AMAZON)... and order directly from the Smoker when their website works, it's a better price. I order from Amazon nearly every day... but sometimes the pricing on Amazon is a bit out of the reasonable.

Product Title: Fazer Marianne Chocolate Filled Mint Candies Imported From Finland 7.76oz(220g)
Review: Chocolate with an minty shell. I bought these after someone mentioned it was their favorite European candy. It sounded good - a thin minty shell wrapped around good chocolate - so I figured I'd give it a try. Personally, I could go either way on them - I'd prefer the shell was slightly thinner so I could chew it right up and get both textures and flavors at once. However, if you let it sit in the mouth for a bit, it gets to that state in about 90 seconds, so not a deal breaker. The mint is decent quality, about a standard sugary peppermint. The chocolate is reasonable quality, better than most common American confections. All in all its an interesting treat.While I am so-so on it, the rest of the family likes it quite a lot and have about finished off the bag already. Whereas I probably won't order it again for myself, I will be ordering it again for them, and possible a couple members of the extended family these holidaysSo would recommend trying at least once, they deserve that much.

Product Title: PLANTERS Variety Packs (Salted Cashews, Salted Peanuts & Honey Roasted Peanuts), 24 Packs - Individual Bags of On-the-Go Nut Snacks - No Cholesterol or Trans Fats - Source of Fiber and Healthy Fats
Review: purchased as a pantry gift for a friend. I purchased these as part of a pantry gift for a friend who needed some help in feeding a family of 5! She reports that they arrived in good shape and were tasty as well! Good source of quick, easy protein and calories.

Product Title: Lao Gan Ma Spicy Chili Crisp (Chili Oil Sauce) - 7.41 Ounce+ Only one NineChef Spoon
Review: Delicious but Overpriced. Delicious product but very overpriced. The 99 Ranch store down the street sells them for $2. Still, they tend to be sold out at that store. In that case, I'd still shell out the $10 the buy these.Yes, it's that good.

Product Title: Frontier Co-op Organic Fair Trade Ground Ceylon Cinnamon 5.57oz
Review: How can you go wrong with Cinnamon?! This is a wonderful way to save money on a relatively expensive spice. The Ceylon is a smooth scent and subtle taste. I usually double the amount required in all recipes, but not everyone likes this. It surprises me, but some people just like that *hint* .... This is a very good cinnamon for that purpose. It is quite floral.

Product Title: Nectave Organic Sweetener Premium Blue Agave Nectar On The Go Stick Packs (100 Pack)
Review: These are great for travel. I use agave almost exclusively in lieu of sugar in my coffee and tea. Most places don‚Äôt have it so finding these was great. The only reason I dropped to 4 stars is the packets are really hard to open. No notch to start your tear. I often have to scrounge up a knife or scissors which isn‚Äôt always easy when traveling

Product Title: Wasa Crisp'n Light 7 Grain Cracker Bread, 4.9 Ounce (Pack of 10)
Review: Healthy snack and good staple. These crackers make wonderful snacks, are a tasty substitute for bread, and perfect spread-board for jam, hummus, salmon, PB&J, etc. Dip in chili, break over chowder or be decadently European: generous layer of butter and dip in your morning cafe au lait - less healthy but very delicious!

Product Title: Carnation Breakfast Essentials Powder Drink Mix, Classic French Vanilla, 10 Count Box of Packets (Pack of 6) (Packaging May Vary)
Review: Ugh it's so expensive for those of us who need it... ... for medically compromised parents/children who need more protein in their diets. The flavor is so much better than Ensure or whatever and I guess that makes this worth the price, but most of us full-time caregivers (I'd guess especially those of us who have been taking care of our kids for decades) are already financially strapped and insurances/Medicaid do not pay anything unless it is IV nutrition. Oh well. It is a great product and I am so grateful to be able to find it here.

Review: nothing to improve. I really like this cotton candy very goodüôÇ

Product Title: Taylors of Harrogate Lapsang Souchong, 50 Teabags

Product Title: Taylors of Harrogate Lapsang Souchong, 50 Teabags
Review: Priced doubled in 5 months; quality suffered. I love this tea! A breakfast tea that is not too harsh yet brisk enough to start my day. In July 2022, I ordered a box of 100 teabags that were individually packaged for $9.96. December 2022 I tried to re-order but was surprised to see that the price has doubled to $19.99. In order to get the same July price, I had to order two boxes of 50 bags that are: (1) not individually packaged, (2) two bags are attached to each other so you do have to rip them a part which is no big deal, (3) these bags are missing the string on each to easily remove the teabag from scalding water in tea cup; (4) the box has no inner wax paper lining to keep the tea from drying out. Disappointing. With what‚Äôs going on in the world today with supply chain issues and all, I can understand a price increase but double?! I‚Äôll be putting the new teabags in a jar with a tight fitting lid to keep them fresh. My photo shows the new box of tea bags with no lining with the previous individually packaged tea bag in front of it.

Product Title: Nik-L-Nips Wax Bottle Candy - 5 LB Resealable Stand Up Candy Bag (approx. 330 pieces) - Wax Bottles Filled with Flavored Syrups - Cherry, Orange, Lemon, Blue Raspberry, and Green Apple Flavors

Review: easy to make. This is so much easier ,than buying envelopes . Just open the jar and make the amount you need,each time. Less waste. there are tiny pieces of mushrooms,in it also.

I recently had to go caffeine free and that seems to be a game changer.But still, good deal for the money snd if you‚Äôre looking for a tasty medium blend, Maud‚Äôs is it.

Product Title: Ghirardelli Squares, Intense Dark Chocolate Midnight Reverie 86% Cacao, 4.12 Ounce Bag (Pack of 6)

Product Title: Yoshi Premium Rice Wine Vinegar - 1L (34oz) | Authentic, Dressings, Sauces, Sushi Rice, Pickling, Marinades, Stir Fry
Review: Hard to find. I don‚Äôt use this often, yet I really like having some on hand. Lately, it has been hard to find a reasonably priced source. Product Title: Kraft Easy Mac Original Macaroni & Cheese Microwavable Dinner (6 ct Packets)
Review: Great for when you need something to eat fast. I will say that you need to use a bigger bowl than you'd expect as the water will bubble and overflow. This then means less liquid to cook the noodles. Overall, not uhappy with the product, I love that I can make a fast mini meal or snack

Product Title: belVita Cinnamon Brown Sugar Breakfast Biscuits, 30 Total Packs, 6 Boxes (4 Biscuits Per Pack)
Review: These breakfast biscuits are very tasty. They are quick ... These breakfast biscuits are very tasty. They are quick inexpensive breakfast option even if you are on the go. The only thing I don't care for is how the biscuits get stuck in your teeth.

Product Title: Crystallized Ginger by D'Allesandro, 5 LB Bag
Review: Decent for cost. Decent taste but way to much sugar coating. Usually a quick rinse and let dry gets sugar down to eatable level. This is also fact of most dried ginger to my taste buds Got quite a few hard, woody spots in this batch. Would buy again.

Product Title: The Gluten Free Brothers Dark Chocolate Coconut Bites - Gluten Free Protein Balls ‚Äì Non GMO, Soy Free, Vegan ‚Äì Snack Size Plant Based Protein Energy Balls, 4 oz (6 Count)
