Product Title: Ocean Spray, Original Craisins, Dried Cranberries, 5oz Pouch (Pack of 6)
Review: Tasty but high priced. I first had these on a flight and I thought they tasted great. I wanted to purchase them but couldn't find them at the grocery stores I normally shop at. I ordered them here but then I found them somewhere else at a fraction of the price. In this order you get six 5 oz bags. If I want healthy, Amazon is is my only option overseas.

Product Title: Biltong Seasoned Dried Beef, Original Sliced, 8 oz
Review: Ok, but dry. The taste is good...but not great.The meat was dry, not fresh and moist

Product Title: Hakubaku Organic Udon, Authentic Japanese Wheat Noodles, No Added Salt, 9.5 Ounce (Pack of 8)
Review: expensive, but tastes good. My local Asian grocery store sells this same brand of "organic" udon noodles for about the same price as Amazon (except that they only make you buy one pack at a time). They also sell non-organic udon noodles that look and taste about the same for less than half the price. Is the "organic" worth the extra money? You have to decide for yourself.Udon is a great general purpose noodle. For a quick cheap tasty bowl of noodle soup, just boil some udon noodles and add some miso soup paste and vegetables. One 3 ounce bundle of dry noodles conveniently makes a nice serving of cooked noodles. A bowl of soup like this takes about the same amount of time to cook as instant ramen, but since the udon noodles are not full of salt and oil, they are a lot healthier for you. Yes, udon does cost a little more than instant ramen, but you can save money by going with the non-organic noodles, and they are still much healthier than instant ramen.You can also stir-fry the noodles or make them into a salad. For a full meal, top the noodles with a serving of meat and sauce.

Product Title: Pacific Foods Organic Free Range Chicken Broth, 8oz, 4-pack
Review: grocery gift for a friend. I purchased this in a group of many other things as a gift for a friend who needed some pantry items to feed a family of 5. I am happy to report that these arrived in good shape and according to my friend, tasty!

Product Title: EDGE Natural Artesian Water - Fiji Pure Drinking Water - Natural Artesian Water From Fiji - Bottled Nature Water √¢‚Ç¨‚Äú 20.28 Fl Oz, (Pack of 24)
Review: This does not taste like Fiji water. It is a product of Fiji, and artesian water, but it has the taste of minerals in it, as Figi water does not. It's quite different. It also costs less, which is a good thing. The only other negative is that the bottles are very very hard to open. The plastic is thin, so in holding tight to the bottle, you apply pressure to keep it closed, and even with a nifty little grip-tight (thanks, Amazon!), it is tough to open. Other than that, it's water.I have now figured out how to open it. Run a sharp knife along the perforation on the cap. Snaps it right open, easy peasy.However, the plastic being so thin means you may also get a case with some bottle's tops bent over and rammed back towards the bottle. The best procedure I've found there is to take a sharp knife and ram the tip into the bottle and decant it. If you are lucky, you'll find a spot where the water isn't pressing against the plastic, eager to spurt out.

Product Title: Marie Callender's Lemon Meringue Pie Frozen Dessert, 31.5 oz
Review: Not exactly what I was looking for. This is lemon meringue pie that arrives frozen. I really wanted to find some of the lemon icebox pie that's made with condensed milk, but only key lime pie comes close. I will keep looking.

Product Title: Anna and Sarah Cinnamon Pecans (2 Lbs)
Review: pretty good, I have had better but the price is decent and they are tasty enough. Pretty good. I tried this brand because the [[ASIN:B09QW52HRF brand I had recently tried went up]] $3-4 in price (influx of 5 star reviews, mine included because they were just so good). But I figured I would shop around and see if I could find something comparable. These are good but not amazing. They dont quite grab my tastebuds like the ones I linked to. Just something different about these despite having similar ingredients. Also, the occasional pecan tastes off, like it is beginning to go rancid. Hasn't stopped me from eating them, and like any sweet coated nut, these are hard to stop eating once I start.Again, these are "good" but not blow my mind amazing. I'll enjoy them alone or added to hot oats. But I will likely cough up the few extra bucks for the other.

Product Title: Kevala Organic Coconut Aminos, 35 Fluid Ounce
Review: First time to ty it out, so far, nice! I used to use other brands, but can not use soy or sodium for health reasons.Very happy to find this, similar taste, used it in a few salad dressings and to enhance other dishes.I predominantly cook with herbs and natural spices these days, no salt needed!This one I can recommend!I will keep using it and come back in a few weeks to update!

Product Title: Idahoan Mashed Potatoes, Buttery Homestyle, 1.5 Ounce (Pack of 12)
Review: lost one star for price, not taste. It's absolutely delicious, but a little pricy

Product Title: Blue Diamond Almond Nut Thins Cracker Crisps, Hint Of Sea Salt, 2oz, Single Serve, 6 Count
Review: All these for 90 calories?! Yes! Great crunchy snacks to fulfill a craving for crunch and cheese! Omg, you get a ton of these for the 90 calories in each pack.If you've never had these crackers, don't expect a real, forward almond flavor.

Product Title: Ito En Traditional Matcha Green Tea 50 Count Zero Calories, Caffeinated
Review: Good product. I wish this was organic but they really helped me. I have always had swelling in my ankles but after a few months of drinking this the swelling is gone.

Product Title: Heinz All Natural Apple Cider Vinegar with 5% Acidity (32 fl oz Bottle) - Packaging may vary
Review: Great product, confusing listing. Heinz cider vinegar is clear, consistent in quality, and flavorful. It contains no grain or gluten like some distilled vinegars, and no added sulfates or sulfites like a lot of wine vinegars.Be careful with this listing though. When I ordered, this listing specified the shipping weight was over 37 pounds and the price was around 30 dollars. I assumed I would receive a case quantity.What I received was one very expensive 32-ounce bottle of Heinz cider vinegar. Amazon customer service (always excellent!) quickly made it right, though.Enjoy the vinegar. Just make sure the listing is clear about what you will receive.

Product Title: Greek Giant Beans, Gigantes, approx. 16 oz (1lb)
Review: Beans is beans! These are very large dried lima beans. I first tasted them at a Whole Foods store. They were in a mildly sweet sauce and I liked them, so being an experimental cook, I decided to try cooking some at home and recreate the sauce for serving them. The idea seemed sound, but so far I haven't been able to cook them without having most of the skins come off...not exactly what I was after. They are very good, however, so I will keep experimenting. I don't have a pressure cooker, so that could be part of my difficulty. I may try slow cooking next. By the way, my sauce turned out just fine...

Product Title: Kashi Cold Breakfast Cereal, Vegetarian, Organic Fiber Cereal, Honey Toasted, 12oz Box (1 Box)
Review: Good cereal especially for gluten free diets. I really like this cereal. It's not available locally and this is a fair price. I thought it would be like raisin bran but it's more like special k . The flakes are puffy but crunchy and the berries are flavorful and plump up in milk. It doesn't have an overwhelming sweetness either.

Product Title: DINTY MOORE Big Microwaveable Bowl, Scalloped Potatoes and Ham, 15 Ounce (Pack of 8)
Review: Not bad at all! Either I was very hungry at dinner or this tasted better than I thought it would. I deducted a star because the potatoes were not quite as firm as I would like, although this satisfied my hunger. I added a vegetable and it was a full meal. Not what I would eat every day, but it is definitely comfort food. If there is a lot of sodium in this, I couldn't taste it.

Product Title: Peeled Snacks Organic Dried Fruit, Mango, √¢√¢‚Äö¬¨√¢‚Ç¨≈ì Healthy, Vegan Snacks for On-the-Go, Lunch and More, 1.23 Ounce (Pack of 10)
Review: Wow, it is the real McCoy. Looks shriveled and unlike the other dried mango slices...there is no sweetness, but after a few slices the mango flavor comes through delicately. a little chewy and hard texture. It appeals to me as you can tell very little additives were added in the drying process. Shame there is so few in the bag, and I am feeling guilty for the additional plastic I have generated by buying this product. But as far as dried fruit goes, this is a good product.

Product Title: King Arthur Gluten-Free Pancake Mix,15 oz
Review: Good flavorful buy for those on gluten-free diets. I like the King Arthur gluten-free products because they're not expensive and they taste good. They are a good flavorful buy for people on a gluten-free diet.

Product Title: Walden Farms Honey Balsamic Vinaigrette Dressing 12 Oz. Bottle (Pack of 6) - Fresh & Delicious Salad Topping, 0g Net Carbs Condiment, Kosher Certified - Great on Salads, Drizzled on Fruits, Vegetables and More
Review: Dressing okay but not my first pick. Prefer the Italian Walden Farms. I was somewhat disappointed in the balsamic Vinaigrette Dressing by Walden Farms. Nothing wrong with it other than I prefer the Walden Farms Italian flavor over this flavor. This is a preference review not a product review. The product was okay.

Product Title: Tara's All Natural Handcrafted Gourmet Sea Salt Caramel: Small Batch, Kettle Cooked, Creamy & Individually Wrapped - 11.5 Ounce

Review: Flag we could find this product. we need Nandos Resturant in The Bay area!

Product Title: Harney & Sons Orange Pekoe Tea, 50 ct teabag box
Review: Its tea what am I supposed to say. Its just alright it is nothing fancy or exciting. If you drink tea you might enjoy this one just brew it as the instructions say because if you don't it will taste bitter.

Product Title: LILA BAZAAR - ORGANIC Sun-Dried Turkish Apricots 2LB, Natural Taste and Fresh, Nutritious and Healthy Snack, In Resealable Bag, No Sulfur Added, No Sugar Added and No Artificial Flavors!!!
Review: Substantial texture, flavor like a cross between apricots and figs. So I'm not a big fan of these, but it's mostly just a matter of taste. These are sweeter than the apricots I'm used to, specifically California sun-dried apricots, which tend to be tart. They are half-way between apricots and Turkish figs, in flavor. Now I don't particularly like figs, so obviously these aren't for me. But if you like figs but aren't in love with the texture, or find them a bit much, this may be a decent compromise.Freshness and texture are both solid - nice and fibrous but not so consistent as the more traditional dried apricots can sometimes be. Two or three is sufficient for a single snack.So I wouldn't buy them again, but would probably recommend trying once, if the above appeals to you.

Product Title: Arizona Watermelon, 23 Fl Oz (Pack of 24)
Review: Watch what you buy. The product was exactly as i expected and i would have bought morebut it almost Doubled After my 1st purchase. This seller just lost another customer.

Product Title: Glenny's Low Fat Soy Crisps, Creamy Ranch, 1.3-Ounce Bags (Pack of 24)
Review: Decent healthy replacement for chips. I originally purchased these as a more affordable option for WonderSlim/Medifast snacks.The bag is a decent amount, especially if you eat with a dip (say a little greek yogurt or fat free sour cream and salsa).The taste is more bland than I'm used to. I'd be okay with the chip being healthy and the flavoring being less healthy (i.e., more salty and better sticking to the chip) as that would at least help satisfy my cravings better.The flavoring is actually decent, it just falls off the chips and sticks at the bottom of the bag. I might buy my own ranch flavoring to sprinkle over these right before eating.I'm buying more. I tried the barbecue flavor, and they tasted more like meat to me than bbq sauce, which I found discomfiting. I'll see how the sea salt flavor go too.

Product Title: Wild Planet Wild Skipjack Tuna, Sea Salt, Tinned Fish, Canned Tuna, Sustainably Caught, Non-GMO, Kosher, Gluten Free, Keto and Paleo, 3rd Party Mercury Tested, 5 Ounce (Pack of 4)
Review: Great tuna to stock up. Mostly the entire can is packed and very good no waste , really good buy

Product Title: Mary's Chicken, Chicken Whole Fryer Bagged Air Chilled Heirloom Pasture Raised Step 4
Review: Ad and photo did not match.! Checked the ad and saw the photo. Ad did not say "organic", but the photo of the product shows the "organic" label. Hoping it was the "organic" product, but I received the "non- organic" product. Oh well. Maybe the "shopper" did not double check their work, or at least advise me during their shopping.

Product Title: Terra Vegetable Chips, Blues with Sea Salt, 5 oz
Review: Cut Too Thick. They are fancy and tasty but maybe a little too frou-frou for me. Put it this way: they taste like they are good for you.

Product Title: Grove Square Hot Cocoa Pods, Milk Chocolate, Single Serve (Pack of 24) (Packaging May Vary)
Review: A very respectable cup of cocoa ... This is a good alternative for when you need that up of cocoa, and you want to use your Keurig machine. I've found that you have to use one of the "smaller" cup settings or the cocoa will taste watered-down. I have a B70 Platinum Keurig, and I set it on the next-to-the-smallest cup setting -- that makes for a creamy full-flavored cup of cocoa.The flavor isn't too sweet -- my problem with most instant cocoa products. Just a lot of good chocolate flavor. I drink this a couple of times a week.

Product Title: Hershey's Nuggets Special Dark Chocolate Truffles, 10.5-Ounce Bags (Pack of 6)
Review: Not bad for the price ... I'm a sucker for dark chocolate, so when these became available, I had to try them.They're not bad at all. If you're familiar with Hershey's Nuggets, these will look and "feel" somewhat familiar. Hershey's isn't the highest quality chocolate out there, but for the price, it's a decent buy.My only quibble with these is the "truffle" filling. I'm used to chocolate truffle that is silky smooth. This seems a tad "grainy" for my taste. The flavor is just fine: a nice dark semi-sweet chocolate taste. But the texture of the filling wasn't quite as smooth as I would have liked and expected.Still, for the money, they're just fine. They have a nice intense dark chocolate flavor with no bitterness, and that puts them well ahead of some of the competition. Amazon's price makes these a decent buy, too.

Product Title: Shock Coffee Ground, The Strongest Caffeinated All-Natural Coffee. Up to 50% more Caffeine. 1 pound
Review: Strong. Bought this hoping for strong coffee and that is exactly what I got. Good strong flavor and plenty of caffeine to keep ya going.

Product Title: McCormick Gourmet Organic Ground White Pepper, 1.75 Oz
Review: Very good ground pepper Watch out for gushes when using. I am happy overall with the product. However, the holes for the pepper spice are very large. I have to shake into my palm and then use my other hand to evenly apply the pepper onto meat or into soups. Other than the shaker top allowing too much to come out at once, the spice itself it good.

Product Title: Nescafe Clasico Instant Coffee,7 Ounce (Pack of 2)
Review: Tasted ok but prefer another style of Nescafe will use ... Tasted ok but prefer another style of Nescafe will use until gone and then switch back to Taster's Choice. Personal taste.

Product Title: Nongshim Soon Cup Noodle Soup, Veggie, 2.6 Ounce (Pack of 6), Set of 2
Review: Better than others. Instead it is more on spicy side. No veggies flavor. But noodles are good. I have bought twice now, reasonable cost, good product.

Product Title: Taylors of Harrogate Yorkshire Gold, 160 Teabags
Review: Good if kept fresh. Place in a sealed container immediately. Label each container. Good when fresh. I initially purchased this item at a grocery store. Liked the taste.Two big negatives.1. Not individually sealed.2. Bags not labelled. No label. no string.Since I removed the bags from the large container to save space, and since I buy different teas, I couldn't remember which tea I had. Didn't use it quickly, not individually sealed, and the tea lost its flavor.Decided to try it again. This time, immediately put all the bags in 2 sealed tea containers I purchased from Teavana. Hope this will allow the tea to retain the fresh flavor.

Product Title: PUR Gum | Sugar Free Chewing Gum | 100% Xylitol | Vegan, Aspartame Free, Gluten Free & Keto Friendly | Natural Peppermint Flavored Gum, 55 Pieces (Pack of 6)
Review: Not my fave. Not my favorite flavor. I prefer the cinnamon one. This flavor gets harder to chew fairly quickly. It‚Äôs good if you just need to pop something in for a quick refresher.

Product Title: Juicy Juice Orange Tangerine, 4.23 Ounce Boxes, 8 Count (Pack of 5)
Review: Need better shipping. Product is great but shipping is horrible as product breaks open

Product Title: steep by Bigelow Organic Rooibos Hibiscus Caffeine-Free Herbal Tea, 20 Count (Pack of 6), 120 Tea Bags Total
Review: People seemed to like it. I give it 4 stars because I ... I'm not a tea drinker but I bought this for a little girls wine party I had at home for those who didn't drink alcohol. I made iced tea and added strawberries to it. People seemed to like it. I give it 4 stars because I personally didn't like it (bc I don't like tea).

Product Title: High Brew Coffee, Cold Brew, Nitro Sweet Cream, 10 Fl Oz Can (Pack of 12)
Review: Bold but not perfect. I bought a 12 pack,The can size is perfect. The taste is bold but not as smooth. I am used to drink espressos and there is something missing. Maybe a little more milk?

Product Title: Cadbury Easter Egg - Mini Eggs Bag Family Size 296g
Review: Lesson learned. Well, I found the exact same product at Walgreens yesterday in a bigger package for less than $9. I paid almost $20 for this puny package. Good thing it's addictive.

Product Title: Miracle Noodle Angel Hair Pasta - Plant Based Shirataki Noodles, Keto, Vegan, Gluten-Free, Low Calories, Low Carb, Paleo, Soy Free, Non-GMO - Perfect for Your Keto Diet - 7 oz (Pack of 24)
Review: The product AND the price stinks! Love everything about them but the price and the smell. Yes, the price stinks as does the product. But, a good rinse takes care of the smell. Now, hopefully the manufacturer will eventually get rid of the high cost?

Product Title: Progresso Vegetable Classics, Garden Vegetable Canned Soup, 19 oz.
Review: Solid basic soup. I prefer a little more zest and tomato flavor, but overall this gets the job done.

Product Title: Popcorn Packs, Pre-Measured, Movie Theater Style, All-in-One Kernel, Salt, Oil Packets for Popcorn Machines by Great Northern Popcorn, 6 Ounce (Pack of 24)
Review: Very good popcorn. You can never go back to microwave popcorn. A little bit too salty. I remove about a teaspoon of seasonings before popping. Also, I use unsalted butter

Product Title: Monin - Passion Fruit Syrup, Sweet Tropical Flavors, Great for Teas, Sodas, & Cocktails, Natural Flavors, No Artificial Sweeteners or Ingredients, Gluten-Free, Vegan, Non-GMO, Clean Label (750ml)
Review: tastes good, but not very visible on cheesecake. tastes good, but not very visible on cheesecake compared to berry sauces.

Product Title: Big Train Blended Ice Coffee, Kona Mocha, Powdered Instant Coffee Drink Mix, 3.5 Pound (Packaging May Vary)
Review: A lot pricey... But worth it if you have a diabetic in the house that likes a blended coffee drink on occasion. I'm so glad Big Train offered a sugar free alternative because their regular blend mixes are loaded with sugar. They used a decent sweetener because I do not taste the chemical taste that comes with other sugar free products. Since we only have these every once in a while it won't break the bank, but I would not purchase these on a monthly basis if we drank them more often. They are way too expensive for that.

Product Title: BEN'S ORIGINAL Ready Rice Cheese Risotto Flavored Rice, Easy Dinner Side, 8.5 oz Pouch (Pack of 12)
Review: A great quick rice. Love this! Just easy to heat rice and NO salt!

Product Title: Litehouse Freeze Dried Jalapeno Peppers - Freeze Dried Pepper, Substitute for Fresh Jalapeno, Dried Pepper Flakes, Non-GMO, Gluten-Free - 0.39 Ounce
Review: Not as strong as fresh. The flavor(s) are not as strong as I had expected. I thought they would be concentrated but was very mild. In some dishes that is preferable tho! I've used them in soup, hamburger and beans to only slightly detect their presence.

Product Title: Go Lightly Sugar Free Hard Candy Assorted 2.75 oz Bag, Kosher
Review: Good sucking candy for after meals or for a pick-me-up during the day. I often have one after some food or coffee. They are refreshing and last awhile in the mouth. They last awhile in my mouth.

Product Title: Frito-Lay Variety Pack, Party Mix, 40 Count (Pack of 1)
Review: you don't eat too many this way. when you buy 40 small bags. you get a variety of 8 types of chips and funyons.

Product Title: A&W Diet Cream Soda, 12 Ounce (12 Cans) (4 Pack)
Review: Tastes like root beer without the sugar. Overall this no sugar A&W root beer tastes like the regular A&W root beer, which is pretty good because I normally hate the taste of artificial sugar. I haven't drank root beer in a while, but this tastes pretty sweet.

Product Title: Progresso Traditional, Chicken & Orzo with Lemon Soup, 18.5 oz (Pack of 6)
Review: Great soup ... nice change from chicken noodle, the lemon flavor is lovely and it makes a delicious lunch or supper. I have to confess I usually eat the whole can myself, but it doesn't break my calorie bank, even with toast or crackers. Very satisfying!

Product Title: Snickers 100 Calories Chocolate Candy Bars, 0.76 Ounce (Pack of 24)
Review: So fresh and tasty, my favorite! I love these bite-sized Snickers ! They are bigger than the mini snickers usually sold in bags, and smaller than a full size bar. These are about 3.5" long x 1/2" thick, (100 calorie snack). Each bar has 13g carbs, and 11g sugars. This is a fraction of a full size bar but with less sugar and carbs. Perfect size to stuff in my bag or to add to my kids lunch bag.If you love Snickers and want to watch your diet or weight, these are really great. But they are very addictive and small, so you may be tempted to eat more of them.If you found my review helpful, please click below so I can improve my reviews and help others as well.

Product Title: Back to Nature Gluten Free Crackers, Non-GMO Multi-Seed Rice Thins, 4 Ounce
Review: 5 if on taste 4 for too small oz. Wish came in larger box

Product Title: Tara's All Natural Handcrafted Gourmet Sea Salt Caramel: Small Batch, Kettle Cooked, Creamy & Individually Wrapped - 11.5 Ounce
Review: Just too soft. Would have gave 5 stars if they weren't so soft. The product was so soft it was almost gooey. They tasted great though and I've gotten ones that were perfect. I chalk it up to a bad batch. Would recommend and buy again.

Product Title: Nutiva Organic Cold-Pressed Unrefined Raw Hemp Seed Oil, 24 Ounce, USDA Organic, Non-GMO, Whole 30 Approved, Vegan, Gluten-Free & Keto, Rich In Omega 3 & 6 Fatty Acids
Review: AWESOME. I love that this hemp oil doesn't change flavor of foods it is added to. And it is a healthy choice to add to most all dishes. I use it for my home-made dressing. I also add a couple of drops to my dog's food, with two drops of organic coconut oil too. My dogs is healthier and stronger than Popeye! :)

Product Title: Jordan's Skinny Syrups Butter Toffee, Sugar Free Coffee Flavoring Syrup, 25.4 Ounce Bottle (Pack of 6)
Review: The jury is still out. The product is good and it's good for keto but it's a little too sweet. Very sugary tasting I'm going to try the other flavors

Product Title: Macadamia Nuts | MacFarms Dry Roasted Macadamia Nuts 24 OZ (1 Pack) - Premium Roasted Nuts with Sea Salt Fresh From Hawaii, Sea Salt Flavored Healthy Snack
Review: Hubby prefers these to Mauna Loa, but not me. We went Keto several months back, so we really upped our nut intake. Although expensive, it's definitely worth it to have these around to snack on. When I realized we were spending upwards of $30 a week on tinned macadamia nuts we bought at the local groceries (3 x 4.5 oz. x $8-9 = 13.5 oz for almost $30!), this was clearly a better alternative.As I said, my husband and kids LOVE these. And they ARE really great, overall. But personally, for some reason, I like the taste of the Mauna Loa brand better. We'll keep getting these instead, though, because not only is it an excellent value, but between the kids and hubby, I'm outnumbered.In terms of freshness, these are excellent. Occasionally, you'll get one or two nuts that seem soft and a little stale-tasting, but I guess that's to be expected?

Product Title: Bear Naked Fit, Granola, Triple Berry, Kosher and Vegan, 4.5lb Case (6 Count)
Review: Inharmonious assembly of ingredients. None of the six bags we received in our box include clusters of any kind, but rather grains of oats and everything else that is included in the fruit and nut blend. Having this in small doses such as in a little cup for a snack, a topping for yogurt, ice cream, or mixed into plain cooked oatmeal, it is okay but sometimes you only get the oats and a residual fruit or nut bit. It's not granola that we select for pouring in a bowl with some milk. We're at the point of saving the majority of oats in a jar in the refrigerator for use in bread dough because the texture when it's free of the fruit or nuts is unappealing. It is not a winner in this household but it's not so bad that it won't eventually be consumed.EDIT: I've raised my rating because by transferring the bag contents into a jar, we have discovered that you can shake it before consuming and get a better mix of the blended ingredients. The lack of overpowering sweetness also is a definite positive. It's been growing on me and I personally now rather like the granola a lot with milk, either cow or almond. It's chewy and doesn't get soggy in the bowl.

Product Title: PUR Gum | Sugar Free Chewing Gum | 100% Xylitol | Vegan, Aspartame Free, Gluten Free & Keto Friendly | Natural Peppermint Flavored Gum, 55 Pieces (Pack of 6)
Review: these are better than Glee. Flavor lasts long enough, so I don't have to use too many. In my opinion, these are better than Glee.

Product Title: Alvita Organic Tea Spearmint - 24 Tea Bags
Review: Received in good time. I'm still not a lover of hibiscus ... Received in good time. I'm still not a lover of hibiscus tea (or herbal tea in general) but of all the herbal teas that I've tried, I do like this and it doesn't give me heartburn like Lipton does which is a plus. My favorite is still jasmine tea but if I have to drink hibiscus tea (and given that I'm trying to keep any hypertension under control), this may be the one for me.

Product Title: Namaste Foods Gluten Free Waffle & Pancake Mix, 21 Oz
Review: This is a good brand and makes good pancakes. I like this brand for a lot of their gluten-free foods. These pancakes turn out very well, fluffy and light, and they taste good. I don't find this to be a very expensive price either, especially for gluten-free.

Product Title: N'Joy Zero Calorie Sweetener | Green Stevia Packets | 200 Count | Kosher | Gluten Free and Sodium Free
Review: Good for the price. I like it, it is the splenda clone. For the price difference, it is worth four stars.

Product Title: Diet Pepsi, 12 Fl Oz Bottles, 8 Pack
Review: Great. I love that I can get drinks from Amazon now, but they are a bit overpriced.

Product Title: Katz Gluten Free Glazed Donuts | Dairy Free, Nut Free, Soy Free, Gluten Free | Kosher (1 Pack of 6 Donuts, 11.3 Ounce)
Review: Good if your into Gluten free. My mistake.....gluten free is the nastiest thing I have ever tried, but they shipped well!

Product Title: Spice Jungle Five Peppercorn M√©lange - 4 oz.
Review: Tasty Tasty with just one shortcoming... I bought this because I'm one of those people that thinks more is better. FIVE! types of pepper! The taste from grinding is fabulous. Will never look at ground black pepper in the cardboard shaker the same way. Used whole in cooking is a real treat.Only negative is that there is one peppercorn variety that is larger than the others, approaching the size of a pea and my grinder isn't able to grab them. I had to manually crush them and put them back in the mill.

Product Title: Best Maid Hamburger Slices 1 Gal (4 Pack)
Review: Don‚Äôt pass these dill pickles up. I have not tasted dill pickle as good as these I love the taste because i love to eat dill pickles. If you like dill pickles don‚Äôt pass these up the jar is huge so they should last you awhile.

Product Title: Mount+Hagen%2c+Coffee+Instant+Jar+Regulr+-+3.53+Ounce
Review: From jar to package? Good coffee, not a competitor for Starbucks Vie, which is finely ground as compared to Mount Hagen Organic Instant Coffee, that seems to be no less and I more than what they sell in their jar version. Still, it is a notch better than other brands. Price wise it beats Starbucks for the amount received. Having these around, plus the Vie, and the instant packages of Taster Choice Hazelnut adds variety and prevents the Starbucks to dissapeared way too soon. 4 Stars.

Product Title: BEN'S ORIGINAL Ready Rice Cheese Risotto Flavored Rice, Easy Dinner Side, 8.5 oz Pouch (Pack of 12)
Review: Great for quick recipes. Love this rice. Been purchasing it for years. Perfect for quick rice meals or serve it plain. Also makes a great shortcut fried rice. üòã

Product Title: Anthony Thomas Old Fashioned Peppermint Bark, Layered Dark & White Chocolate, Chocolate Bark (7 oz, Dark and White Chocolate)
Review: good and pepper-minty. but I think I like another's old fashioned peppermint bark. It was crumbly and most of the squares were broken, but we soldiered on and ate it.

Product Title: Tara's All Natural Handcrafted Gourmet Sea Salt Caramel: Small Batch, Kettle Cooked, Creamy & Individually Wrapped - 11.5 Ounce
Review: Maybe better at a lower price. Some are very soft and some very hard. Tastes though.

Product Title: Fazer Omar Cream Classic Finnish Toffee Sweets Candies Candy Bag 220g.
Review: In U.S. terms, this is fudge. It is very good fudge, but not elastic/chewy at all, as we expect toffee to be.

Product Title: San Francisco Bay Compostable Coffee Pods - Fog Chaser (12 Ct) K Cup Compatible including Keurig 2.0, Medium Dark Roast
Review: strong cup of coffee. I got those on sale for my husband, since he was looking for another brand besides starbucks. We got them a week ago and he already went through the first bag and really likes it. They are much stronger than the standard, so be prepared for a good strong cup of coffee. They'll get you up and running :-)

Product Title: North Bay Produce - Dried Unsweetened Cherries - Gluten Free, Vegan, No Added Sugar - Healthy Snacks for Kids and Adults - Resealable Bag, 5oz
Review: Sweet & tangy. I've been using these cherries in my yogurt, they are sweet with just a little tangy taste. A nice addition to my snack or just to eat alone.

Product Title: Monk Drops - 100% Monkfruit Liquid Sweetener, Zero Glycemic, Zero Calories, Zero Sugar, No Added Water, Concentrated Monk Fruit (350 Servings) ‚Ä¶
Review: Good product. I like this product. It has a little bit of an aftertaste I just use a little bit.

Product Title: 365 by Whole Foods Market, Organic Packaged Baby Arugula, 5 oz
Review: A Little Wilted. We ate this right away, so the freshness - or near lack thereof - was not an issue. The flavor was great, no brown or liquidy stuff in the bag. We just needed to get to it before nature did its thing. Recommend with caveat.

Product Title: Everton Toffee Butter Toffee Caramels, Original Toffee Flavor (8 oz. tin) Gourmet, Artisan Soft Toffee Caramels, Soft and Creamy Caramel Candy, Small Batch Crafted Chewy Toffee Treats
Review: Good but expensive. Delicious Carmel‚Äôs. But you only get 20Too expensive.

Product Title: Unique Pretzel Splits Extra Salt, 11 oz
Review: Liked better than the dark version. I purchased these once they came out in the store, in the dark version because I generally loved darker pretzels and chips. I was not impressed as they were TOO dark. It made them bitter rather than more flavorful. I looked for the regular version in the store but they were always sold out so when I saw them online I threw two in the cart. I liked them better than the dark ones. Warning: they are very hard . Good teeth, much care needed eating them. One of my favorite low calorie treats is a hard pretzel or two dunked in flavored seltzer (orange is good) or a diet root beer. Had nothing for dunking but did managed to out away the two bags within a week or so. They are good, just the right amount of salt and not terribly pricey. Will purchase again but make sure I have something carbonated.

Product Title: McCormick Dark Chili Powder, 20 oz
Review: Decent enough. Another standard spice item to have on ... Decent enough. Another standard spice item to have on hand. I'm not too particular in use of dark vs. normal vs. chipolte (and other flavours of the month). Gives the kick and spice I'm looking for in such.

Product Title: Newman's Own Special Blend Coffee, K-Cup Portion Pack for Keurig K-Cup Brewers (Pack of 48)
Review: One of my favorites. Coffee is essential during these times and Newman's own is one of the best for the Keurig.

Product Title: Gatorade G Zero Fruit Punch Thirst Quencher, 28 Fl Oz Bottle
Review: Good if you're trying to lose weight. Of course it doesn't taste as good as the one with sugar, but it's good.

Product Title: WonderSlim Pea Protein Snack Chips, Cool Ranch 10ct Value Pack - 130 Calories, 10g Protein, Gluten Free
Review: The taste is great and does not leave an after taste. The flavor is good, texture is more like a popcorn snack then a chip. I would like it to be more crispy, but this is a great alternative to chips.

Product Title: The Nutty Fruit House Raisin Collection (Yogurt Raisin, 2 Pound (Pack of 1))
Review: Don't order chocolate products in the Summer if you live South of Canada. After receiving two five lbs bags of DARK CHOCOLATE covered raisins, with labels which say milk chocolate covered, I have come to the conclusion that the supplier doesn't really have any milk chocolate covered raisins, and got a good deal on some mislabeled stock. Having said that, I must admit that the DARK CHOCOLATE covered raisins I received in the milk chocolate covered raisins bag were delicious and of top quality. For that reason, I give them a Four Star Rating. I understand about the heat of Summer in the South, so the fact that the bag arrived with most of the raisins floating on top of the DARK CHOCOLATE syrup in the bottom of the bag was to be expected, I suppose. The shippers attempt at preventing this by insulating the bag and including a small freezer gel pack was futile, of course, since they sat in the mail box in the sun all day. I threw them in the freezer after rolling them around in the bag a bit, and later cut them into chunks to eat. Yummy.

Product Title: Knorr Pasta Sides For Delicious Quick Pasta Side Dishes Chicken Broccoli No Artificial Flavors, No Preservatives, No Added MSG 4.2 oz
Review: Knorr side dishes. We really like Knorr side dishes.Like the flavor. Easy to cook. Good value for the money.

Product Title: Laird Superfood Non-Dairy Coffee Creamer Mocha, Shelf-Stable Superfood Non-Dairy Powder Creamer, Gluten Free, Non-GMO, Vegan, 8 oz. Bag, Pack of 1
Review: Not quite the same as powdered MCT creamer. This uses a tablespoon of product in to one cup of coffee. It blends well. I have only had to stir it with a spoon. It doesn't leave the skim that you get from MCT powdered creamer. I don't seem to get the same results from this as from the products I typically use. But, it isn't bad.

Product Title: Sailor Boy Pilot Bread Crackers, 2 lb
Review: Quite good for hard tack. A good alternative to saltines. P.s. why have saltines become so scarce?

Product Title: Dynamic Health Pomegranate Juice Concentrate, Natural Antioxidants and Polyphenols, No Additives or Preservatives, Vegan, Gluten Free, 16oz
Review: tastes great if you like the named ingredients. I take a shot of this every morning. I don't know if it helps at all with my health issues because they vary so much, but I do think it tastes great and helps calm the woozy stomach I sometimes get from my morning meds.

Product Title: PG Tips Extra Strong 80s (Pack of 3)
Review: Not extra strong. May be a tad darker in ... Not extra strong. May be a tad darker in color but not much difference in taste of flavor. I will stick to the original.

Product Title: Snackwells Vanilla Creme Sandwich Cookie, 1.7 Ounce (Pack of 12)
Review: Far from gourmet but they hit the spot. I purchased several of these to distribute to folks who need a pick me up without a lot of unhealthy additives. Too many cookies I've purchased arrived in crumbled condition, but these all arrived intact and for some strange reason, each box was shipped in its own envelope. In this time of distancing, I'm not baking for folks as I used to do but I want them to have a little something sweet that is free of human hands touching the food. Each package has four relatively small sandwich cookies that take the edge off of a hungry person and I can't tell you how quickly the boxes I purchased disappeared. They are a pick me up for the person delivering your next package, and this little kindness doesn't break the bank. I was told that these are preferred to the little packages of nuts because the saltiness brought on thirst more quickly than these cookies.

Product Title: Hint Water Peach, Pure Water Infused with Peach, Zero Sugar, Zero Calories, Zero Sweeteners, Zero Preservatives, Zero Artificial Flavors,16 Fl Oz (Pack of 12)
Review: Yuck. Not for me. I think fruit flavors are primarily sweet, which of course these are not. The scent right when you open the bottle is nice, but it only lasts seconds, and for me the flavor was just like tap water. I don't like the taste of water - except Fiji. I like that. I think I'll stick to that.

Product Title: NOW Foods, Erythritol, Great-Tasting Sugar Replacement, Zero Calories, Low Glycemic Impact, Kosher, 1-Pound (Packaging May Vary)
Review: Great product. This is a great sweetener, and works perfectly when added to Stevia.

Product Title: Wish-Bone Fat Free Chunky Blue Cheese Dressing
Review: Great tasting dressing at a fabulous price! Really great tasting dressing at an unbelievable price! Thank you, Amazon!

Product Title: Red Rose Powder, 8 Ounce or 227 Grams(Pack of 1) | Natural| No Added Preservatives | Natural Powdered Rose Petals for Face Masks, Skin & Hair Care Products
Review: Will need to use soon. Not sure what I was expecting, but there was not much lemon smell when I opened the package. The taste is what I imagined- but there was no lemon smell. I moved it into a mason jar and pressure sealed the lid on, keeping it in the dark- to preserve freshness- but feel I will need to use it up in the next few months.

Product Title: Atomic Fireballs Candy, 5 Pound Bulk Bag
Review: Not as not as they were 50 years ago. If you like fire balls buy this one because fire balls never spoil.

Product Title: Ojio Ultra Pure UNREFINED Organic Extra Virgin Coconut Oil - Cold Pressed, Gluten-Free, Keto & Paleo Friendly - Organic Pure Coconut Oil For Skin & Hair Care, Cooking, Baking and More - 16 Oz (Pack of 1)
Review: Good for your skin... This coconut oil is pretty good.. I do wish it didn't come in a glass jar...Would prefer plastic as the glass gets oily & I'm always afraid of dropping it...

Product Title: LaetaFood Butterscotch Hard Candy, Individually Wrapped Old Fashioned (Pack of 1 Pound)
Review: They do tast diffrent. I thought butterscotch candies were all the same until I started buying diffrent brand's. They do tast different from other butterscotch candies I bought In the past very tasty you can get addicted and want to not stop at just one. I'm glad they sold them in a 1lb bag I didn't want more than that great value for the money.

Product Title: Duncan Hines Mega Cookie Double Chocolate Chunk Pan Cookie Mix, 8.4 oz
Review: Yummy, very sweet! Smells incredible while baking! It was easy to put together. 2 Tbs. Ea of melted butter and water. Mix, spread in the provided pan and bake for 22 minutes. It Smells INCREDIBLE while baking. There are also directions for the microwave but the reviews frowned upon that method. Let cool a bit and you have a warm chewy YUMMY Cookie.

Product Title: In The Raw - Monk Fruit In The Raw Natural Sweetener - 40 Packet(s), 1.12 oz (32g)
Review: Not as sweet as 1:1. Pure though. A little pricey but suits my needs. It's not as sweet without the erythritol. It is mixed with a little other sweetener though. I can't have erythritol because it causes gut problems. This more expensive than the 1:1.

Product Title: Vegan, Gluten Free, Nut Free | Peppermint Choco NoNo's (3 Pack) | Dairy Free, Soy Free, Sesame Free | Allergy Friendly Snacks | No Whey Foods
Review: They taste good but they don‚Äôt look like regular M&Ms. They taste good but they don‚Äôt look like regular M&Ms. I know that it has to look a little different but I was hoping to trick my child who wants to eat M&Ms badly but is allergic to milk

Product Title: Mug Root Beer, 12 Fl Oz (pack of 12)
Review: Better but more expensive. If it weren‚Äôt for the cost, I would purchase much more frequently. I do like the taste better than others but I don‚Äôt know why.

Product Title: Traeger Grills SAU028 Sweet & Tangy Apricot BBQ Sauce
Review: Thicker would be nice. Source has a great flavor i just wish it would be thicker which would keep more on the food and less on the heat shield of my smoker.

Product Title: BEN'S ORIGINAL Ready Rice Cheese Risotto Flavored Rice, Easy Dinner Side, 8.5 oz Pouch (Pack of 12)
Review: Quick and easy. Better with help. The rice is quick and easy to heat and serve. The seasoning leaves a little to be desired, but is easy enough to doctor up. Nice to have if you're not wanting to take the time to cook, but craving rice.

Product Title: Munchkin¬Æ Milkmakers¬Æ Lactation Cookie Bites, Oatmeal Raisin, 10 Ct (Contains Fenugreek)
Review: Came in the mail fast. Tea was great and cookies were awesome. I didn‚Äôt really enjoy the bars but others might !

Product Title: Stove Top Stuffing Mix, Chicken, 12 Ounce Box
Review: Stove top stuffing. The flavor is good. Good value for the price. Easy to use.

Product Title: 365 by Whole Foods Market, Tomatoes Whole Peeled Organic, 28 Ounce
Review: Probably want to drain first. These are less expensive than the yellow label ones. They are organic. They taste good. The tomatoes are nice and firm.BUTThey are packed in juice, not puree. Which means that you probably do not want to just chuck them in the blender. They're good if you drain them or reduce the liquid while cooking, but you can't just throw them into the food processor with some peppers and cilantro and call it salsa.

Product Title: Kraft Mayonnaise FatFree (0.16oz Packets, Pack of 200)
Review: Great value! I bought Tyson chicken kits which have a mayonnaise packet. I don't trust it because it is runny and looks spoiled, so I ordered these. These taste much better and they are fat-free, which I find interesting because they don't taste like fat-free things usually do. These are thick and creamy, perfect for mixing with tuna and chicken on-the-go kits. If I'm reading it right, my expiration date is in 2014, so I have some time to use these. I ordered them for travel, but I am single and I don't like opening jars of food that I use sporadically. I feel more comfortable with these smaller portions that will keep fresh longer.

Product Title: Keto Organic Thai Style Noodles - Zero Carb, Sugar & Gluten Free Shirataki Noodle, Plant Base Vegan Diet, Made of Konjac Flour & Oat Fiber | Healthy Instant Meal Ready to Eat (200g) Pack of 6
Review: Great when you are on a keto diet. No carbs, no taste but you get something to put alfredo sauce and shrimp or whatever your choice of protein is and be able to eat like everyone else.

Product Title: Tazo Passion and Wild Sweet Orange tea bundle,40 count,1 pack
Review: Taste great but expensive. The tea tastes very good especially the wild seeet orange tea. But the price is pretty expensive comparing to other brands

Product Title: We Got Nuts Sweetened Banana Chips (4 Pounds) Sealed For Freshness - We Got Nuts
Review: This bag is better than last. I‚Äôve not eaten a lot from this bag but there‚Äôs more banana flavor!! Very excited and they‚Äôre softer also. Improvement and impressive.

Product Title: Kinnikinnick KinniTOOS Gluten Free Chocolate Sandwich Cream Cookies, 8oz/220g (Pack of 6)
Review: Soy free too! Kiddo with multiple food allergies loves these. They're not my favorite, because the texture is a little gritty (like a lot of gluten free things), but if you really really want an Oreo substitute that doesn't have soy, they're pretty great. Not overly sweet, which is nice. Expensive, because of course allergy free things are, but that's understandable. The bulk pack is a pretty good deal.

Product Title: Gold Peak Sweetened Black Tea, 6 ct, .5L Bottle
Review: Tastes good, but Pure Leaf brand has more natural ingredients. I cannot make a decent home brewed iced tea to save my life. Thus, I am forced to rely on bottled teas or the kindness of my neighbor. This Gold Peak sweet tea really is pretty good. It has a lighter flavor than the Pure Leaf and both taste more natural than the Arizona. The Gold Peak is just sweet enough without feeling like you had a cola. My one star deduction is because water is first ingredient and there are other additives. Compared to the Pure Leaf which has tea as the first of only three ingredients total. Given the choice, I'll take the Pure Leaf first and this stuff second every time.

Product Title: Multifloral Manuka Honey w/ Lemon MGO 45+ (1.1 LB)
Review: Good but not certified... Taste is good and the lemon isn't too strong as to overwhelm. Not certified as per comments posted by others though.

Product Title: Dave's Killer Bread Thin Sliced 100% Whole Wheat, 20.5 oz
Review: Good tasting and healthy. It's not easy finding healthy whole wheat loaves of bread that don't have 10-15 additives. This bread fit our needs, and the taste was great. We will purchase this brand again.

Product Title: Coconut Pacific 100% Pure Organic Extra Virgin Raw Coconut Oil, 4-Ounce Glass Jars (Pack of 4)
Review: Great product............. ....but REALLY need larger jars! These are for the person who is almost afraid to use coconut oil! :0

Product Title: Simply Asia Japanese Style Ramen Noodles, 8 oz (Pack of 6)
Review: Ok noodles. Used my own spices. I received the noodles, expecting then to include some spices. My wrong assumption. I should have paid more attention to the amazon description of the product.The quantity, met my expectations. I received exactely what they advertised, neatly packaged. It also arrived in a reasonable amount of time.The noodles are a bit harder, gummy like, and take longer to cook, in my opinion. Product Title: SPLENDA No Calorie Sweetener, Granulated Sugar Substitute, Resealable Twin Pack Bags, 25.22 Ounce (Each Pouch: 12.61 oz)
Review: Gotta pay for Brand Name when it comes to sucralose. I've been using Splenda or its generic substitute for all of my coffee and tea sweetening needs since forever. The problem is, there really is no generic / house-brand equivalent. You'd think by now manufacturers would get the chemical formula down to a science, but it's just not meant to be, I suppose. Which is why I pay extra for name brand: There is a BIG difference in taste and texture. So buying dual Splenda packs makes sense because the volume price is a little lower at retailers and Amazon. But, come on now. Is it really that expensive to manufacture chlorine, which is the base component of this artificial sweetener? (Yes; I know... It's not at all good for you, but I like my 0 calorie sweetness in my coffee and tea, and that's another issue entirely.) I don't think so, but I'm not a sucralose manufacturer.

Product Title: Hoosier Hill Farm Big Daddy Mac Mix, 1 Pound
Review: CHANGED to ADD A STAR AND WHY - OH and I put CORRECT LABEL INFO I got from the company. EDIT!: OK, I figured out how I like this best. Since the sauce thing didn't work well for me, I decided I would try STRAIGHT out of the container...but kind of sifted, dusted over the pasta. VOILA! WORKED GREAT! I like it much better. If I kind of dust/sift it a little at a time directly over my cooked pasta in the bowl and stir, no clumps, and I am not getting the really salty taste.This will be lengthy, as I want to put what the CORRECT info is, not what was on my container.It has 19 GRAMS of FAT per serving on the label on my container. THAT sounded just wrong, so contacted the company.I won't put ALL the nutritional info, just calories, total fat and sodium. And here it is, according to the company (for the UNCOLORED VERSION):Calories per TABLESPOON 25Fat per TABLESPOON 1 GRAMSodium per TABLESPOON 240 MGI don't even keep milk in the house and decided as this is powdered CHEESE, AND I like a THICK sauce, I would use it straight from the container, and just mix with a bit of water in a bowl and then add the cooked pasta DIRECTLY to the bowl.So, mixed up three tablespoons of powder with JUST enough water to make not powdery and the consistency was GREAT! NO CLUMPS.Added the cooked pasta to the bowl. VOILA.NICE THICK consistency, not lumpy, then I tasted it. I figured this MUST be really cheesy as it is basically from the container with a TOUCH of water. I know people shake directly onto popcorn (which I may have liked better).I got mostly...salty. It was edible, I don't mind a bit salty, but very little cheese flavor. I sniffed the contents in the container and not much of a cheese scent either.SO,PROS:EASY AND CONVENIENT.LOW CAL/LOW FATHEALTHIER (NO DYES, basically powdered cheese)COST EFFICIENT compared to using shredded cheeseCONS:JUST ONE, TASTE. For MAC N CHEESE, just a bit salty for me and not big cheese flavor.AGAIN, I think I might like better just SPRINKLED on things like popcorn, a baked potato.I will finish the container, but won't reorder.I WANTED TO LOVE THIS, but the salt is a bit overwhelming and the cheese taste underwhelming. .

Product Title: Season Skinless & Boneless Sardines in Oil, 4.37 Ounce (Pack of 6), Packaging May Vary
Review: Moroccan Fish Caught in the Wild Have Mild Flavor. I've been on a sardine kick lately. My favorite so far are the King Oscar Brisling Sardines in Olive Oil because they taste fishy and are small. The Season skinless and boneless sardines in olive oil taste less like the stereotypical sardine and more like a kipper. There are about 3 sardines, or at least 3 large pieces of fish in the cans, each has quite a bit of the darker flesh, but there is absolutely no skin and no bone. Although they have salt added, they are not salty to the taste compared to other sardines. Sometimes when a can of sardines is opened, the fish is sort of soft and mushy, but in these that is not the case. I've drained the cans, had them with onions and hot mustard in a sandwich or simply put them on a salad, again with onions. The next can will be cooked with onions and scrambled eggs, like what my mother did with kippers. The cans are structurally sound and have a very light lid that is easy to remove with a lightweight tab. No sharp edges or metal taste seeping into the fish.

Product Title: Drogheria & Alimentari Extra Fine Himalayan Pink Salt, 43.74 oz

Product Title: Tara's All Natural Handcrafted Gourmet Sea Salt Caramel: Small Batch, Kettle Cooked, Creamy & Individually Wrapped - 11.5 Ounce
Review: Tasty, But Not My Go-To Caramels . . . I'm addicted to soft caramels, so obviously, I have a go-to brand. One day, when that brand was out of stock, I had no choice but to search for a decent replacement. I always check the reviews before purchasing an item, and that's when I discovered Tara‚Äôs caramels. Tara‚Äôs had surprisingly high and positive ratings. The only thing that held me back from immediately ordering the caramels was the steep price tag. However, I was craving soft caramels, so finally, I took the plunge and submitted my order.The caramels came wrapped in an almost butcher-like paper, which made it easy to unwrap the caramels without the frustration of the caramel sticking to its wrapping paper. The caramels were very soft, just the way I like them. Also, I was pleasantly surprised by the quantity that came in the container. In regards to the taste, it was a bit different than the original tasting caramels I'm used to having. The hint of sea salt was a nice contrast from what I usually pig üê∑ out on. However, if I'm being straightforward, the taste of Tara‚Äôs caramels couldn't beat how costly they are. The brand I usually have is nowhere near the price of Tara‚Äôs caramels. Maybe that's why I believe Tara‚Äôs caramels, while tasty, are not worth the cost. To be completely honest, I would indulge in Tara‚Äôs caramels if offered some. I just wouldn't pay for these caramels out of my pocket. On the other hand, if I were offered a free lifetime of caramels, with any brand of my choosing, without a doubt, I would pick my usual go-to brand Werther‚Äôs Soft Caramels over all other brands.

Product Title: Bob's Red Mill - Resealable Organic Golden Flaxseed Meal, 16 Oz (4 Pack)

Review: Pouring means unnecessary waste - keep those Agave bottles handy! Great product, but container is too stiff to use. The best way i have found so far is to transfer it to an Agave squeeze bottle with a regulator cap and pour it from there - no more waste or mess!

Product Title: Horizon Organic, Colby Cheese Sticks, 6 oz

Product Title: Lemonhead Hard Lemon Candy, Individually Wrapped, 150 Count Tub
Review: A go to in our house. I bought these for my nausea, ginger isn‚Äôt my thing and someone recommended trying lemon, and it turns out it worked. They are also pretty good as just a regular candy, my husband loves them.

Product Title: Tabasco Sauce Keychain - Includes Mini Bottle of Original Hot Sauce. Miniature Individual Size Perfect for Travel, Key Chain or Purse. Refillable and Strong.
Review: This is really good. I really like these, and have already bought more. Highly recommended for those of you that can't get through the day without your tabasco sauce.

Product Title: Waka Quality Instant Coffee ‚Äî Dark Roast ‚Äî Ethiopian 100% Arabica Freeze Dried Beans ‚Äî 3.5 oz Bulk Bag
Review: Good, but expensive. I generally drink only brewed coffee, but wanted a super quick way to make a single cup once in a while. I've usually found instant coffee to have a disappointing taste, but thought I'd try a better quality instant. And Waka is better than most instants.If I was traveling, I'd like the single packets, but since I'm using this at home, I feel the packets are wasteful... and they are a little annoying to open at times. I also dislike packets if I want to adjust the strength of the coffee. And this is a bit expensive at $1.50/packet.All in all, this coffee did not disappoint in flavor, but I probably won't get it again, unless I plan to travel.

Product Title: Pure Horseradish - 16oz Jar - Homestyle
Review: Great. I don't have the roots in my garden. This is the next best thing.Able to make horseradish SAUCE any strength for different dishes we eat.

Product Title: S&B Layu Chili Oil, 1.11-Ounce (Pack of 10)
Review: Small bottle, tons of flavor. This is essential for spicy Asian foods.

Product Title: Amazon Brand - Happy Belly Peanut Butter Plenty Trail Mix, 16 Ounce (Pack of 2)
Review: Not the product's fault. Just a friendly reminder that chocolate, or anything that melts should not be ordered until the fall. Amazon doesn't provide air conditioned delivery trucks. Everything turns liquid in the southern heat. It's not from being left on the porch. I retrieved the items within a couple of minutes upon delivery. On the up side, instead of the yogurt chips the trail mix is now covered in the chocolate type goodness. Just pop them in the fridge or freezer and they won't be stuck to the package. I'll be giving the product good reviews, but Amazon gets a thumbs down for being cheap.

Product Title: Stash Tea Double Spice Chai Black Tea, Box of 100 Tea Bags (Packaging May Vary)
Review: Individually Wrapped. This is great tea - I have tried other brands but always end up with Stash. Wish it was available with less packaging but I understand why not.

Product Title: Shelton's Turkey Jerky, Hot & Spicy, 0.5-Ounce Bags (Pack of 12)
Review: My father would have loved these :-). Dry, tough & salty..and already in great travel size snack packs! Love that it‚Äôs made with tamari soy sauce since I have gluten issues. But the price is just ridiculous so I usually just make my own yummy jerky & save these for travel emergencies!

Product Title: Wilton Cookie 9oz Icing, White
Review: Very sweet and hardens so it doesn't stick to other cookies.. This flavor is very sweet and smooth. Goes on a little runny so take your time. It does harden like it's supposed to. Some others say they do but they don't and stick to each other. Once this hardens it doesn't stick.

Product Title: Light Grey Celtic Sea Salt 1 Pound Resealable Bag ‚Äì Additive-Free, Delicious Sea Salt, Perfect for Cooking, Baking and More - Gluten-Free, Non-GMO Verified, Kosher and Paleo-Friendly
Review: LOVE the taste of this. This is SO delicious. It has a texture similar to kosher salt but a more complex flavor and a less pickling/puckering effect.The one thing I would suggest is letting it air dry a bit before you put it in a grinder. Otherwise, the damp salt will not grind up and shake out right.

Product Title: Four Lou Malnati's Deep Dish Pizzas (2 Cheese 2 Pepperoni)
Review: Awesome pizza is awesome. Amazing pizza! Sauce was excellent. Mozzarella, pepperoni, sausage all tasted high quality and the crust was perfectly done. This is the best chicago-style pizza I've ever had! MY only gripe is the cost. $90 for 4 little pies is a bit pricey imo.

Product Title: SPANGLER CANDY Candy Cane Red White Peppermint, 5.3 OZ
Review: Spangler Candy Canes. Spangler always makes the prettiest canes... Guilty pleasure. Good news: they are using vegetable dye for color. Now, if we could get them to just use cane sugar and remove the corn syrup - I'd be in the 5 star opinion! They are delicious - but I love peppermint. They are individually wrapped so perfect for tree decor or stocking adds. Or.. .just to eat - I put in a glass vase and help myself! Please just use the cane sugar - no corn syrup!

Product Title: Nature Valley Crunchy Granola Bars Oats 'N Honey, 98-Count 1.49oz bars
Review: Review update #2: Package never arrived. Great deal on my favorite brand and flavor of granola bar. Will buy again in the future.2nd order never arrived tho it was labeled as "delivered", so I had to contact the seller for a refund. Apparently my package was damaged in transit.

Product Title: Torani Syrup, Red Raspberry, 25.4 Ounces (Pack of 4)
Review: Delicious and sugar free! Great for coffee, ice cream, desserts, and more. First off, this Torani Syrup has 0 calories, 0 sugar and 0 carbs and is obviously Keto friendly. This is a delicious way to sweeten or flavor up your coffee or favorite foods. Great for coffee, ice cream, desserts, and more. Be creative. I like to add some flavor to my morning coffee every once in a while. Size of this bottle is 750 ml or about 25.4 ounces. Personally, I invested in the "pumps" for these bottles.For a great diet Starbucks style Chocolate Flavoured Coffee knockoff, try my following recipe:8 oz brewed HOT or Cold unsweetened iced coffee 10 cal.2 Cap-fulls or one "pump" of Torani Sugar Free Chocolate Syrup, ( or as desired ) 0 cal.2 oz low fat milk ( or as much as you desire ) 25 cal6 oz ice cubes or just use Hot coffee 0 calReddi-wip Fat Free Whipped Dairy Cream Topping (Keto Friendly) 5 cal.Drizzle some Fat free or Sugar free Chocolate syrup on top of cream 5 cal.Total for this sugar free coffee: only 45 caloriesOr, you can use regular ingredients if you are not watching calories or sugar. If you like this review or recipe, please click helpful below.Enjoy!

Product Title: Tealyra - Milady Grey - Delightful Black Loose Leaf Tea - Rose Petals and Lemongrass with Orange - Medium Caffeine - Blend - All Natural - 110g (4-ounce)
Review: Not to bad Lady Grey. Good tea. Tea did have a slightly dusty taste toward the end of the bag. Not terrible, just enough to notice.

Product Title: Campbell‚Äôs Chunky Soup, Sirloin Burger With Country Vegetable Beef Soup, 15.25 Oz Microwavable Bowl (Case of 8)

Product Title: Sunbursts Chocolate Covered Sunflower Seeds 1LB Bag

Product Title: Brew Your Bucha Kombucha Tea SCOBY with Starter Fluid - Kombucha Starter Kit with Scoby, Live Culture, Scoby Kombucha Starter, Kombucha Kit, DIY Kombucha Brewing Kit, Scoby Kombucha Starter (1 Scoby)
Review: Be patient, liitle sluggish to begin with. The first batch of Kombucha made with this Scoby took quite a lot longer to brew than has been my experience. Product Title: Juicy Juice Orange Tangerine, 4.23 Ounce Boxes, 8 Count (Pack of 5)
Review: Cheaper in the store, but great size. These are the perfect carb count for my type 1 diabetic. But a little pricier than they are in the store.

Product Title: ORGAIN Organic Strawberries and Cream Nutri Shake 4 Pack, 11 FZ
Review: smooth light vanilla taste, leans a bit sweet for my preference/Cafe Mocha good too! Orgain Organic Nutritional Shake, Vanilla Bean - Meal Replacement is pretty good. It is a tad more sweet than I like, and I would prefer more fiber. Usually I make a smoothie using a meal replacement powder, but I wanted some convenient ready to drink option available for on the go, or when I just dont feel like getting the blender out. I also use this as creamer in my coffee.I see there that there are many reviews stating theirs were chunky. I have had a few now, and haven't had any issues thankfully. I poured one into a glass and took a picture so I can show you how smooth my supply is. Purchased June 2021 with best by date of May 2022-------------------Edit to add: I like Orgain shakes enough that I have purchased the vanilla few more times, and I recently purchased the Cafe Mocha. I came here to review the cafe mocha, and my old vanilla review came up. They must be on same page. While I prefer the vanilla for its versatility (drink straight, add to smoothies, use as coffee creamer), I like this Cafe Mocha a lot too. Has a light easy to drink flavor. I have added to coffee, or I have added some instant coffee to this and then poured into a cup with ice. All good.

Product Title: Mestemacher Protein Bread,Carrot , 9 Count
Review: trusty stand by for very healthy shelf stable bread, high protein is a little off tasting. I have been a consumer of these German breads on and off since childhood. Definitely an acquired taste, or should I say texture. These shelf stable breads are dense, moist, and are best (to me) simply toasted and buttered (or dairy, non dairy, nut butters, etc). I like it for smashed avocado toast, but not so much as a regular sandwich bread. Does better as an open face sandwich bread. Once the package is opened, it is best if it is stored in fridge and used up soon.As for this particular variety-- carrot, it has a nearly neutral carrot taste; hint of carrot. There is another flavor that comes through that is not bad, but makes me less likely to buy it again. I think it is the fact that this is one of their high protein varieties. I normally just go with the regular stuff, and this is my first time trying the high protein kind. I love all the ingredients, but there is a pronounced protein taste. I will definitely use these packages up, then next time I will simply choose one of my usual varieties. Very healthy bread that has been around forever.

Product Title: OliveNation Premium Coconut Extract - 4 Ounces
Review: Strong alcohol notes. The coconut flavor was good but I thought the strength of the alcohol used to make it was perhaps a bit Diesel

Product Title: Nathan's Famous Jumbo Crinkle Cut French Fries, 28 oz (Frozen)
Review: Use the right oil. Maybe I didn't use the right oil to fry the fries in.I decided to use my Air Fryer...much better

Product Title: Fontina Val d'Aosta Cheese (1 lb)
Review: Very strong cheese. I've ordered three of these and use for potato, broccoli and cauliflower casseroles. It's very strong cheese (similar to Limburger) so combine with other cheese to mellow a bit.My problem is more the Post Office delivery issue. We get our mail late in the day and the box rides in the heat for at least six hours before being delivered. Not only was the ice melted, the cheese had started to melt too. It's not a food safety issue as cheese can stay unrefrigerated for five days. Will order again as this makes great tasting veggie casseroles.

Product Title: Al Ameed Gourmet Turkish Ground Coffee Medium Roast With Cardamom, 100% Authentic Arabica, Fresh & Finely Ground, 8oz (Pack of 6)
Review: dark roast is strongly doused w/ cardamom-- loses coffee flavor. Must love cardamom. I can give it 5 stars for quality, but in the taste category (and overall rating) I am giving it 4 stars. I know this is a preference thing, rather than a quality thing. So if you really like cardamom then go for it. I like cardamom, but this is rather strong. I taste that more than the coffee itself. If I could at least still taste the dark coffee, then I would like this a lot more. If you like strong cardamom then you will be pleased with this. If you want to try this anyway, know that the quality is quite good. I plan to add in some supplemental dark roast without cardamom to see if I can get a more balanced flavor. I never add cream or sugar to my coffee, and I find I need both to mellow out the cardamom.I love a good cup of Turkish coffee. I have learned to look for dark roast, as many of the offerings available tend to default to a light, very green tasting roast. Anytime I have had it in an restaurant, it has always been dark roast, which is my preference for coffee anyway. The darker the better. Black. No sugar. No cream.This small bag (in a box) of coffee is powdery as expected. Dark and rich smelling. I have the "with cardamom" option. Like I said.. the flavor is robust. I think I may cut in some fine ground dark coffee, or see if they offer a dark roast without it. I like it enough to finish it, but likely wont buy it again. Yet, I like the quality of the brand enough to want a non cardamom option.I prepare it as it should. I use an Ibrik over a gas burner. I am not good at making it. My foaming skill is not as good as I want, but the coffee at least tastes pretty good. I love strong, bold flavor of Turkish coffee. I never water it down.I really like that this company has so many offerings-- dark, medium, light roasts, some with cardamom, some without. I think I will try the French Roast so long as it doesnt have cardamom (or at least less of it). Otherwise will try another brand.

Product Title: Light Brown Baking Sugar - 2 LB Bag (32 oz)
Review: What‚Äôs do dislike about light brown sugar? Just right for baking... this is packaged will. It was nice and soft upon arrival; easy to use!

Product Title: Ghee, 95% organic, Clarified Butter, 13 oz pack of 4
Review: The best ghee you pay a lot for. This is the best of the several ghees I have tried over the years, hands down. Great taste, great texture. However, as it became more popular (perhaps because of paleo thing) it has gotten pricey and limited availability. This was available and also seemed to be the best price per ounce.My only other gripe with the product besides price/availability is the packaging. While it is admirable that it comes in a glass container without a BPA liner and has a plastic overwrap, in shipping it is not quite adequate to prevent leaking. Two of mine arrived leaking, one barely and the other more severely. The lids just weren't screwed down all the way tight or had come looser on shipping. The plastic overwrap cannot contain the liquid ghee becomes when subjected to the merciless heat we have been experiencing these weeks so I had some slippery heavy glass jars to deal with. Cleaned them up, ghee is fine. From the looks of it they may have spent some time upside down too, which again, in this heat, ghee is a liquid so you are going to have spillage in this kind of container.If they would find a way to make an inner seal without BPA that would be great. Or maybe they can tape down the lid to not loosen up. They also need to ramp up production/distribution. This is not kobe beef but is getting as expensive.

Product Title: Gogo SqueeZ Applesauce, AppleStrawberry (4 Count, 3.2 Oz Each)
Review: a gift for a friends pantry. I have a friend who is a live-in grandma of a military family. They are trying to feed a family of 5. I sent this and several other things via "Prime Pantry" and my friend reports it arrived quickly and in good condition. Thank you Amazon for making it easier to help my friend.These are AWESOME handy... and for a treat, sometimes I freeze them. It's just apples and whatever other fruit is added. No added sugar or dyes.

Product Title: Armour Star Classic Homestyle Beef Stew, 20 oz. (Pack of 12)
Review: comfort food paired w/buttered toast, emergency food, versatile uses, between broth&gravy. The product pictures are pure BS, but anyone expecting anything coming out of a can shouldnt be gullible enough to think that is what this looks like.I dont hate it, but I dont love it. Like it enough to keep stacking it. It's got it's purpose, especially these days and upcoming. It isn't bad, and I stack these on my shelf for a variety reasons. Now, anyone expecting a quality beef stew on par with homemade will severely disappointed. This is more like a chunky soup. I can say that is has lots of good sized bits of potato and carrot slices. The background flavor is indeed beef, and I dont find it weird tasting. The beef pieces are spongy, reminiscent of canned ground beef rather than chunks of roast. They list "beef", and so whatever that is, it is soft and spongy, and there is plenty of it. The liquid is thicker than a broth but not as thick as a gravy. Add a little flour to thicken it up if need be.Loaded with sodium like most canned goods. Be careful, one can is ridiculously considered "2 servings". that will overblow your sodium content for the day.Overall... for what I buy it for.. I am pleased. I dont eat this stuff often. It really isnt my go to. But I do have a robust pantry, and I keep stuff like this on hand for quick desperate meals, for using as a sort of flavor base (keep as is, or blend), for adding over rice, pasta, etc. Make up a bunch of buttered toast and dip it in this? Mmmm yes. Quick, easy comfort food. Got someone who cant chew real well? This stuff can be gummed. Or can be blended to make for a beefy smoothie (gross sounding, but people have issues that may benefit from this knowledge).The price on this stuff has gone up a lot. Inflation, and food shortage combined. If you can get it for less than $3 per can (04/2022) then it is still holding at older pricing (I think $2.85 at DollarGeneral). If you are looking to stack your pantry, this is worthwhile to have. Gives some variety, convenience. Need a can opener. I know reviews are totally unfavorable, but this brand is reasonably (so far) priced, and has the most natural taste. I dont cringe eating it- no off taste, or after taste. Maybe grab a can from the store before committing to a case, or jump on getting the case and keeping it for emergency (or give away).Know what you are getting this for, understand the limitations of taste and texture, and then proceed if you so desire. 4 stars from me. Not because it is necessarily better than others (in some cases yes), but because it fills a need, meets expectations (I set them low, haha), and the taste isnt too shabby. Also, my cans are all good. No dents. And, I bought another case.

Product Title: Marshmallows Sugar/Gluten Free Sugar Free Marshmellow 2.7 OZ
Review: It was bairly OK, could use more of a flavor. So - so for me, it was just OK. I eat and drink a lot of diet things and this one just doesn't have much flavor. It's worth trying to see if you like it, but for the price and taste it was a one time shot.

Product Title: Hormel Premium Real Crumbled Bacon, 4.3-Ounce Pouches (Pack of 6)
Review: previous version was very good - will try this one. howdy y'all,*****update 2011-01-06, Thursdaythe stuff i got is the item i refer to in the review as the OLD version. apparently the data shown by amazon is actually the out-of-date info and the newer info is what i called OLD. [*grin*]very good & well worth a FOUR.*****i rate this [based on the previous version] a FOUR.the previous version ["You purchased this item on July 6, 2010"] of this was really quite good. this stuff is lovely on sandwiches, scrambled eggs, baked potatoes, mac-n-cheese and most anything that you like with bacon on it. that's most anything for me. [*grin*]i came here to buy some more and now i'm hesitating. why? cuz ...old - no mention of "picnic bacon" on labelnew - "with picnic bacon"what is picnic bacon? from google = "Picnic bacon is from the picnic cut, which includes the shoulder beneath the blade. It is fairly lean, but tougher than most pork cuts."old - no mention of smoke flavoringnew - "smoke flavoring added"often, to me, smoke flavoring tastes sweetish. i don't care for sweet bacon.old - "50% less fat than USDA data for pan-fried bacon"new - "30% less fat than USDA data for pan-fried bacon"more fat? does that mean more flavor or more of the [very rare in the old package] lumps of pure fat that are so ... revolting when bitten into?old - "Fat content has been lowered from 3 g to 1.5 g per serving"new - "Fat content has been lowered from 3 g to 2 g per serving"more fat in another measurement. again, what does it mean to the flavor?they are still both "one tablespoon = one slice fully cooked bacon". plus, they are still the same 4.3 ounces per package.i'm gonna buy the stuff but it worries me when SO MANY changes show up. [*sigh ...*]take care,lee

It is interesting to see what flavor combination they have come up with lately. I really loved the raspberry lemonade and tried the tangerine mango. Those are my two favorites.Then I wondered what the grape would taste like. To be honest it tastes great after sitting for about 10 minutes after you mix it all up. I don't know why it tastes so different right after you mix it. It is like the flavors are enhanced if you let it sit a bit. I don't think this tastes exactly like grape juice, it is not that sweet! It is more like you diluted strong grape juice and added a bit of stevia.I would vote for stronger flavors in all their pure drinks to be honest. But if not, I'm happy with them for now. They make water easier to drink and I think that is the point. To keep hydrated!~The Rebecca ReviewP.S. I tried the package with less water and the grape flavor is much stronger. So like drink 1/4 cup of the water in a regular 16.9 ounce water bottle so there is less water to flavor. Much better!!!!

Product Title: Beef Ribeye Steak Boneless Step 1
Review: UPDATE: my 2nd order not so...Excellent - one of the best I have ever had. UPDATE: ordered for a second time. See original review below. This time was not so wonderful just took off a star. After my first five star experience I figured the only was to go from there was probably down. But still not too far. As with my first order I asked for a pound. Since the first one was almost TOO think I figured I would slice thickness and get two steaks out of it and have one suitable for a steak n eggs breakfast. This steak was thinner. Not as marbled and gorgeous as the first. I did debate whether to halve it (I probably shouldn't have but did anyway because I am stupid like that) Got well two thin steaks. Froze one, cooked the other. I figured a quick sear even on cast iron and it should be a perfect medium. Eh, I messed up was more a medium well but it definitely didn't have the marbling or flavor (fat is flavor!) of that first purchase. A few days later and I decide to pull out the frozen half and try steak and eggs. I normally don't cook from frozen but since this was thin I did hoping it would save interior. My, that baby while a perfect sear also ended up well done (UGH). However, regardless of temp I can say my second serve of second order did not have the marbling or flavor of that first ordered single. Still on the fence as to what "meat" I will order for xmas. Maybe will go off to the brick n mortar butcher even and pick something out. Still kicking myself for not taking the first steak and saving it for the holiday in the freezer. I still dream about. Beautiful. These two, your average supermarket steak.What can I say? I am old and this has to rank as one of the best I have ever had whether prepared myself or at a steak house. For a steak that is choice grade, this was truly a great value even at what many would consider a high price point. I have seen ribeyes at the supermarket going for more than this per pound. Was it on sale maybe?I had this instead of turkey for Thanksgiving. Actually I made it today on Black Friday as I just wasn't feeling like an indulgent meal yesterday. Did not disappoint. Unwrapped and sprinkled with seasalt on both sides while it got the chill off and dropped it into my biggest cast iron skillet I had preheated. Initially considered slicing it in half thinner as I was concerned if I could get a nice medium (no more no less for me) on the stove top but kept it as it was. Perfect. Made some au jus with the drippings and a spoonful of dark soy sauce. Didn't even need the A1 I had already poured onto a warm plate.I wouldn't hesitate to buy again. Especially at that price. Meat is always a gamble, even when I pick it out myself in person you never really know until you prepare and eat it. Looking forward to it I think I will get it again for Christmas but just get a ham slice in case this was a one-off.At least give it a try. Never would have guessed it is probably only Choice grade, so tender.

Review: Strands and grainy texture - Zip bag doesn't close. 1st off, it's a great value for the ginger. It has a strong kick to it.
