Product Title: Rani Sabudana (Tapioca / Sago) Pearls 64oz (4lbs) 1.81kg Bulk ~ All Natural | Vegan | No Colors | NON-GMO | Indian Origin
Review: Works well in savory, traditional, sabudana dishes. I became interested in trying out a recipe for sabudana khichdi a while back, and I purchased this brand of sabudana (AKA tapioca pearls) for that purpose. I also separately purchased curry leaves here on Amazon for that reason as well. I had never tried that particular herb, but it seems to be a main component of traditional Asian, savory, sabudana recipes.Note that tapioca has very little healthy, nutritional value in and of itself, so I would not categorize it as a ‚Äúhealth food.‚Äù Sabudana has zero fat, which in itself won‚Äôt be considered a negative by many people. But, unfortunately, it contains no fiber and no protein, because it entirely consists of starch. I addition, apparently it is quite common, in the process of manufacturing tapioca pearls, no matter who is doing it, that chemical additives are used, particularly during the process of manufacturing tapioca flour from the cassava plant (the pearls are created from tapioca starch). These chemicals typically include:--Sulfuric acid as a bleaching agent. This highly corrosive chemical is actually a common food additive in its ‚Äúfood grade‚Äù formulation. It is commonly used in the production of cheese, in the refinement of sugar, in the treatment of drinking water, in the production of whey protein powders, and in the production of many kinds of modified food starch, including tapioca starch.--Aluminum sulfate for increasing the viscosity of tapioca starch/flour. The primary health concern with all forms of aluminum is long-term exposure to low levels of this chemical, which can cause damage to the nervous system. In addition, aluminum from natural sources may contain traces of toxic metals such as chromium.--Sulfur dioxide for percolating out the tapioca starch, as a bleaching agent and antimicrobial. Sulfur dioxide is a sulfite, a preservative that some people are dangerously allergic.--Chlorine as a bleaching agent and antimicrobial. All public drinking water in the USA contains chlorine.In spite of these issues, I may, occasionally, continue to enjoy sabudana as an intriguing, ethnic addition to my vegan diet. I really liked the chewy texture, and when well spiced, sabudana is quite tasty.Pros of this particular product: The sabudana seems fresh, and it worked well in the dish I made with it, which turned out great. The seller, Rani's World Foods, is located in Texas. It is a family-owned company that has been in business over 40 years. It is listed with the Better Business Bureau. It has no complaints against it, though it has no rating.Cons of this product: The seller offers no nutritional information nor any cooking instructions on the package. I have provided information on both below for any customer who might be interested.Nutritional information for 1 cup uncooked sabudana:Calories: 544Fat: 0Carbs: 135 gmFiber: 1 gmProtein: 0SABUDANA KHICHDI RECIPEYield: 5-3/4 cupsCalories: 196 per 1-cup servingIngredients1 cup uncooked sabudana AKA tapioca pearls1/2 cup raw, skinned peanuts, lightly roasted, ground to coarse powder2 medium (2-1/4 cups) potatoes, peeled and diced into small cubes1 cup chopped green onions1 cup frozen spinach1/2 cup unsweetened coconut flakes1-1/2 inch fresh, peeled ginger root2 tablespoons ground curry leaves (I ground them in my spice grinder)1 tablespoon ground, mild chili pepper (I ground them in my spice grinder)1 tablespoon cumin powder1 teaspoon coriander powder1/4 teaspoon stevia (OR 1 teaspoon sugar)1/2 teaspoon black pepper1/2 teaspoon salt1 tablespoon lemon juice (OR 1 tablespoon lime juice)1 tablespoon coconut oilInstructions1. Rinse the sabudana pearls multiple times in a colander under running water.2. Place the sabudana in a container with 2-1/2 cups of purified water. Stir in 1 teaspoon curry leaves and soak the pearls a minimum of 5 hours, but ideally overnight, in order for them to absorb enough water to soften adequately. You will know they are sufficiently soft when several different pearls crush easily between your thumb and pointer finger when you press on them.3. After it has sufficiently soaked, drain the sabudana and set it aside.4. Peel and dice the potatoes. Boil them with 2 cups of purified water for about 5-7 minutes until soft. Drain and set aside.5. If you are using raw, red-skinned peanuts, roast the peanuts lightly (400 degrees in a toaster oven for 4 minutes), remove the skin, and grind them to a coarse powder in a food processor, coffee grinder, or with a mortar and pestle. Pour the peanut powder on top of the sabudana and mix well, such that every pearl is coated. This helps keep the sabudana pearls from clumping together.6. Place in a food processor or blender all of the remaining ingredients except the coconut oil. Grind them to the consistency of a coarse, moist, green powder. Pour it on top of the potatoes, and blend completely.7. Pour the sabudana and peanut powder mixture on top of the vegetable mixture and blend well.8. Place the coconut oil in a large skillet or wok. Melt it on medium heat and spread it throughout the bottom of the pan. Place the sabudana mixture into the pan and cook it on medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent its sticking to the bottom of the pan, until the mixture is thoroughly hot. Serve immediately.NOTESYou can prepare this mixture ahead of time on the same day you plan to serve it, setting it aside in a covered container, either at room temperature or in the refrigerator. You can then follow Step 8 when you are ready to serve it. It is not recommended to serve this food as leftovers, because it can congeal and get rather gluey. Therefore, if 5-3/4 cups is too much food for your needs for one meal, you might want to cut down the proportions to suit your requirements.I checked out about 15-20 traditional sabudana recipes and ended up creating my own modified recipe. My personal objections to traditional recipes are twofold: not enough flavorful spices and not enough vegetables. I also made a decision to grind up the vegetables I use in my recipe in order to provide a more complete job of coating the sabudana to prevent the pearls from clumping together. Traditional recipes rely solely on the powder from coarse-ground, roasted peanuts to achieve that purpose, but I did not think that this would be adequate enough for my particular preference. I also decided to pre-soak the sabudana pearls with some curry leaves, in order to create a kind of water-based marinade. This experiment definitely worked to boost the absorption of flavor on the part of the tapioca pearls which, in and of themselves, are a tasteless starch. Soaking with curry leaves did not, for me, preempt using more of them in the ultimate flavoring of the dish, because the soaking curry leaves are removed when the water is drained off.Photos left to right: Sabudana prior to soaking, sabudana after soaking overnight, sabudana drained, sabudana about to be stirred into vegetable mixture, completed sabudana khichdi.

Product Title: Tasty Brand Organic Fruit Snacks, Mixed Fruit Flavors, 0.8-Ounce Pouches, 24-Count
Review: Tastes great, very expensive, a couple of questionable ingredients. I recently discovered gummy vitamins, and they tasted so good, it made me crave gummy candy, something I had previously never been drawn to, even as a child. I decided if I was going to indulge in candy, I should try to get the least unhealthy brand I could find, which led me to these particular gummies. Since I made a big commitment buying a box with 24 packets of them, I was delighted to discover that they taste great. The texture is terrific, too, not at all hard, but pleasantly soft and chewy.The biggest drawback of this brand is the cost. At the price I paid here on Amazon, these gummies cost about 7 cents each. They are sold in tiny, individual packets with 11 pieces of candy in each, weighing per packet .8 ounce (23 grams). The label on each packet proudly proclaims the candy inside comes to "only" 70 calories, but that's a lot of calories for such a small amount of candy. A single tiny gummy has 7 calories.In short, every bite of these tasty gummies is expensive in both calories and cost.Below is a list of ingredients. There are only two that are somewhat problematic, carnauba wax and natural flavors. I have provided information on them. The rest of the ingredients are as acceptable as junk-food ingredients can be. Nothing can counteract the fact that all sweeteners, even natural ones, can have adverse effects on blood sugar, and sticky candy is particularly hard on the teeth because it clings tenaciously to the enamel.Note to vegans: Though these gummies use pectin instead of non-vegan gelatin, unfortunately, the vegan status of the sugar content is a big unknown because it is hard to tell how much processing has been done to the "organic cane sugar" listed in the ingredients. That confusingly generic term offers no clue if it was bleached, which often involves the use of non-vegan bone char rather than the vegan-friendly methods of granular carbon or an ion-exchange system.Ingredients: Organic tapioca syrup, organic cane sugar, organic tapioca syrup solids, organic white grape juice concentrate, pectin, citric acid, ascorbic acid, color added (black carrot juice concentrate, turmeric, annatto), natural flavors, sodium citrate, organic sunflower oil, carnauba wax.Carnauba Wax AKA Brazil Wax and Palm Wax. This wax is harvested from the leaves of the Copernicia prunifera, a palm plant that grows only in northeastern Brazil. The trees grow up to 50 feet tall. Their leaves are individually removed by hand, a maximum of 20 leaves per tree, per year, to avoid harming the tree. The leaves are dried in the sun, then beaten to loosen and remove their wax. Carnauba wax has many industrial uses, but its main one is to produce a glossy finish, whether on candy, cars, shoes, dental floss or floors. Because it is hypoallergenic and has emollient properties as well shine, it is frequently used in cosmetics. It is also used for pharmaceutical medications to coat tablets in order to make them easier to swallow. Carnauba wax is regularly used in a range of food products, for example: sauces, chewing gum, candy corn, jelly beans, and gummy candy. As of 2001, the EU accepted usage of carnauba wax in food products up to a maximum level of 200 mg/kg of food and an estimated safe consumption level per individual of up to 8 mg/day. It is impossible to know how much carnauba wax is contained in a serving of this product.Natural Flavor: The definition of natural flavor under the Code of Federal Regulations is: "The essential oil, oleoresin, essence or extractive, protein hydrolysate, distillate, or any product of roasting, heating or enzymolysis, which contains the flavoring constituents derived from a spice, fruit or fruit juice, vegetable or vegetable juice, edible yeast, herb, bark, bud, root, leaf or similar plant material, meat, seafood, poultry, eggs, dairy products, or fermentation products thereof, whose significant function in food is flavoring rather than nutritional" (21CFR101.22). That essentially means that natural flavor is derived from a real food, but the process by which it is derived is unexplained and there is no way to know how safe or healthy a natural flavoring is.Sodium Citrate: This is used in food products as an emulsifier and refers to any one of the three sodium salts of citric acid, and most commonly the third one: monosodium citrate, disodium citrate, and trisodium citrate. Sodium citrate is metabolized to sodium bicarbonate (baking soda), thus acting as a systemic alkalizer.

Product Title: Taylors of Harrogate, Ntingwe Kwazulu Tea, Loose Leaf, 4.4 Ounce Box
Review: An upbeat breakfast tea that offers a different note. The Ntingwe Kwazulu is without a doubt a breakfast tea. It would not be an all day drinking tea in the sense of having it straight. Definitely has the darker color of a breakfast tea. The taste on the other hand is upbeat compared to other breakfast teas. It doesn't have that same bitterness in the background. Bit on the light side to be there much even for a more concentrated brew.It's more fine than a CTC since there isn't much of a curl. They almost look uniform in cut and a coffee filter would be suggested for this. Not quite the bitterness as the Assam, Ceylon and combination of the two if someone is looking for an alternative to the coffee and cream to start the day.If the idea is to have an alternative to an espresso or Turkish coffee in terms of that heavier taste, I suggest the Assam, Ceylon or combo. This one would be more of an alternative to that brand everyone is familiar seeing at every other street corner or in a mall. Much of the coffee that brand has are from Africa so this would be similar in the lightness or upbeat characteristic.I would say that not every Assam and Ceylon are going to be the same. T of H Assam is weak. Assam is known for the maltiness when you add the milk. Ceylon lends more of the bitterness. To have a good combo of the two that makes a good coffee and cream alternative is the royal blend by F&M. I like the royal blend and this one for a breakfast tea. Main difference is that the royal blend is more addictive for me. This one is good in a different way.For those who enjoy a good breakfast tea, I would recommend this. It does have a twist to it that isn't present in most breakfast teas. It has a tenor note to it at the end. The taste starts off as breakfast and then finishes at the end with a light jump. Many breakfast teas end with a fall vs. a jump. Not fall in a bad way. More of the note being heavier, bitter, characteristics of coffee and a bass note.Taste wise, it's good. In a way, refreshing for a breakfast tea. Full body, but still some lightness to it. Milk and honey/sugar would be suggested for this the way most breakfast teas are better paired with.To compare it to coffee, this is more of a medium roast. For those who want that French roast or espresso, I suggest the Assam and Ceylon. Unlike coffee, it does not have that nice aroma to travel around the room when it is hot.The unique note to the Ntingwe Kwazulu is hard to describe, but it's noticeable in a good way. Can not seem to find any other brand that offers the tea from this region.Anyone who is not familiar with breakfast teas, do keep in mind it is the tea version of coffee minus the strong aroma. They are usually heavier, stronger and meant to be mixed with milk and sugar/honey. There isn't a set rule of what qualifies as a breakfast tea. Most of them are stronger, heavier, darker and is usually an Assam, Ceylon, Kenyan or a combo of any of them.If you're looking for a tea that doesn't require milk or anything at all, the breakfast teas are the ones to stay away from. It's not an all day drinking tea. All day or afternoon drinking tea usually means a lighter tea than the breakfast ones. The flavored teas, the more colorful ones, those are all day drinking teas. Those will always stand out a bit more due to the different ingredients added. Where as the breakfast tea is going to be a tad more on the dull side. The caffeine may wake up the senses, but the taste itself isn't going to be as lively as a peach/ginger tea, a Lady Grey, a tisane and such.For the ones who are experimenting with teas and the different flavors, the breakfast tea is in a whole different category by itself. It's not made to stand out so differently as if you are picking apples, oranges, pears, plums, apricots, berries and such. It's a very subtle type of tea that usually isn't meant to be mixed with anything else that you would find in the afternoon or all day drinking teas.A breakfast tea with a little more distinction, this is the one. Most breakfast teas just has people go ehh. Similar to having toast with butter and plain corn flakes. It's not to meant to be very exciting. Not that it couldn't be, but the base of most breakfast teas aren't made that way. The minor details or subtle differences varies, but that is what has one choose one breakfast tea over the other.You will find that some co. make more than one combo of the same teas. It doesn't mean they all taste the same. Sometimes it varies by grade and they won't tell you or they vary by region or something else. Only way to figure out which one you like better than the other is by trying them. Describing can only go so far. What has that je ne sais quoi for one drinker may not for another.I enjoy the heavier taste of the Assam/Ceylon combo, but then I am one to enjoy espresso and Turkish coffee. This is a 2nd alternative for a breakfast tea if I want something a little brighter. To like something heavier in taste does not necessarily mean that the tea is made more concentrated. A good, heavier tea doesn't require a heavier serving to get a good result. In fact, good teas that are distinctive enough would not require 2-3x the serving to be adequate.The same goes for coffee as well. If something is made well, the one serving is enough to get that taste, texture and over all experience that is most enjoyable. To double the amount in coffee or tea to make it more enjoyable either says the product isn't made well enough to begin with or the person has a heavier palate.You can double the serving into one cup for this tea, but it won't be the same as a Ceylon or Assam. That is because it isn't a Ceylon or Assam. That would be similar to saying that one expects a mushroom of any kind to be covered in any sauce and expect it to be the same experience as having steak. It can be cooked in beef fat and it's still not beef. Not the same texture, taste or over all experience.My advice is if you find a good breakfast tea you like, whether it be an Assam, Ceylon or combo, stick to that. If you want to experiment trying to blend those teas till you find one you like, you will find yourself owning a small tea shop. The combinations are endless. More so than the many combos of Earl Grey.

Product Title: Terrasoul Superfoods Organic Cacao Butter, 1 Lb - Raw | Keto | Vegan | Unrefined
Review: I didn‚Äôt have much luck baking with it. Regarding the general quality of this product, it seems to be excellent. It smells very good, and it seems to be free of any impurities.I personally purchased this cacao butter to experiment with using it in baked goods. The main thing I was interested in making with it was vegan ‚Äúblondies.‚Äù These are brownies made, not with cocoa or cacao powder, but typically with white chocolate. Vegan white chocolate is made with cacao butter, coconut oil, sugar and vanilla. Rather than going to all the trouble of first making white chocolate candy, and then putting it in my blondies, I decided not to worry about that extra step, since my recipe already contained coconut oil, sugar and vanilla.I created my own blondie recipe, after looking on every site I could find with advice on baking with cacao butter, and cross comparing that advice to any vegan recipes I could find for making blondies. Essentially, all any of the latter did was throw commercial white chocolate chips into a brownie recipe minus the cacao powder. That wouldn‚Äôt work for me, so I decided to simply adjust my tried-and-true, vegan brownie recipe.I left out the cacao powder and substituted the following for the 1/2 cup of coconut oil my recipe calls for: 1/4 cup of coconut oil plus 1/2 cup of cacao butter. Cacao butter is solid and dense at room temperature. Therefore I needed to liquefy it. To do this, I followed instructions from several professional cooking sites and heated the cacao butter over medium-low heat along with the coconut oil, stirring frequently, until it was fully liquid. Then I proceeded as usual with the assembling and mixing of my revamped brownie recipe.I also baked the blondies the same length of time as I bake my brownies, 30 minutes at 350 degrees F. in an 8 x 8 glass pan. Unfortunately, this proved to be a mistake. When baked that way, my brownies turn out as a gooey type of chewy, which is the ideal texture for brownies. Unfortunately, my blondies were the opposite of gooey. The sugar in the blondies dough crystallized, and as they cooled, the blondies got hard on the edges and only very slightly soft and chewy in the middle.Obviously, it will take some experimentation to figure out how to bake with cacao butter. Unhappily, it is extremely expensive, so this package won‚Äôt allow me the option to do a whole lot of experimenting before it is used up.If my baking attempt fails a second time, I will probably just use up the rest of this cacao butter as a skin moisturizer.

Product Title: Puroast Low Acid Ground Coffee, Decaf French Roast, High Antioxidant, 5 Pound Bag
Review: When your brain wants another cup, but your stomach cringes... Let me start by saying that everything I've read about the company makes me want to love their coffee.An inquiry to learn more was never answered, however.Taste is subjective. I love lots of varieties, but most often I reach for a lighter or full city roast with more depth than most roasters can achieve on that level.As a coffee addict, I must sometimes opt for a brewing method that is low acid, and/or use a lower acid bean like Puroast. Sacrificing some of what I crave is a fair exchange if it means I can still feed my lovely addiction.The Lost Art Blend is lively with subtle hints of tart citrus and a dry finish. Not dry to the point of being a negative...but almost.A star taken away for the lack of body, an one added right back for lack of acid.

Product Title: Belveder Smoked Sprats in Oil 250g, Kosher Product, Non GMO, Rich in Omega-3 Fatty Acid, Pack of 2
Review: Tasty preserved fish, smokiness is mild but dominant nonetheless. These sprats are tasty tinned fish, and the equal of high quality sardines. They are hardly bony at all, they don't have any of that mild bitterness you sometimes get with kippers, and the smokiness isn't overbearing. You get plenty of sprats in a jar, I'd estimate between 3 and 4 standard sardine tins worth.Personally I like them, and I'd order them again, but I wouldn't want to make them my primary choice of sardines. The smokiness is pleasing but it is also the dominant flavor. In total, a single jar has about 600 calories, and some, but not too much, residual oil. I'd prefer olive oil but rapeseed/linseed oil is fine too, it just doesn't add much character. I don't know if you'd have to refrigerate these after opening - the jar doesn't say one way or the other - but I'd rather not risk it, and though I like tinned fish I definitely don't like it cold.So I would recommend at least trying these, especially if you like tinned fish, and I'd like it if Belveder put out a spiced variant.

Chickweed is said to aid digestion and this is what I found - in terms of it being a mild diuretic. Good for gently getting things moving again without throwing the rest of the system out of wack.Maybe keep it in the cupboard for that purpose? A single teabag in 8oz is enough to give the flavor without causing any other effects. Worthy tasting, if you've never had it, but I probably won't include it in my usual lineup.

Review: Not as Good as Fresh, But Probably as Good as Bottled Can Get. This is one of my favorite drinks. I love ordering it every time I go out. Product Title: Yellow Dock Root Tea (50 tea bags, ZIN: 510806)
Review: It grows on you. I myself and a fan of yellow dock root tea. In contrast to many herbal teas, it is quite strong, something I appreciate. It is also very bitter, but it lacks the acidity that you find in more traditional teas, and so I have never had it make me nauseous. If anything, it seems to settle my stomach, after the fashion of an aperitif.If there are any positive health benefits, I have not noted them, nor did I expect to.I generally take water from a hot water tap, drop the tea bag right into it, and let it steep indefinitely. My sister found this to be far to bitter to stomach, so you may want to start with a shorter steep, but I think it is fine like it is. I generally use one satchet in 20z of water, so it's diluted some.This yellow dock root tea is a little weaker than the Buddah Tea equivalent - ASIN: B00QL8EKOC - and I think I prefer that one to this one, but they aren't really all that different.It is an acquired taste, and many will find it far too bitter to enjoy, but I would recommend trying it at least once. I plan on buying it again.

Very easy to eat, and truly a unique experience if tasting it for the first time, nothing like it anywhere else? It is definitely more of an original than most other similar products sold at local groceries. Once difficult to find, now we were happy to find it in the one and only, amazon.com, who seems to be expanding their culinary horizons even as I write these lines. 4 Stars.

Product Title: Slap Ya Mama Cajun Seasoning from Louisiana, Original Blend, No MSG and Kosher, 8 Ounce (Pack of 2)
Review: Great spice blend. I usually don't use spice blends which contain salt, especially when it's the first ingredient, but being a pepper and garlic lover, ordered a single can of Slap Ya Mama All Natural Cajun Seasoning from Louisiana Original Blend from Amazon. The blend is great and fresh tasting, however the paper canister was covered with stickers which obstructed almost everything on it. Additionally, the dispensing disk is not sitting properly, so it does not seal the freshness and I've had to transfer the blend into another spice jar. Next time, I'll purchase this locally I hope.The peppery spice adds oomph to anything food on which I've used it. I'm not a fan of very salty foods, so I add none until after I've Slapped some of this stuff into the dish and tasted it first. It's wonderful as a simple popcorn seasoning, french fry enhancement, or just a tad on a bowl of cottage cheese. It's good as long as it's fresh.

Product Title: In the Mix Gingerbread Cookie Kit, Ninja, 9.5 Ounce
Review: Cookies Taste Good, But Decorating Is Difficult. For a packaged cookie mix, this NINJABREAD GINGERBREAD COOKIE KIT makes pretty good cookies. They have a light gingerbread taste, and the icing doesn't leave an unpleasant aftertaste. You will need a couple of extra ingredients to make these: 1/4 cup honey (for the cookies), and 1/2 cup powdered sugar (for the icing).The mix really does produce 20 cookies. One of mine is a round blob (see the photo), because I didn't want to roll out any more dough. However, I could have gotten another Ninja cookie out of it. Before rolling out the gingerbread dough, I divided it into quarters, so I could tell how thick the dough needed to be to get five cookies per quarter.The cute Ninja cookie cutters are included. As you can see, I'm not terribly good at decorating cookies. It was harder than I expected to duplicate the package illustrations to make the gingerbread shapes look like Ninjas. Instead of using the included pastry bag, I used an [[ASIN:B00L9X382O OXO Baker's Silicone Decorating Bottle Kit]], which gave pretty good control. I had to chill the icing in the freezer for a little while, because when I mixed it according to the package instructions it was too thin for decorating purposes. All I could get were runny blobs.Because the decorating was kind of difficult, and the cookies taste like they came from a packaged mix, I rate this item at 4 stars ("I like it" on the official Amazon scale).

Product Title: Vana Life's Foods Plant based Ready Meal - Green Chickpea Superfood Bowl Heat and Eat Microwaved Cooked Bowl | Product of the USA (Chipotle & Lime Combo, 6-Pack)

Product Title: Dry Riced Cauliflower by Keto and Co | Unseasoned | Just 5.6g Net Carbs Per Serving | Gluten free, Vegan, Non-GMO, Diabetic Friendly | (5 Servings-Makes 1 Pound)
Review: I love this but it's crazy expensive. I've been eating cauliflower rice, but I'm not a big cauliflower fan, so when I saw this product (Dry Riced Broccoli by Keto and Co), I ordered some.And I really love it! I love the texture, the flavor, the convenience. It's so quick and easy to make, it's lightweight and easy to store with no refrigeration.There are only two things I don't like about it. First, it would have been nice if it had come in a resealable container. And second, the price. $8.99 for 5 16-gram servings. Come on! And do they at least reward regular customers by offering a bag twice as big at a lower price per serving - say 10 servings for $14? Nope.I'm still going to buy this periodically, but I would have bought regularly if it were just a little cheaper or if you got more per bag. But although I don't like caulflower as much, I can buy 585 grams of another brand's dried riced cauliflower for $20, but this 80 gram bag of riced broccoli is $9. I'm not always a value shopper, but the value comparison between the two is eyebrow raising.

Product Title: Coffee++ Paleo Butter Coffee Creamer 8.5 fl oz, Certified Organic, Pasture Raised, Lactose Free, Gluten-Free, Non-GMO, Paleo, Keto-Friendly, Batch Tested for Casein and Whey
Review: If you are following Bulletproof and travel this will save you the hasstle of Bulletproofing your coffee. I have adopted a BULLETPROOF lifestyle in the last year with amazing results. I also travel to Canada frequently and not only have to carry 100% grassfed butter (which is not available in Canada) but secure my MCT OIL in a container so airplane pressure doesn't cause leakage in my luggage. The restrictions for bringing butter into Canada to suit my needs during my trip is challenging. 20lbs or $20. It is the latter I have to adhere to along with raised eyebrows from custom officials. I am hoping this solves my problems on my next trip in May.I have tried both their ghee and coconut/ghee in my coffee along with my existing MCT oil and it is a definite improvement. The taste is smooth. A little goes a long way, I may just stop buying butter altogether even when I'm at home. It is a bit more expensive, however, the convenience and the flavor is worth it.

Product Title: CozyUp Signature Cozy Blend, Single-Serve Coffee Pods Compatible with Keurig K-Cup Brewers, Medium Roast Coffee, 100 Count
Review: Perfectly acceptable. It was priced right and tasted good. But not outstanding. Good adequate coffee at a good price.

Product Title: Pork Loin Chop Bone-In Step 1
Review: Update: second order Yummy. see my original review of pork chops way below - I ate one immediately and froze the other two. In a week or two placed a second order, follows.I placed a second order of same PC a week or two later. The first order I chose two pounds (received 3 lovely chops w/o tenderloin attached - they were great), scroll down. This order I placed for one pound (hoping to receive two chops of a medium to thick-cut). What a received was one mastodon chop. Really. Straight out of the Flintstones. One single humongous (with tenderloin portion attached) chop that really should be called a roast for two/or 3. Not having a bandsaw I was stuck with either cooking this like a roast or deboning it so I could halve its thickness (keep tenderloin separate). I decided to roast. Mistake. While the tenderloin was tender it had an off-taste (no idea why) but it was all I could eat at first serving. Refrigerated, reheated in air fryer the next day. Darn it was dry. Like the sahara. Ate about half the chop, diced the leftover, soaked in tamari in fridge to throw in rice tonight While I am still a fan of this, my advice is go for a 2lb order. You will probably get 3 chops. You need 4 chops? well go for 3lbs and put some in fridge. Don't chance with a 1lb order (unless you have a bandsaw)Second meat order for delivery and very happy with it (the first was truly wonderful beef ribeye). My only point off was this didn't seem terribly fresh. Not gone over at all but not firm enough, lost a lot of water in package, just a whiff here or there a little off. I had tried to get a qty of 2 chops so guessed at what that might weigh since you order by pound. Ended up with three chops. I can only eat one for a serving (and these were big) so I froze the other two and prepared the one with some good old shakenbake. It cooked up nice, still juicy, no off flavor and quite tender. Would buy again. Will probably try one of the other two prepared differently. I think just some simply seasoning, a good sear in a pan and then into the air fryer to finish off and serve with the au jus from searing and a little worcestshire. The one i had definitely was not dried out so I don't think the s&b is really necessary. Will update how that one goes when I get to making it.

Product Title: Red Bull Energy Drink, 16 Fl Oz Cans, 12 Pack

Product Title: Pacific Foods Organic White Bean Verde Chili, 16.5 Ounce Can
Review: Tasty, but sodium content is rather high ... I love a good vegetarian chili, and this harvest black bean is excellent -- a great combination of ingredients, nice consistency, etc. My only quibble is the sodium content -- to get the maximum protein and fiber content, you have to consume the entire can (not a problem -- 17 oz is a good serving size), and in so doing, you also consume 1240mg of sodium -- 54% of the daily recommended value.Those of us who have to watch sodium (high blood pressure/etc.) have to weigh the pros/cons of high-sodium meals and adjust the day's meal plan to accommodate something like this. For example, if I wanted to have this for lunch, I would likely limit my breakfast to yogurt/berries/granola (low sodium) and my supper to a salad topped with some diced grilled chicken with a low-sodium dressing.Something to consider. Yes, I'll purchase this again -- it's really a good veggie chili -- but I'll also be careful to plan to offset the high sodium content.

Product Title: Amazon Brand - Happy Belly Chunky Chocolate Chip Cookies, 11.75 Ounce
Review: Affordable Cookies. Normally I avoid talking about cost but these are Amazon's Happy Belly store brand, generics if you will and they were, for the times, quite affordable.They're a good cookie, fresh, crunchy, plenty of chips in each cookie, plenty of cookies in the pack and they taste great.

Review: Great price for a wonderful product I use often. Was so happy to find ground ginger on Amazon since it is difficult to find locally. Great price for a wonderful product I use often.

Review: I love these! OMGOSH! These are delicious! I'm hooked!Update: just ordered more. üíñMinus one ‚òÜ star as they arrived in pieces.

Review: Another very good Simply Organic product. Nice dark color and I like other Simply Organic products I have in the kitchen. I do wish this had more of a fragrance to it, however, which is why I knocked off one star. I really like using Dill Weed with potatoes and this tastes just fine, but it doesn't have the Dill Weed fragrance that I expected.

Product Title: NOW Foods, Certified Organic Light Agave Nectar, Blue Agave, Certified Non-GMO, Low-Glycemic Sweetener, Kosher, 23.2-Ounce
Review: Good on pancakes and less sugar than other syrups. Not too expensive either. This isn't too expensive for the amount and it's very sweet so you don't need a lot! It's fairly thick and not runny. I use it on pancakes and for baking instead of maple syrup. It has less sugar than other syrups.

Product Title: Bubly bubly Sparkling Water, 12oz Cans (18 Pack), Passionfruit, 216 Fl Oz
Review: Good tasting for unsweetened. Don't expect sweet because it's not. It's fizzy water with a little flavor. I like the blackberry and mango the best. They have the best flavor. They are better chilled too.

Product Title: StarKist Wild Alaskan Pink Salmon - Reduced Sodium - 14.75 oz Can (Pack of 12)
Review: Mild canned salmon with bones and skin. The large chunks of salmon are packed really well into these 5 serving cans and if the rest of the case is in a similar condition, I'll be happy. With no added salt, I taste the salmon and nothing but the salmon and I mean all parts of it. The dog enjoyed a few bits of the skin as I prepared it for us humans and since calcium is a pro for our nutrition, we didn't share with her. The cans require a can opener, they are not a pull-tab top. Mine was packed with the top down and therefore since the cans are a little wider at the top than the bottom, the water in which the fish is packed covers more of the salmon. The interior of the cans are a dark slate color, there is no obvious coating, and there is nothing that addresses BPA on the attached paper label. The fish was, "pulled from the icy cold Alaskan waters," and they were, "cooked and packed fresh from the boat." It is indeed a mild wild salmon. I tried to trace the fish online at their website but the code on the cans is not valid. It's best by date is 08/20/2022 and about half of the cans have a single tiny dent which is not a big deal for me. The price changes like crazy on this product so I'd suggest tracking it to see the trend. There is also a variety with added salt which as of this minute is more affordable.

Product Title: Fisher Snack Oven Roasted Never Fried, Made with Sea Salt, Almond & Cashew Blend, 9 Oz
Review: Less Is More. These nuts, though.Sorry. Seriously, they are very fresh and well-prepared. The only thing I would change is the amount of salt.They seem to be thoroughly coated in a fine salty dust, rather than stippled with grains. That is a recurring issue with sea salted snacks. Coarser salt makes for flavor without driving you straight to the water trough for a fifteen minute drink.Other than that, they're lovely. A little rich in the wallet, but lovely.

Product Title: Golden Flavor Sesame Sticks - Salted - 3 pounds total - (4) 12 ounce bags
Review: Good product. Good product, just wish it came in a resealable bag but tuperware works.

Product Title: Benchmark Bouquets Flowering Fields, With Vase (Fresh Cut Flowers)
Review: The real issue is not if I like them, but if my friend that I sent them to did. I met my childhood friend when I was 10 years old. I remember us playing on the playground, having sleepovers, chatting about boys, talking while away at college, etc. And now years later, after husbands and kids, at almost 50, we still keep touch. She lives in Kansas and I live in HotLanta. So this Mother's Day, I decided to surprise her with some flowers, a kind of special thanks to her for always being there. Of course, she was surprised and pleased (see picture). She said that the sunflowers were beautiful (unfortunately you can't really see them in the photo that she took), and that since some of the flowers hadn't fully opened yet, she was sure to enjoy them over the next few days. I however, wished they had been a little fuller. Perhaps she should have cut the stems a little shorter, which would have made them fill out the vase more but regardless, that was a negative I found about this particular bouquet. Simply stated, I thought they could have been fuller. BUT on the positive side (there were definitely more positives than negatives), Amazon made it super easy to order; they delivered them on time and in good condition. Overall, she was pleased so I guess I am too.

Product Title: Coco Lite Muligrn Pop Cakes Original Pop Cakes 2.64 Ounce, Pack of 12
Review: So glad to find them! My local store used to carry these, but evidently not much call for them these days. But I like them, I must reduce my wheat intake due to arthritis and these are the lowest in wheat or carbs, perfect for me.Really appreciate finding them, of course being as delicate as they are, you get a couple broken in a bag, but I had that from the store bought ones. All in all, a good purchase, this will be my ‚ÄúGo To‚Äù seller for my Coco Lites!Recommend this seller, the Pop Cakes were shipped very fast and in a nice sturdy box, very satisfied with my purchase, thank you!

Product Title: Wedderspoon Raw Premium Manuka Honey, KFactor 16, 17.6 Oz, Unpasteurized, Genuine New Zealand Honey, Traceable from Our Hives to Your Home
Review: Great companion for my ginger tea, but the lid gets stuck. A lot thicker and opaque (tan/golden) than the regular honey I am used to.Kind of pasty, VERY sticky.I put a spoonful in my ginger tea and it works out perfectly.It dissolves into a darker brownish color into the hot water.The lid though.... it have heck of a time keeping the lid clean.The lid gets sticky, sticks onto the plastic jar and then I can't open it.Sigh.I tried putting plastic wrap between the lid and jar,did not help.

Product Title: Amazon Brand - Happy Belly Honey Graham Crackers, 14.4 Ounce
Review: Tasty and spreadable. I have a few of these most evenings after dinner with some cut up fruit spread on top.I just wish they were a little less expensive.

Product Title: Numi Organic Black Tea, Breakfast Blend, 18 Count (Pack of 3) - Packaging May Vary
Review: Okay but could be stronger imho... Nice aroma, just wish the flavor was stronger. I steep the bag for 6 minutes and the expiration date id a year from now so not sure why they taste so weak, but I'm always game for trying varieties I've never tried before, at least once! :)

Product Title: Tapioca Pearl / White , Large Balls, 14oz (400g)
Review: Takes forever to cook. The only problem I had with this product was the fact that it did not give clear instructions that were correct for cooking.

Product Title: Kraft Mac & Cheese Original Macaroni & Cheese Dinner, Value Size, 14.5 Ounce (Pack of 8)
Review: I really want to give it 5 stars, because ... I really want to give it 5 stars, because it's such a go-to staple in our house, a sure-fire hit with the kids. I just wish it were a little healthier, a little less salt and fat. Also, at least one of the boxes that I received had a lot of what I hope was crumbled macaroni "dust" in it - it was some powder that didn't look normal. But i didn't discover it till I dumped it all in the boiling water. I tried to extra rinse it, but I don't know what it was or if I got it off. Nobody seemed adversely affected afterwards, so I hope it was just ground up macaroni. All that said, we will definitely reorder frequently.

Product Title: Del Monte Veggieful Veggie Bowl, Garlic and Herb, 7.4 Ounce (Pack of 12)
Review: adds variety to pantry and preps, add more goodies to it, add broth for quick broth bowl. Not too shabby! Definitely more for convenience, to have something on hand. Not my go-to for a healthy meal (shelf stable is not going to be epitome of health food). But it adds a little variety to my pantry, and I love the fiber and protein content for each portion. Could use a little less sugar and sodium (from soy sauce) but it isnt terrible.I added this to my longer term pantry, not exactly emergency food, but something that could be used as such since there is really no preparation needed. I can eat this alone, or use it to flavor something else. Add in more vegetables (fresh, canned, frozen, left overs), or a protein (beans, canned, fresh, frozen, left overs), or more grain (or pasta), or add in a bunch of broth to make a quick soup (my favorite application). It is well packaged and the shelf life is going to be longer than the best buy date stamped on it (does not expire the day that is stamped in it- be smart).

Product Title: Torani Syrup, Red Raspberry, 25.4 Ounces (Pack of 4)
Review: Not for me. This taste was off for me. I think it‚Äôs just preference. It was well packaged and seemed like a quality product but I did not like it. So, I‚Äôm not sure I would put much stock in this review because there is really not any accounting for taste. You might like it very much. I just didn‚Äôt.

Review: One of the Best. Very good. The bars come in 'separable bite sized' squares once the packaging is opened. Product Title: Lavazza Crema E Gusto Ground Coffee Blend, Espresso Dark Roast, 8.8 Oz Bricks (Pack of 4) Authentic Italian, Blended And Roasted in Italy, Non GMO, Value Pack, Full bodied with rich aftertaste
Review: Good strong coffee best using pour-over brewer. This coffee is ground very fine, and it produces a weak cup of coffee with most automatic drip coffee makers. However, using a basic pour-over brewing technique, the resulting coffee is good - bold but smooth. Just pour over small amounts of just-below-boiling-temperature water (2 oz or so at a time) until the water has passed completely through the filter.

Product Title: Muir Glen Organic Diced Canned Tomatoes, 28 oz.
Review: excellent brand, but cans should be better protected- many dented from warehouse. Tired of smashed, crap products. I will take a small dent here and there but most were smashed. WTF. I understand that most products are still good and likely why they end up as a warehouse item (which is where I ordered from), but when it comes to tomato products? Unacceptable. So buyer beware. Might seek a refund, might just use them up in an upcoming chili. I know I dont intend to store them long in this condition. Had I bought them full price, I would be making a bigger stink. My review is to reflect quality of actual product as Muir Glen is a fantastic brand.I dont rate on price. Everyone can see the price before order, we all have different budgets, needs, preferences, prices fluctuate, there are sales, and right now.. prices have simply been rising on everything. If I can get good organic tomatoes at $2 or less per can, then I think that is reasonable (currently $25 with subscribe and save). DO I want to pay way less, yes (actually I got mine on sale at $12 so I did get a great deal, but at cost of mostly dented cans). Hence why my focus is on actual product.Tomatoes are good and fresh tasting. No noticeable degrade with dented cans. I wont let the sit for long though.

Product Title: Santa Cruz Organic No Stir Creamy Dark Roasted Peanut Butter, 16 Oz (Pack of 6)

Review: Good pasta from a name you can trust. Barilla makes good gluten free pasta. I wish it didn't contain so much corn however because if you cook it too long it will end up mushy. It wasn't any more expensive than it is at the stores.

Product Title: Weetabix Breakfast Cereal, 24 Biscuits
Review: Just as satisfying as I remember. I first had these when I was living in Ireland many years ago, and so I thought it was time to try them again.For the uninitiated, these are small bricks or blocks of compressed wheat flakes, about 3"x1.5"x.5" or so. They are mostly wheat - dry and light with no additional sweetness. to them. You can eat one directly, which I don't recommend trying more than once, or you can put a couple in a bowl and pour some milk over them, crushing them up afterward with a spoon. They soften immediately, but still retain a little bit of their fiber and body. So they aren't crispy or dense like many wheat flakes tend to be in milk, and they aren't "goopy" like porridge. Basically, if you like wheat-type cereal but have trouble chewing or working through denser options, this is a good alternative.Neato, in my opinion. I still like them, I usually have two or three of these in a bowl and they are satisfying enough. Not as filling as museli or oatmeal, but pretty nice anyway. A box would last me about three weeks, since I don't have them every day, and I'll probably order some again in the future.Would recommend.

Product Title: Traina Home Grown Sun Dried Baker‚Äôs Fruit Medley - Diced Peaches, Cranberries, Apricots, Pears, Nectarines, and Raisins - Non GMO, Gluten Free, Packed in Resealable Pouch (2 lbs)
Review: great mix. Love it. It has a great assortment of dried fruit. If this had the right assortment of nuts mixed in, it would be perfect!

Product Title: SunWest Fresh Navel Oranges (2 Pounds of Oranges)
Review: Great product. I sent these to my mom she loved them she said they were very juicy.

Product Title: OREO Green Creme Easter Chocolate Sandwich Cookies, Limited Edition, Easter Cookies, 12.2 oz
Review: Keeps your portions in control. Although I was a hydrox fan, well, they are gone and for years have gotten my cookie fix with various Oreos. I like the little cookies, not as many stray crumbs and the little pouches are good for portion control and freshness. What's not to like? Well, they ain't hydrox but :( It is probably more expensive purchasing this way but again, the freshness keeping is probably worth it. I don't snack a lot on such things and I don't have to worry about the rest of my cookies going stale. To me, it is worth the trade off.

Product Title: 1 X Dark Danncy Pure Mexican Vanilla Extract From Mexico 33oz Each 1 Plastic Bottle Sealed
Review: Pleasant flavor and inexpensive. I really like this product for the money. If you've never had Mexican Vanilla, it has a little bit of a floral presence that is actually pleasant. Just don't over, the vanilla is stronger than you think. Not bad, but think of it like using a seasoning (and really it kinda is). Part of the strong flavor is due to the fact it is alcohol free and doesn't evaporate like alcohol based ones. I've had people compliment the flavor this vanilla. For the money, you can't go wrong. It is mostly real vanilla, but it also contain "other" natural flavors. I don't know what that means, but just so you know... It does contain Potassium Sorbate if that bothers you. It's a small amount and I don't use that much at one time, so I figure its safe.Packaging: If you worry about leaking, we laughed at how well it was packaged. It took me a few minutes to get into all the packaging and tape. They were not going to allow leaks to happen on their watch at this company LOL.

Product Title: KIND Bars, Dark Chocolate Mocha Almond, Healthy Snacks, Gluten Free, Low Sugar, 5g Protein, 12 Count
Review: KIND bars are a great snack or pick-me-up ! I like Kind bars because nuts are good for you, so you have crunch, dried fruit or peanut butter and dark chocolate is good for you too. Having one for snack keeps you from overeating and they easy to chew. Some other brands can pull your fillings out of your teeth and are dry and tasteless. KIND Bars have many flavors and quench your hunger. I definitely recommend them.

Product Title: Energy Drink Sample Box, 7 or more samples ($7.99 credit with purchase)
Review: Perfect way to sample a variety! Bought and sent to DD as her age group loves to try these type products. No complaints from her, so guess all was well. I would add watch those with energy labels, so as not to overdue and stress the body, possibly, same as watch sugar contents. The Healthy Greens are a good option.

Review: Great value! Good for soups and stews! Simple to use. Good for base in soup or stew.

Review: ALMOST! I brought these to a game night with relatives. I had been looking for the individually packaged short twizzlers that I had found years ago around Valentine's day. They were softer, more plump and very good. These are definitely softer than the regular twizzlers and more plump.. but not quite the ones I got years ago. Wish Twizzler would make those available! I would, however, buy these again since they are the closest I've found.

Review: How to quickly open the candy wrapper. With each hand, take the ends of the candy paper and pull away from the candy. It will spin around and the paper will practically fall off. This is my second batch of these and they are different from the first batch. There's barely any salt and they don't taste nearly as good without it. These are meant to melt in your mouth, not chew. But I miss the salt at the end. Still good tho

Product Title: Jansal Valley Diced Glazed Lemon Peel, 1 Pound
Review: I think it taste good, me and my girlfriend like to have orange ... I think it taste good , me and my girlfriend like to have orange peels with tea , so I ordered lemon peels to try . The only negative thing I think they're too tiny ( chopped into small cubes ) , wish they were bigger and wish they were less sweet . Pieces are small and sweet so has almost like a marmelade taste , wish they were little more natural tasting but over wise it's fine , probably good for baking but a bit too sweet in my view to eat out of the box .

Review: Good for the body. Looking into herbal remedies and was to take them tea is a good route. I am not going to lie to you the flavor is not amazing and something you will need to get used to. The only place i can find it is on amazon. I have noticed in my experience drinking it once a day i do not get as sick as i did.

Product Title: Snappy Popcorn 1 Gallon Snappy Pure Peanut Oil No Color Added, 128 Fl Oz

The fries had a nice subtle crunch. They were perfect and tasted just like restaurant fries. Lumpia (Filipino spring rolls) tasted awesome with this oil too. Product Title: Manoir des Abeilles ¬∑ Lavender honey, glass jar ¬∑ 250g (8.8 oz)

Product Title: Nescafe Dolce Gusto Coffee Pods, Cafe Au Lait,16 Count (Pack of 3)
Review: Almost as good as the Vanilla Latte. I like the Cafe Aulait better than I expected to considering it's just a single combo capsule rather a separate capsule for milk. I add a splash of peppermint syrup to this and it's pretty darn good - almost as good as my favorite Vanilla Latte Gusto flavor.

Product Title: Planters Mixed Nuts, Lightly Salted, 8.5 oz Canister

Product Title: The Original Whole Bean Coffee, Medium Roast, 3 Pack - 12 Oz, Bulletproof Keto 100% Arabica Coffee, Certified Clean Coffee, Rainforest Alliance, Sourced from Guatemala, Colombia & El Salvador
Review: Strong and powerful, like my man. Very good coffee. Purchasing by subscription now.

Product Title: Folgers Simply Gourmet Natural Chocolate Raspberry Flavored Ground Coffee, 10 Ounces
Review: Not my favorite flavor of the Folgers Naturals, but pretty darn good. I'll admit right now: I am a "Quality + Price" snob when it comes to flavored coffee. After years spending upwards of $15-30/bag on high-end, whole-bean flavored coffees, I awoke one day and said to myself: "My life needs purpose. I shall now search far and wide to find the very best tasting flavored coffee I can buy for the least amount of money."Okay, Okay...I didn't do that. At all.But if I HAD done, I would be right to stop looking once I found the Folgers Simply Gourmet "Natural..." line.I actually buy each flavor in bulk now--despite the fact that a tiny seed of bourgeois pompousness deep inside me feels ridiculous for admitting I landed on FOLGERS...the same company that makes the adulterated, sacrilegious INSTANT coffee my gran used to drink. So I'll say, going in, that you CAN'T go wrong with anything available in the Folgers SG Naturals line.Still, of them all, this is probably my least favorite. Don't get me wrong. It's REALLY GOOD. It's just that I LOVE raspberries, and I think the combination of the chocolate with the raspberries HERE just doesn't land as well as the singular flavours they offer in this line.In the spirit of blatant hypocrisy, though, something I have to admit I DO love is to combine the Naturals Caramel flavor (which is by far my fave) with their Chocolate one, at a ratio of 1:1. THAT combo works MUCH better, and rivals any $20 bag of flavored coffee I've ever bought!

Product Title: PBfit All-Natural Peanut Butter Powder, Powdered Peanut Spread From Real Roasted Pressed Peanuts, 8g of Protein, 30 Ounce (Pack of 1)
Review: SO MANY USES BESIDES SMOOTHIES! HEALTHY DESSERT TIP -. OK DESSERT TIP FIRST:I work to eat as HEALTHY as I can. Not necessarily not fat or calories, but making those I do eat COUNT.I needed to get cholesterol, triglycerides down, so gave up even low fat ice cream, cheese, etc. in between redoing labs. BUT YA GOTTA have something sweet that feels indulgent, satisfying sometimes!THIS IS LIKE GOOEY PB FUDGE with walnuts.I take a SMALL bowl, like a sauce bowl, something about the size of a small cat bowl.TWO HEAPING TABLESPOONS of PB FITAdd JUST enough water that it is still thickAdd TWO DARK CHOC HERSHEY KISSESNUKE SECONDS at a time, keep stirring til choc and pnut butter blendADD ABOUT 10-12 WALNUT HALVES, so 5-6 walnuts (I know high in fat, but I need the omegas)OPTIONAL: Sprinkle with Ceylon CinnamonSOOO SATISFYING, RICH AND FILLING! MORE THAN if I ate a bowl of ice cream.PROS:MORE intense peanut taste than most regular peanut butters!SO much lower in fat so I can incorporate it into my diet moreMUCH easier to blend into smoothies or ice cream shakes than regular peanut butter!I also add to oatmeal (I add a little less water and cook just a tad less, so it's the consistency of cookie dough :-) and it takes like oatmeal peanut butter cookies (also add Ceylon cinnamon and stevia, SO GOOD and HEALTHY)Great SIMPLE ingredientsYou can RECONSTITUTE with water and make a sandwichCOST EFFECTIVE! You really get a lot for the moneyCONS:Maybe I like it a little too much?!

Product Title: Taylors of Harrogate Herbal Infusions Variety Box, 12 Count (Pack of 1)
Review: Taylors of Harrogate Herbal Infusions Variety Box - great way to try some teas! I wanted to try some Taylors of Harrogate herbal/fruit teas (sorry, infusions), and this assortment seemed like a great way to go. Let me tell you about the various flavors.My favorite is Mandarin & Ginger. Very fruity, almost like juice, and smells heavenly if you love the smell of citrus juice. The ginger is definitely the secondary or tertiary taste here, but there are notes of it in the background to warm up the overall taste. It had a couple of ingredients I wasn't familiar with, but both seem to be related to the blackberry family. They add a tiny hint of sweetness and a very faint herbal flavor. Very nice hot and delightful iced. Overall a winner for those who love fruit tea without too much spice - I've already ordered a box of it.Next is peppermint. It's not as sharp as a lot of peppermint teas area, and I appreciate that. It tastes good on its own, and tastes great with some fruit teas I had around the house. Very nice hot, and it's also good with some milk. I've already ordered more.The rose lemonade smells of both rose and lemon, and it tasted more of rose than I expected and a little less than I expected of the lemon. If that sounds good to you, chances are you'll love it. Otherwise if you're like me, it's best with a couple splashes added and stirred in - yum!Last, for me, is the Sweet Rhubarb. I've had strawberry rhubarb pie and loved it with no reservations. This tea, however, to me had such an unpleasant smell that I literally couldn't bring myself to taste it. Even dry in the bag, the smell was repulsive to me, to the point that I wondered if it had gone bad, but more than one bag smelled that way, so I guess I don't like rhubarb tea.Overall I gave the Taylors of Harrogate Herbal Infusions Variety Box five stars because although I disliked one of the teas, I loved two of them, found the third one tasty, and I got to try them all before committing to a larger box of each. I feel that this is what buying an assortment of anything should be about, and I'm happy I tried this one.

Product Title: Great Lakes Pure, Beef Gelatin, 16oz 4-Pack
Review: A great protein source. This gelatin has been a great tool in getting my kids to eat more protein without the taste of meat. I use it in homemade fruit snacks, and it gives them more protein than a yogurt for their afternoon pick-me-up. I use it for homemade marshmallows, jello and a quick substitute when I don't have bone broth to drink. It is helpful with strengthening joints, weight loss and the health of hair and nails. Seriously amazing stuff! There's 6g of protein per Tbs. of gelatin powder. It gels quickly so I recommend heating part of the liquid you are putting it in as well as having an immersion blender (or a really quick, strong hand to whisk). Just a small warning with the fast gel action - it will clump if you add too much and don't start stirring right away. I highly recommend it nutritionally, and for that reason I give this product 5 stars.

Review: The best of the Pirouline flavors ... Of all the flavors offered by Pirouline, this Dark Chocolate is my all-time favorite. So far, I've used 4 of the 6 cans, each containing 2 foil-wrapped sleeves (so I've opened 8 sleeves so far). I've had 3 sleeves with NO breakage at all -- every one completely intact with just a tiny bit of crumbling on an end here and there. The other 5 sleeves contained some broken cookies -- ranging from 20% to probably 60% of the contents. Since I purchased these for my own use, this isn't a problem. The broken ones taste as good as the unbroken ones. :-) So far, I've had no sleeves with total disintegration of the contents. But if you're looking for perfect presentation, bear in mind that you're probably going to have to deal with some breakage.That said, I'll purchase these again. The price is comparable to my local supermarket, and having it delivered is a convenience I'm willing to pay a bit extra for. Product Title: Walker's Shortbread Fingers, Pure Butter Shortbread Cookies, 5.3 Oz (Pack of 6)
Review: Fingers and Highlanders are both reviewed. FINGERS: These are cookie sticks, not fingers. When Alexa announced that my fingers were out for delivery, I was taken aback until I recalled ordering the Walkers shortbread cookies. Walkers knows how to make nice cookies for having with a cup of tea and the "fingers" are the shape that's best suited for dunking. They are also great for dunking in melted chocolate as a base for crystallized ginger or some almond slivers if you're so inclined. You don't have to spill the beans and let folks know that you didn't actually bake the shortbread yourself because they will be so impressed by how cute they are on a plate. If you purchase the package of 6 little boxes, you can always wrap a ribbon around one and present it as a quick gift, perhaps with a little box of tea. Be forewarned, though, that even though the box is petite, it's not intended as a single treat. Each cookie is a mere 100 calories and I wouldn't call that terrible for a treat that's not overly sweet.HIGHLANDERS: Oh wow, I don't even care that each of the several boxes of these arrived in its own plastic envelope with no other padding or protection and some arrived broken. They are that good. Round, thick, a little salty, a little flour like, a little buttery, and a nice edge of sweetness from the demerara sugar. What I received are baked on the lighter side, not even brown, so they are not as hard as some shortbread cookies. I purchased these to share but since they are broken, I'm transferring the broken ones to my own cookie jar and repackaging the whole cookies into tins for distribution. If you need 6 intact cookies, I'd recommend buying two packages.

Product Title: SunyamGo Food Flavoring, 10 Packs Concentrated Flavoring Extracts Flavors for Baking Candy Lip Gloss Making, Water and Oil Soluble - Vanilla Chocolate Watermelon Banana Mint Caramel .35 Fl Oz Bottle
Review: More Delicious Flavorings Than I've Ever Tasted Before! If you bake a lot and want to add some food flavorings to your icings and cakes these are an excellent choice. I first tried the caramel flavor in a vanilla protein drink and was impressed that I could get such a good tasted from six tiny drops. So these are very concentrated and a little goes a long way.Next I made a strawberry icing. It was great. I then added coconut and banana flavoring and came up with something really unique. So using one flavoring is good but you can also combine the flavors for chocolate banana, chocolate mint, strawberry chocolate, watermelon banana and vanilla cream.The flavors you get in this package include: strawberry, coconut, watermelon, chocolate, vanilla, blueberry, mint, cream, caramel and banana.Now I will say that tasting these flavors straight from the containers does not give you a good idea of what the flavor is going to taste like. I tried that! You really need to put it in sweetened food to get the full range of deliciousness.If you want to test out flavors I suggest either putting them in sweetened milk and drinking it or putting 3 tablespoons confectioners' powdered sugar in a bowl, using a spatula to blend in 1/2 teaspoon salted butter then a few drops of whipping cream. This gives a nice icing base for you to test the flavors. Add a few drops of what you are considering and mix in well. I can promise you, you will be impressed!These flavors are better than anything I've tasted that is made in America. These flavorings are made in China and they obviously have access to some really great food grade ingredients and realistic artificial flavorings.The ingredients include: Food Extracts, Water, Propylene Glycol, Natural and Artificial Flavors.This arrives in a cute box that keeps all the flavorings organized. It fits nicely in my kitchen cabinet.Other ways to use these flavorings would be to put them in ice cream, milkshakes and coffee drinks. I have not tried them in beauty products but I guess they would work well in sweetened lip balm.I'm very happy with these flavorings and love them! I think you will enjoy using them too.~The Rebecca ReviewP.S. I made chocolate caramel cupcakes and strawberry cupcakes using these flavorings They are great! You literally need just a few drops for really good flavor.

Product Title: Lotte Milkis Soft Soda Variety Favor (Melon, Pack Of 6)
Review: DELICIOUS sodas! I even use them for cocktails too! I'm now addicted to these drinks!!! The first I tried was the Melon, then the Banana, and now I placed an order for another Melon + the Strawberry and and Peach! I have traveled around the world but never came across these drinks till I saw them on Amazon. The price is steep BUT the taste is awesome imo! It's not like the American soft drinks or carbonated sodas - the flavor is just enough without being overwhelming and the carbonation is minimal (i.e. Pepsi, other fruit flavoured sodas). Not only are they great (and thirst-quenching) for drinking alone, but I also use them to make cocktails! One example of one using the Melon flavor is (I don't really measure, just kinda eyeball the amounts or ratios of ingredients, but you can always adjust them to your liking): 2 - 2 1/2 parts Midori (Japanese) Melon liquor, 1 - 1 1/2 parts vodka (I found one in a melon/dragonfruit flavor by Svedka brand, but you can use another complementary flavor, or brand). Add these to a tall rocks glass with ice and then fill with this Melon soda and stir well. Be careful not to shake the soda since it does have some light carbonation which will go all over the place if you do. Adjust amounts as you like after tasting. This makes, imo, a great tasting and very light alcoholic beverage - perfect for summer! For those who like the other flavors just as much (or more) as the Melon, you can still make the same drink by adding another flavor vodka and ‚Äòliquor‚Äô (like a banana). My favorite brand is Giffard, made in France since the 1800‚Äôs, and not cheap either, if you can find it! They make other great tasting flavors too like peach and grapefruit, lychee, etc. and they taste really good on their own too! The only thing I wish is that these drinks didn't come in a can, but instead with a twist off cap which would keep the fizz if you don't finish the whole can at once, but otherwise great beverage, in spite of the price!

Product Title: LaCroix Sparkling Water, Pamplemousse (Grapefruit) 8 pack
Review: Very pleased - will definitely purchase again! I was really not sure what to expect from this product. I'd read the reviews, and they ranged from "gross" to "crisp and light".I couldn't find it locally, so finally ordered one on Amazon.Now, I LOVE carbonated drinks. I've never bought a Soda Stream though, because there's no place around here to get canister refills, and most of the syrups were disgusting, so no point. I've been drinking sodas, but want to wean myself off the cola type drinks. I thought this might be a good compromise, as I don't really like plain water.I bought two brands to try - the other one (not naming it here, since this is a review about LaCroix, but it was strawberry dragonfruit. It was gross, and I love dragonfruit) was NOT good at all, so I almost didn't want to try this one! That would have been a mistake.This comes very close to Sierra Mist, IMHO. Of course, it isn't the same, since there is no sweetener in it. That's right - no sugar, so salt, no fake coloring. Clear and bubbly. It was very good. The colder, the better. I tried it right from the case and it was meh. But, stuck a few cans in the fridge and let them get nice and cold (I don't always have access to ice), and it improved it a great deal.I can see this being a regular part of my drink lineup. It will help me not drink so many sugary sodas, but still give me the carbonation I love.The light lime taste is nice, and I am a big fan. You could float lime slices in it if you wanted it more pronounced.LaCroix, you did a GREAT job with this one, and you've won me over. Wish I could find you in our area, but I'll spoil myself and get it here until it arrives. Will be happy to try the other flavors as well. Yum!

Product Title: PNM Cacao Powder Organic Raw Unsweetened Cocoa (3 Pack 16 Oz)
Review: This is amazing cacao powder, and can be used to make chocolate sauce and chocolate (nut, soy, rice, or dairy) milk. Enjoy! Having given up dairy and chocolate milk powder, I had to find another way to make my own chocolate soy milk and chocolate dip. This power is amazing. All one has to do is to mix up powder and a bit of sugar, add hot (boiling, or nearly so) water, and stir. I have settled on a ratio of 1 level tablespoon of cacao powder and one level teaspoon of natural german sugar--this cuts the bitterness enough to make it good to add to coffee or to soy milk, or to refrigerate and use as a chocolate sauce. It was too bitter for me with less sugar, but your tastes may be different. I tried making a 5 tbsp. cacao powder and 5 tsp. sugar mix (with hot water, of course), stirring it really well, and then refrigerating it. Imagine my surprise when it turned into a thick shiny brown chocolate sauce! I was so excited, I tried it on nearly everything (OK, almond butter and rice crackers, with chocolate sauce drizzled on top)--SUCCESS! I now know that I can use this mixture just as I would have used cocoa powder or chocolate drink mixes in the past. The flavor is deep and wonderful, and is absolutely vegan.

Product Title: Yupik Nuts Raw Shelled Filbert Hazelnuts, 2.2 lb
Review: Fresh and delicious. My order of these hazelnuts was fresh and well packaged. The nuts have an excellent taste. Because nuts of any kind can become rancid, I store these hazelnuts along with all my nuts in the refrigerator and/or the freezer.I got these raw, shelled hazelnuts specifically to make a homemade version of Nutella. The Center of Science in the Public Interest (CSPI) describes Nutella as ‚Äúmore sugar and modified palm oil than hazelnut.‚Äú Palm oil is not only unhealthy, but it is associated with horrendous abuse of plantation workers, including sexual abuse, and my personal goal is to avoid it.The seller of these nuts, Yupik, is located in Montreal, Quebec, Canada. The main hazelnut producing countries are Turkey, Italy, Spain, USA and Greece. These particular hazelnuts are sourced from Turkey.Below is my (relatively) low-sugar recipe for homemade Nutella, for anyone who might be interested. I‚Äôve also attached photos of it.HOMEMADE NUTELLA, CHOCOLATE-HAZELNUT SPREADIngredients1-1/4 cup (176 gm) hazelnuts lightly roasted and skinned5 tablespoons cacao powder1 tablespoon coconut milk powder1 tablespoon agave nectar1 tablespoon maple syrup1 tablespoon honey1/2 teaspoon monk fruit powder1/2 teaspoon stevia3 big dates (21 grams)1 tablespoon vanilla1 teaspoon cherry extract OR almond extract (optional, enhances flavor of chocolate)3 tablespoons purified waterInstructions1. Roast hazelnuts in toaster oven on 400 degrees for about 5 minutes, until they are lightly browned.2. Place the nuts on a terrycloth towel and fold it over on top of them. Rub the nuts briskly against each other and the rough texture of the fabric in order to loosen their skin and remove as much of it as possible. Do not worry if absolutely all of the skin is not removed. Note: Another option is to place the roasted nuts in a wire-mesh colander and rub them briskly against the wire mesh to loosen their skin.3. Blend the nuts and all the other ingredients on high speed in a Vitamix or a food processor until the mixture is smooth and creamy. Add additional water 1 tablespoon at a time, as needed, in order to increase the creaminess to a desired consistency.Yield: 1-1/3 cups (22 tablespoons)Calories: 63 per tablespoon (commercial Nutella is 100 calories per tablespoon)

Product Title: Druids Grove Lactic Acid ‚òÆ Vegan ‚äò Non-GMO ‚ù§ Gluten-Free ‚ú° OU Kosher Certified - 8 oz.
Review: Excellent for making vegan cheese. I purchased this lactic acid as an ingredient in making vegan mozzarella cheese. Along with nutritional yeast, it helps impart to vegan cheese the authentic flavor of dairy cheese. This seems to be an excellent brand of lactic acid for making vegan cheese. It is a white, granular powder that seems to be free of impurities. It is certified non-GMO, vegan and Kosher.Below is general information about lactic acid.Lactic acid was first produced for commercial use 60 years ago, but it is only within the past two decades that it has been consistently utilized both in processed food and in cosmetics. Lactic acid is manufactured commercially by two distinct methods: fermentation or chemical synthesis. European nations tend to use fermentation, and in the USA it is mostly produced by chemical synthesis. Vegan versions, such as this product, are extracted from cane or beet sugar.In food, lactic acid acts to reduce levels of pH. Variations in pH must be carefully controlled in processed food because it can impact the degree of sour flavor of food, its consistency, and its shelf-life. Speaking of the latter, lactic acid is a safe preservative frequently used in processed food due to its ability (like many other natural acids such as vinegar and citric acid) to limit microbial growth.Examples of uses of lactic acid in processed foods include: sourdough bread, beer, wine, bottled beverages and alcoholic cocktails with a sour flavor, meat products, and dried egg white. In bottled Spanish olives, it prevents spoilage and stalls further fermentation. Controlling pH is particularly important in every type of dairy product, from butter, to cheese, to yogurt and other fermented milk products. In dairy cheese production, lactic acid is also a natural flavoring agent.In cosmetics, lactic acid is currently a very popular type of alpha hydroxy acid (AHA), which is marketed to help heal acne and reduce winkles. It achieves these goals mainly by exfoliating the skin (sluffing off the top layer). However, according to the FDA, lactic acid increases the skin's sensitivity to damage from the sun, so if you go outside much, you could be defeating the purpose of reducing wrinkles if you utilize cosmetics that contain lactic acid.

Review: So delicious, they are to die for. These little cookies are so delicious, they are to die for. I like to keep them in the fridge and enjoy them with glass of unsweetened almond milk as a treat.I LOVE all of them with Chocolate Chip being my favorite. I am anxious to try all the flavors and all the keto friendly treats by HighKeyI tried many Keto products and this is one of three Keto foods that will I will continue to buy as I transition to my permanent low card food plan. Product Title: Stacy's Flavored Pita Chips, 1 Ounce (Pack of 24)
Review: Ah, FELLOW AMAZONIANS, THE SACRIFICES I made to bring you this review :-). Before writing a review of these, I tried all three flavors over 24 hours. How ELSE could I do a proper review?!THINGS I LOVE:TASTE - Well if they don't TASTE good, nothing else really matters. I tried the GARLIC and HERB first as I was a tad reticent. I am not a big fan of garlic. Not bad, but if you really don't like garlic, you won't like these. Not horrible. NOT my fav. It's a small bag, so you're not eating a bunch.The CHEESE was yummy, flaky and crispy. DEFINITELY would buy again.Strangely, I like the SEA SALT BEST. JUST the right amount of salt, light and flaky. PERFECT for dips. YUMMY on their own.TEXTURE - next to taste, TEXTURE is huge. I was a little concerned this would be SO much thinner, wouldn't work well with dips. Well, for me, they do. Now if you were going to try to put a lot on them, really scoop up something heavy, maybe not. BUT considering HOW FLAKY (LOVE THAT) and CRISPY (LOVE THAT TOO), these make good little dippers!THE TEXTURE of these chips is AMAZING. I like to crumble them up and put on top of anything that needs a bit of crunch. Get creative. Casseroles, sandwiches, I make rice dishes that just need a bit of crunch, these are great. OH and the CHEESE chips are PERFECT crumbled on top of mac n cheese before serving!PRICE - FOR 24 BAGS, EXCELLENT price. With tax, they were about 11 bucks. Granted, small sizes, but PERFECT size for me.FRESHNESS - They tasted VERY fresh.NO REAL CONS, BUT ONE: CHECK EXPIRATION DATE! These are not made to be shelf stable forever, which is why they're flaky. So expiration date is not usually very far off. Out of multiple orders, I only got one order that the expiration date was passed by the time I received them.

Product Title: MOM Brands Better Oats Revolution Steel Cut, Classic, 11.6 Ounce
Review: MOM Knows Best! An instant steel cut oatmeal?Are you kidding me?Any oatmeal that comes out of the microwave is a vile, gooey, slimy, mess.Steel cut oats are chewy...a perfect balance of comfort and health.And they take a half hour to prepare.I make steel cut oats quite often, usually in big batches so they can be reheated over the course of a few days.When I saw these, I thought I'd give them a try.Never have I been so happy to be wrong about a product. Unbelievably, these oats actually have the taste and texture close to slow cooked steel cut oats. They are even packaged cleverly. The box turns into a holder so that they can sit invitingly on the counter top.To microwave, tear open the top of a pouch, empty into a bowl or mug, and (drum roll) you fill the empty pouch to the water line with cold water, stir and nuke. No measuring cup needed! Also no need to stir halfway.I like my oats extra chewy so I use slightly less water and shave a few seconds off the cook time.Brown sugar, perhaps a bit of butter or a splash of cream, and get ready for a perfect day.
